208 
209 namespace {
210 // These variables provide access to the current embedded blob without requiring
211 // an isolate instance. This is needed e.g. by
212 // InstructionStream::InstructionStart, which may not have access to an isolate
213 // but still needs to access the embedded blob. The variables are initialized by
214 // each isolate in Init(). Writes and reads are relaxed since we can guarantee
215 // that the current thread has initialized these variables before accessing
216 // them. Different threads may race, but this is fine since they all attempt to
217 // set the same values of the blob pointer and size.
218 
219 std::atomic<const uint8_t*> current_embedded_blob_code_(nullptr);
220 std::atomic<uint32_t> current_embedded_blob_code_size_(0);
221 std::atomic<const uint8_t*> current_embedded_blob_data_(nullptr);
222 std::atomic<uint32_t> current_embedded_blob_data_size_(0);
223 
224 // The various workflows around embedded snapshots are fairly complex. We need
225 // to support plain old snapshot builds, nosnap builds, and the requirements of
226 // subtly different serialization tests. There's two related knobs to twiddle:
227 //
228 // - The default embedded blob may be overridden by setting the sticky embedded
229 // blob. This is set automatically whenever we create a new embedded blob.
230 //
231 // - Lifecycle management can be either manual or set to refcounting.
232 //
233 // A few situations to demonstrate their use:
234 //
235 // - A plain old snapshot build neither overrides the default blob nor
236 // refcounts.
237 //
238 // - mksnapshot sets the sticky blob and manually frees the embedded
239 // blob once done.
240 //
241 // - Most serializer tests do the same.
242 //
243 // - Nosnapshot builds set the sticky blob and enable refcounting.
244 
245 // This mutex protects access to the following variables:
246 // - sticky_embedded_blob_code_
247 // - sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_
248 // - sticky_embedded_blob_data_
249 // - sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_
250 // - enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_
251 // - current_embedded_blob_refs_
252 base::LazyMutex current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_ = LAZY_MUTEX_INITIALIZER;
253 
254 const uint8_t* sticky_embedded_blob_code_ = nullptr;
255 uint32_t sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_ = 0;
256 const uint8_t* sticky_embedded_blob_data_ = nullptr;
257 uint32_t sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_ = 0;
258 
259 bool enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_ = true;
260 int current_embedded_blob_refs_ = 0;
261 
262 const uint8_t* StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() { return sticky_embedded_blob_code_; }
263 uint32_t StickyEmbeddedBlobCodeSize() {
264  return sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_;
265 }
266 const uint8_t* StickyEmbeddedBlobData() { return sticky_embedded_blob_data_; }
267 uint32_t StickyEmbeddedBlobDataSize() {
268  return sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_;
269 }
270 
271 void SetStickyEmbeddedBlob(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t code_size,
272  const uint8_t* data, uint32_t data_size) {
273  sticky_embedded_blob_code_ = code;
274  sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_ = code_size;
275  sticky_embedded_blob_data_ = data;
276  sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_ = data_size;
277 }
278 
279 } // namespace
280 
281 void DisableEmbeddedBlobRefcounting() {
282  base::MutexGuard guard(current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_.Pointer());
283  enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_ = false;
284 }
285 
286 void FreeCurrentEmbeddedBlob() {
287  CHECK(!enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_);
288  base::MutexGuard guard(current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_.Pointer());
289 
290  if (StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() == nullptr) return;
291 
292  CHECK_EQ(StickyEmbeddedBlobCode(), Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode());
293  CHECK_EQ(StickyEmbeddedBlobData(), Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobData());
294 
295  OffHeapInstructionStream::FreeOffHeapOffHeapInstructionStream(
296  const_cast<uint8_t*>(Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode()),
297  Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobCodeSize(),
298  const_cast<uint8_t*>(Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobData()),
299  Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobDataSize());
300 
301  current_embedded_blob_code_.store(nullptr, std::memory_order_relaxed);
302  current_embedded_blob_code_size_.store(0, std::memory_order_relaxed);
303  current_embedded_blob_data_.store(nullptr, std::memory_order_relaxed);
304  current_embedded_blob_data_size_.store(0, std::memory_order_relaxed);
305  sticky_embedded_blob_code_ = nullptr;
306  sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_ = 0;
307  sticky_embedded_blob_data_ = nullptr;
308  sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_ = 0;
309 }
310 
311 // static
312 bool Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobIsBinaryEmbedded() {
313  // In some situations, we must be able to rely on the embedded blob being
314  // immortal immovable. This is the case if the blob is binary-embedded.
315  // See blob lifecycle controls above for descriptions of when the current
316  // embedded blob may change (e.g. in tests or mksnapshot). If the blob is
317  // binary-embedded, it is immortal immovable.
318  const uint8_t* code =
319  current_embedded_blob_code_.load(std::memory_order_relaxed);
320  if (code == nullptr) return false;
321  return code == DefaultEmbeddedBlobCode();
322 }
323 
324 void Isolate::SetEmbeddedBlob(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t code_size,
325  const uint8_t* data, uint32_t data_size) {
326  CHECK_NOT_NULL(code);
327  CHECK_NOT_NULL(data);
328 
329  embedded_blob_code_ = code;
330  embedded_blob_code_size_ = code_size;
331  embedded_blob_data_ = data;
332  embedded_blob_data_size_ = data_size;
333  current_embedded_blob_code_.store(code, std::memory_order_relaxed);
334  current_embedded_blob_code_size_.store(code_size, std::memory_order_relaxed);
335  current_embedded_blob_data_.store(data, std::memory_order_relaxed);
336  current_embedded_blob_data_size_.store(data_size, std::memory_order_relaxed);
337 
338 #ifdef DEBUG
339  // Verify that the contents of the embedded blob are unchanged from
340  // serialization-time, just to ensure the compiler isn't messing with us.
341  EmbeddedData d = EmbeddedData::FromBlob();
342  if (d.EmbeddedBlobDataHash() != d.CreateEmbeddedBlobDataHash()) {
343  FATAL(
344  "Embedded blob data section checksum verification failed. This "
345  "indicates that the embedded blob has been modified since compilation "
346  "time.");
347  }
348  if (v8_flags.text_is_readable) {
349  if (d.EmbeddedBlobCodeHash() != d.CreateEmbeddedBlobCodeHash()) {
350  FATAL(
351  "Embedded blob code section checksum verification failed. This "
352  "indicates that the embedded blob has been modified since "
353  "compilation time. A common cause is a debugging breakpoint set "
354  "within builtin code.");
355  }
356  }
357 #endif // DEBUG
358 }
359 
360 void Isolate::ClearEmbeddedBlob() {
361  CHECK(enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_);
362  CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_code_, CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode());
363  CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_code_, StickyEmbeddedBlobCode());
364  CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_data_, CurrentEmbeddedBlobData());
365  CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_data_, StickyEmbeddedBlobData());
366 
367  embedded_blob_code_ = nullptr;
368  embedded_blob_code_size_ = 0;
369  embedded_blob_data_ = nullptr;
370  embedded_blob_data_size_ = 0;
371  current_embedded_blob_code_.store(nullptr, std::memory_order_relaxed);
372  current_embedded_blob_code_size_.store(0, std::memory_order_relaxed);
373  current_embedded_blob_data_.store(nullptr, std::memory_order_relaxed);
374  current_embedded_blob_data_size_.store(0, std::memory_order_relaxed);
375  sticky_embedded_blob_code_ = nullptr;
376  sticky_embedded_blob_code_size_ = 0;
377  sticky_embedded_blob_data_ = nullptr;
378  sticky_embedded_blob_data_size_ = 0;
379 }

414 // static
415 base::AddressRegion Isolate::GetShortBuiltinsCallRegion() {
416  // Update calculations below if the assert fails.
417  static_assert(kMaxPCRelativeCodeRangeInMB <= 4096);
418  if (kMaxPCRelativeCodeRangeInMB == 0) {
419  // Return empty region if pc-relative calls/jumps are not supported.
420  return base::AddressRegion(kNullAddress, 0);
421  }
422  constexpr size_t max_size = std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max();
423  if (uint64_t{kMaxPCRelativeCodeRangeInMB} * MB > max_size) {
424  // The whole addressable space is reachable with pc-relative calls/jumps.
425  return base::AddressRegion(kNullAddress, max_size);
426  }
427  constexpr size_t radius = kMaxPCRelativeCodeRangeInMB * MB;
428 
429  DCHECK_LT(CurrentEmbeddedBlobCodeSize(), radius);
430  Address embedded_blob_code_start =
431  reinterpret_cast<Address>(CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode());
432  if (embedded_blob_code_start == kNullAddress) {
433  // Return empty region if there's no embedded blob.
434  return base::AddressRegion(kNullAddress, 0);
435  }
436  Address embedded_blob_code_end =
437  embedded_blob_code_start + CurrentEmbeddedBlobCodeSize();
438  Address region_start =
439  (embedded_blob_code_end > radius) ? (embedded_blob_code_end - radius) : 0;
440  Address region_end = embedded_blob_code_start + radius;
441  if (region_end < embedded_blob_code_start) {
442  region_end = static_cast<Address>(-1);
443  }
444  return base::AddressRegion(region_start, region_end - region_start);
445 }
446 
447 size_t Isolate::HashIsolateForEmbeddedBlob() {
448  DCHECK(builtins_.is_initialized());
449  DCHECK(Builtins::AllBuiltinsAreIsolateIndependent());
450 
451  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
452 
453  static constexpr size_t kSeed = 0;
454  size_t hash = kSeed;
455 
456  // Hash static entries of the roots table.
457  hash = base::hash_combine(hash, V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL);
458 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
459  hash = base::hash_combine(hash,
460  static_cast<int>(RootIndex::kReadOnlyRootsCount));
461  RootIndex i = RootIndex::kFirstReadOnlyRoot;
462  for (auto ptr : StaticReadOnlyRootsPointerTable) {
463  hash = base::hash_combine(ptr, hash);
464  ++i;
465  }
466 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
467 
468  // Hash data sections of builtin code objects.
469  for (Builtin builtin = Builtins::kFirst; builtin <= Builtins::kLast;
470  ++builtin) {
471 #if V8_ENABLE_GEARBOX
472  if (Builtins::IsGearboxPlaceholder(builtin)) {
473  // When v8 enables gearbox for builtins, there are 3 builtin objects for a
474  // builtin, one is generic variant, another one is ISX variant, and final
475  // one is a placeholder, it will be set as either generic or ISX variant
476  // at runtime. Therefore v8 will modify the contents of the placeholder
477  // code object when it is being launched, so we didn't take it into the
478  // hash calculation, otherwise it will cause hash check failed.
479  continue;
480  }
481 #endif
482  Tagged<Code> code = builtins()->code(builtin);
483 
484  DCHECK(Internals::HasHeapObjectTag(code.ptr()));
485  uint8_t* const code_ptr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(code.address());
486 
487  // These static asserts ensure we don't miss relevant fields. We don't hash
488  // instruction_start, but other data fields must remain the same.
489  static_assert(Code::kEndOfStrongFieldsOffset ==
490  Code::kInstructionStartOffset);
491 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
492  static_assert(
493  Code::kInstructionStartOffsetEnd + 1 +
494  (V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL ? kJSDispatchHandleSize : 0) ==
495  Code::kFlagsOffset);
496 #endif
497  static_assert(Code::kFlagsOffsetEnd + 1 == Code::kInstructionSizeOffset);
498  static_assert(Code::kInstructionSizeOffsetEnd + 1 ==
499  Code::kMetadataSizeOffset);
500  static_assert(Code::kMetadataSizeOffsetEnd + 1 ==
501  Code::kInlinedBytecodeSizeOffset);
502  static_assert(Code::kInlinedBytecodeSizeOffsetEnd + 1 ==
503  Code::kOsrOffsetOffset);
504  static_assert(Code::kOsrOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
505  Code::kHandlerTableOffsetOffset);
506  static_assert(Code::kHandlerTableOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
507  Code::kUnwindingInfoOffsetOffset);
508  static_assert(Code::kUnwindingInfoOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
509  Code::kConstantPoolOffsetOffset);
510  static_assert(Code::kConstantPoolOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
511  Code::kCodeCommentsOffsetOffset);
512  static_assert(Code::kCodeCommentsOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
513  Code::kJumpTableInfoOffsetOffset);
514  static_assert(Code::kJumpTableInfoOffsetOffsetEnd + 1 ==
515  Code::kParameterCountOffset);
516  static_assert(Code::kParameterCountOffsetEnd + 1 == Code::kBuiltinIdOffset);
517  static_assert(Code::kBuiltinIdOffsetEnd + 1 == Code::kUnalignedSize);
518  static constexpr int kStartOffset = Code::kFlagsOffset;
519 
520  for (int j = kStartOffset; j < Code::kUnalignedSize; j++) {
521  hash = base::hash_combine(hash, size_t{code_ptr[j]});
522  }
523  }
524 
525  // The builtins constants table is also tightly tied to embedded builtins.
526  hash = base::hash_combine(
527  hash, static_cast<size_t>(heap_.builtins_constants_table()->length()));
528 
529  return hash;
530 }

546 Isolate::PerIsolateThreadData*
547 Isolate::FindOrAllocatePerThreadDataForThisThread() {
548  ThreadId thread_id = ThreadId::Current();
549  PerIsolateThreadData* per_thread = nullptr;
550  {
551  base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&thread_data_table_mutex_);
552  per_thread = thread_data_table_.Lookup(thread_id);
553  if (per_thread == nullptr) {
554  if (v8_flags.adjust_os_scheduling_parameters) {
555  base::OS::AdjustSchedulingParams();
556  }
557  per_thread = new PerIsolateThreadData(this, thread_id);
558  thread_data_table_.Insert(per_thread);
559  }
560  DCHECK(thread_data_table_.Lookup(thread_id) == per_thread);
561  }
562  return per_thread;
563 }
564 
565 void Isolate::DiscardPerThreadDataForThisThread() {
566  ThreadId thread_id = ThreadId::TryGetCurrent();
567  if (thread_id.IsValid()) {
568  DCHECK_NE(thread_manager_->mutex_owner_.load(std::memory_order_relaxed),
569  thread_id);
570  base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&thread_data_table_mutex_);
571  PerIsolateThreadData* per_thread = thread_data_table_.Lookup(thread_id);
572  if (per_thread) {
573  DCHECK(!per_thread->thread_state_);
574  thread_data_table_.Remove(per_thread);
575  }
576  }
577 }

599 
600 char* Isolate::Iterate(RootVisitor* v, char* thread_storage) {
601  ThreadLocalTop* thread = reinterpret_cast<ThreadLocalTop*>(thread_storage);
602  Iterate(v, thread);
603  // Normally, ThreadLocalTop::topmost_script_having_context_ is visited weakly
604  // but in order to simplify handling of frozen threads we just clear it.
605  // Otherwise, we'd need to traverse the thread_storage again just to find this
606  // one field.
607  thread->topmost_script_having_context_ = Context();
608  return thread_storage + sizeof(ThreadLocalTop);
609 }
610 
611 void Isolate::IterateThread(ThreadVisitor* v, char* t) {
612  ThreadLocalTop* thread = reinterpret_cast<ThreadLocalTop*>(t);
613  v->VisitThread(this, thread);
614 }
615 
616 void Isolate::Iterate(RootVisitor* v, ThreadLocalTop* thread) {
617  // Visit the roots from the top for a given thread.
618  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
619  FullObjectSlot(&thread->exception_));
620  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
621  FullObjectSlot(&thread->pending_message_));
622  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
623  FullObjectSlot(&thread->context_));
624 
625  for (v8::TryCatch* block = thread->try_catch_handler_; block != nullptr;
626  block = block->next_) {
627  // TODO(3770): Make TryCatch::exception_ an Address (and message_obj_ too).
628  v->VisitRootPointer(
629  Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
630  FullObjectSlot(reinterpret_cast<Address>(&(block->exception_))));
631  v->VisitRootPointer(
632  Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
633  FullObjectSlot(reinterpret_cast<Address>(&(block->message_obj_))));
634  }
635 
636  v->VisitRootPointer(
637  Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
638  FullObjectSlot(continuation_preserved_embedder_data_address()));
639 
640  // Iterate over pointers on native execution stack.
641 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
642  wasm::WasmCodeRefScope wasm_code_ref_scope;
643 
644  for (const std::unique_ptr<wasm::StackMemory>& stack : wasm_stacks_) {
645  if (stack->IsActive()) {
646  continue;
647  }
648  stack->Iterate(v, this);
649  }
650  StackFrameIterator it(this, thread, StackFrameIterator::FirstStackOnly{});
651 #else
652  StackFrameIterator it(this, thread);
653 #endif
654  for (; !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
655  it.frame()->Iterate(v);
656  }
657 }
658 
659 void Isolate::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) {
660  ThreadLocalTop* current_t = thread_local_top();
661  Iterate(v, current_t);
662 }
663 
664 void Isolate::RegisterTryCatchHandler(v8::TryCatch* that) {
665  thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_ = that;
666 }
667 
668 void Isolate::UnregisterTryCatchHandler(v8::TryCatch* that) {
669  DCHECK_EQ(thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_, that);
670  thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_ = that->next_;
671  SimulatorStack::UnregisterJSStackComparableAddress(this);
672 }

674 DirectHandle<String> Isolate::StackTraceString() {
675  if (stack_trace_nesting_level_ == 0) {
676  stack_trace_nesting_level_++;
677  HeapStringAllocator allocator;
678  StringStream::ClearMentionedObjectCache(this);
679  StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
680  incomplete_message_ = &accumulator;
681  PrintStack(&accumulator);
682  DirectHandle<String> stack_trace = accumulator.ToString(this);
683  incomplete_message_ = nullptr;
684  stack_trace_nesting_level_ = 0;
685  return stack_trace;
686  } else if (stack_trace_nesting_level_ == 1) {
687  stack_trace_nesting_level_++;
688  base::OS::PrintError(
689  "\n\nAttempt to print stack while printing stack (double fault)\n");
690  base::OS::PrintError(
691  "If you are lucky you may find a partial stack dump on stdout.\n\n");
692  incomplete_message_->OutputToStdOut();
693  return factory()->empty_string();
694  } else {
695  base::OS::Abort();
696  }
697 }

735 void StackTraceFailureMessage::Print() volatile {
736  // Print the details of this failure message object, including its own address
737  // to force stack allocation.
738  static_assert(arraysize(ptrs_) >= 6);
739  base::OS::PrintError(
740  "Stacktrace:\n ptr0=%p\n ptr1=%p\n ptr2=%p\n ptr3=%p\n "
741  "ptr4=%p\n ptr5=%p\n failure_message_object=%p\n%s",
742  reinterpret_cast<void*>(ptrs_[0]), reinterpret_cast<void*>(ptrs_[1]),
743  reinterpret_cast<void*>(ptrs_[2]), reinterpret_cast<void*>(ptrs_[3]),
744  reinterpret_cast<void*>(ptrs_[4]), reinterpret_cast<void*>(ptrs_[5]),
745  this, &js_stack_trace_[0]);
746 }
747 
748 StackTraceFailureMessage::StackTraceFailureMessage(
749  Isolate* isolate, StackTraceFailureMessage::StackTraceMode mode,
750  const Address* ptrs, size_t ptrs_count)
751  : isolate_(isolate) {
752  size_t ptrs_size = std::min(arraysize(ptrs_), ptrs_count);
753  std::copy(ptrs, ptrs + ptrs_size, &ptrs_[0]);
754 
755  if (mode == kIncludeStackTrace) {
756  // Write a stracktrace into the {js_stack_trace_} buffer.
757  const size_t buffer_length = arraysize(js_stack_trace_);
758  FixedStringAllocator fixed(&js_stack_trace_[0], buffer_length - 1);
759  StringStream accumulator(&fixed, StringStream::kPrintObjectConcise);
760  isolate_->PrintStack(&accumulator, Isolate::kPrintStackVerbose);
761  // Keeping a reference to the last code objects to increase likelihood that
762  // they get included in the minidump.
763  const size_t code_objects_length = arraysize(code_objects_);
764  size_t i = 0;
765  StackFrameIterator it(isolate_);
766  for (; !it.done() && i < code_objects_length; it.Advance()) {
767  code_objects_[i++] = it.frame()->unchecked_code().ptr();
768  }
769  }
770 }

772 bool NoExtension(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>&) { return false; }

775 
776 bool IsBuiltinFunction(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<HeapObject> object,
777  Builtin builtin) {
778  if (!IsJSFunction(object)) return false;
779  Tagged<JSFunction> const function = Cast<JSFunction>(object);
780  // Currently we have to use full pointer comparison here as builtin Code
781  // objects are still inside the sandbox while runtime-generated Code objects
782  // are in trusted space.
783  static_assert(!kAllCodeObjectsLiveInTrustedSpace);
784  return function->code(isolate).SafeEquals(isolate->builtins()->code(builtin));
785 }
786 
787 // Check if the function is one of the known async function or
788 // async generator fulfill handlers.
789 bool IsBuiltinAsyncFulfillHandler(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
790  return IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object,
791  Builtin::kAsyncFunctionAwaitResolveClosure) ||
792  IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object,
793  Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorAwaitResolveClosure) ||
794  IsBuiltinFunction(
795  isolate, object,
796  Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorYieldWithAwaitResolveClosure);
797 }
798 
799 // Check if the function is one of the known async function or
800 // async generator fulfill handlers.
801 bool IsBuiltinAsyncRejectHandler(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
802  return IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object,
803  Builtin::kAsyncFunctionAwaitRejectClosure) ||
804  IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object,
805  Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorAwaitRejectClosure);
806 }
807 
808 // Check if the function is one of the known builtin rejection handlers that
809 // rethrows the exception instead of catching it.
810 bool IsBuiltinForwardingRejectHandler(Isolate* isolate,
811  Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
812  return IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object, Builtin::kPromiseCatchFinally) ||
813  IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, object,
814  Builtin::kAsyncFromSyncIteratorCloseSyncAndRethrow);
815 }
816 
817 MaybeHandle<JSGeneratorObject> TryGetAsyncGenerator(
818  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<PromiseReaction> reaction) {
819  // Check if the {reaction} has one of the known async function or
820  // async generator continuations as its fulfill handler.
821  if (IsBuiltinAsyncFulfillHandler(isolate, reaction->fulfill_handler())) {
822  // Now peek into the handlers' AwaitContext to get to
823  // the JSGeneratorObject for the async function.
824  DirectHandle<Context> context(
825  Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->fulfill_handler())->context(), isolate);
826  Handle<JSGeneratorObject> generator_object(
827  Cast<JSGeneratorObject>(context->extension()), isolate);
828  return generator_object;
829  }
830  return MaybeHandle<JSGeneratorObject>();
831 }
832 
833 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
834 MaybeDirectHandle<WasmSuspenderObject> TryGetWasmSuspender(
835  Isolate* isolate, Tagged<HeapObject> handler) {
836  // Check if the {handler} is WasmResume.
837  if (IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, handler, Builtin::kWasmResume)) {
838  // Now peek into the handlers' AwaitContext to get to
839  // the JSGeneratorObject for the async function.
840  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = Cast<JSFunction>(handler)->shared();
841  if (shared->HasWasmResumeData()) {
842  return direct_handle(shared->wasm_resume_data()->suspender(), isolate);
843  }
844  }
845  return MaybeDirectHandle<WasmSuspenderObject>();
846 }
847 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

849 int GetGeneratorBytecodeOffset(
850  DirectHandle<JSGeneratorObject> generator_object) {
851  // The stored bytecode offset is relative to a different base than what
852  // is used in the source position table, hence the subtraction.
853  return Smi::ToInt(generator_object->input_or_debug_pos()) -
854  (BytecodeArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag);
855 }
856 
857 class CallSiteBuilder {
858  public:
859  CallSiteBuilder(Isolate* isolate, FrameSkipMode mode, int limit,
860  Handle<Object> caller)
861  : isolate_(isolate),
862  mode_(mode),
863  limit_(limit),
864  caller_(caller),
865  skip_next_frame_(mode != SKIP_NONE) {
866  DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode_ == SKIP_UNTIL_SEEN, IsJSFunction(*caller_));
867  // Modern web applications are usually built with multiple layers of
868  // framework and library code, and stack depth tends to be more than
869  // a dozen frames, so we over-allocate a bit here to avoid growing
870  // the elements array in the common case.
871  elements_ = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(std::min(64, limit));
872  }
873 
874  void SetPrevFrameAsConstructCall() {
875  if (skipped_prev_frame_) return;
876  DCHECK_GT(index_, 0);
877  Tagged<CallSiteInfo> info =
878  Tagged<CallSiteInfo>::cast(elements_->get(index_ - 1));
879  info->set_flags(info->flags() | CallSiteInfo::kIsConstructor);
880  }
881 
882  bool Visit(FrameSummary const& summary) {
883  if (Full()) return false;
884 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
885 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
886  if (summary.IsWasmInterpreted()) {
887  AppendWasmInterpretedFrame(summary.AsWasmInterpreted());
888  return true;
889  // FrameSummary::IsWasm() should be renamed FrameSummary::IsWasmCompiled
890  // to be more precise, but we'll leave it as it is to try to reduce merge
891  // churn.
892  } else {
893 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
894  if (summary.IsWasm()) {
895  AppendWasmFrame(summary.AsWasm());
896  return true;
897  }
898 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
899  }
900 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
901  if (summary.IsWasmInlined()) {
902  AppendWasmInlinedFrame(summary.AsWasmInlined());
903  return true;
904  }
905  if (summary.IsBuiltin()) {
906  AppendBuiltinFrame(summary.AsBuiltin());
907  return true;
908  }
909 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
910  AppendJavaScriptFrame(summary.AsJavaScript());
911  return true;
912  }
913 
914  void AppendAsyncFrame(DirectHandle<JSGeneratorObject> generator_object) {
915  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function(generator_object->function(), isolate_);
916  if (!IsVisibleInStackTrace(function)) {
917  skipped_prev_frame_ = true;
918  return;
919  }
920  int flags = CallSiteInfo::kIsAsync;
921  if (IsStrictFrame(function)) flags |= CallSiteInfo::kIsStrict;
922 
923  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver(generator_object->receiver(), isolate_);
924  DirectHandle<BytecodeArray> code(
925  function->shared()->GetBytecodeArray(isolate_), isolate_);
926  int offset = GetGeneratorBytecodeOffset(generator_object);
927 
928  DirectHandle<FixedArray> parameters =
929  isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array();
930  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.detailed_error_stack_trace)) {
931  parameters = isolate_->factory()->CopyFixedArrayUpTo(
932  direct_handle(generator_object->parameters_and_registers(), isolate_),
933  function->shared()
934  ->internal_formal_parameter_count_without_receiver());
935  }
936 
937  AppendFrame(receiver, function, code, offset, flags, parameters);
938  }
939 
940  void AppendPromiseCombinatorFrame(DirectHandle<JSFunction> element_function,
941  DirectHandle<JSFunction> combinator) {
942  if (!IsVisibleInStackTrace(combinator)) {
943  skipped_prev_frame_ = true;
944  return;
945  }
946  int flags =
947  CallSiteInfo::kIsAsync | CallSiteInfo::kIsSourcePositionComputed;
948 
949  DirectHandle<JSFunction> receiver(
950  combinator->native_context()->promise_function(), isolate_);
951  DirectHandle<Code> code(combinator->code(isolate_), isolate_);
952 
953  // TODO(mmarchini) save Promises list from the Promise combinator
954  DirectHandle<FixedArray> parameters =
955  isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array();
956 
957  // We store the offset of the promise into the element function's
958  // hash field for element callbacks.
959  int promise_index = Smi::ToInt(element_function->GetIdentityHash()) - 1;
960 
961  AppendFrame(receiver, combinator, code, promise_index, flags, parameters);
962  }
963 
964  void AppendJavaScriptFrame(
965  FrameSummary::JavaScriptFrameSummary const& summary) {
966  // Filter out internal frames that we do not want to show.
967  if (!IsVisibleInStackTrace(summary.function())) {
968  skipped_prev_frame_ = true;
969  return;
970  }
971 
972  int flags = 0;
973  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = summary.function();
974  if (IsStrictFrame(function)) flags |= CallSiteInfo::kIsStrict;
975  if (summary.is_constructor()) flags |= CallSiteInfo::kIsConstructor;
976 
977  AppendFrame(Cast<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>>(summary.receiver()), function,
978  summary.abstract_code(), summary.code_offset(), flags,
979  summary.parameters());
980  }
981 
982 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
983  void AppendWasmFrame(FrameSummary::WasmFrameSummary const& summary) {
984  if (summary.code()->kind() != wasm::WasmCode::kWasmFunction) return;
985  DirectHandle<WasmInstanceObject> instance = summary.wasm_instance();
986  int flags = CallSiteInfo::kIsWasm;
987  if (instance->module_object()->is_asm_js()) {
988  flags |= CallSiteInfo::kIsAsmJsWasm;
989  if (summary.at_to_number_conversion()) {
990  flags |= CallSiteInfo::kIsAsmJsAtNumberConversion;
991  }
992  }
993 
994  DirectHandle<HeapObject> code = isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
995  AppendFrame(instance,
996  direct_handle(Smi::FromInt(summary.function_index()), isolate_),
997  code, summary.code_offset(), flags,
998  isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
999  }
1000 
1001 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1002  void AppendWasmInterpretedFrame(
1003  FrameSummary::WasmInterpretedFrameSummary const& summary) {
1004  Handle<WasmInstanceObject> instance = summary.wasm_instance();
1005  int flags = CallSiteInfo::kIsWasm | CallSiteInfo::kIsWasmInterpretedFrame;
1006  DCHECK(!instance->module_object()->is_asm_js());
1007  // We don't have any code object in the interpreter, so we pass 'undefined'.
1008  auto code = isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
1009  AppendFrame(instance,
1010  handle(Smi::FromInt(summary.function_index()), isolate_), code,
1011  summary.byte_offset(), flags,
1012  isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
1013  }
1014 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1015 
1016  void AppendWasmInlinedFrame(
1017  FrameSummary::WasmInlinedFrameSummary const& summary) {
1018  DirectHandle<HeapObject> code = isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
1019  int flags = CallSiteInfo::kIsWasm;
1020  AppendFrame(summary.wasm_instance(),
1021  direct_handle(Smi::FromInt(summary.function_index()), isolate_),
1022  code, summary.code_offset(), flags,
1023  isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
1024  }
1025 
1026  void AppendBuiltinFrame(FrameSummary::BuiltinFrameSummary const& summary) {
1027  Builtin builtin = summary.builtin();
1028  DirectHandle<Code> code = isolate_->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
1029  DirectHandle<Smi> function(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(builtin)),
1030  isolate_);
1031  int flags = CallSiteInfo::kIsBuiltin;
1032  AppendFrame(Cast<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>>(summary.receiver()), function, code,
1033  summary.code_offset(), flags,
1034  isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
1035  }
1036 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1037 
1038  bool Full() { return index_ >= limit_; }
1039 
1040  Handle<FixedArray> Build() {
1041  return FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate_, elements_, index_);
1042  }
1043 
1044  private:
1045  // Poison stack frames below the first strict mode frame.
1046  // The stack trace API should not expose receivers and function
1047  // objects on frames deeper than the top-most one with a strict mode
1048  // function.
1049  bool IsStrictFrame(DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
1050  if (!encountered_strict_function_) {
1051  encountered_strict_function_ =
1052  is_strict(function->shared()->language_mode());
1053  }
1054  return encountered_strict_function_;
1055  }
1056 
1057  // Determines whether the given stack frame should be displayed in a stack
1058  // trace.
1059  bool IsVisibleInStackTrace(DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
1060  return ShouldIncludeFrame(function) && IsNotHidden(function);
1061  }
1062 
1063  // This mechanism excludes a number of uninteresting frames from the stack
1064  // trace. This can be be the first frame (which will be a builtin-exit frame
1065  // for the error constructor builtin) or every frame until encountering a
1066  // user-specified function.
1067  bool ShouldIncludeFrame(DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
1068  switch (mode_) {
1069  case SKIP_NONE:
1070  return true;
1071  case SKIP_FIRST:
1072  if (!skip_next_frame_) return true;
1073  skip_next_frame_ = false;
1074  return false;
1075  case SKIP_UNTIL_SEEN:
1076  if (skip_next_frame_ && (*function == *caller_)) {
1077  skip_next_frame_ = false;
1078  return false;
1079  }
1080  return !skip_next_frame_;
1081  }
1082  UNREACHABLE();
1083  }
1084 
1085  bool IsNotHidden(DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
1086  // TODO(szuend): Remove this check once the flag is enabled
1087  // by default.
1088  if (!v8_flags.experimental_stack_trace_frames &&
1089  function->shared()->IsApiFunction()) {
1090  return false;
1091  }
1092  // Functions defined not in user scripts are not visible unless directly
1093  // exposed, in which case the native flag is set.
1094  // The --builtins-in-stack-traces command line flag allows including
1095  // internal call sites in the stack trace for debugging purposes.
1096  if (!v8_flags.builtins_in_stack_traces &&
1097  !function->shared()->IsUserJavaScript()) {
1098  return function->shared()->native() ||
1099  function->shared()->IsApiFunction();
1100  }
1101  return true;
1102  }
1103 
1104  void AppendFrame(DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>> receiver_or_instance,
1105  DirectHandle<UnionOf<Smi, JSFunction>> function,
1106  DirectHandle<HeapObject> code, int offset, int flags,
1107  DirectHandle<FixedArray> parameters) {
1108  if (IsTheHole(*receiver_or_instance, isolate_)) {
1109  // TODO(jgruber): Fix all cases in which frames give us a hole value
1110  // (e.g. the receiver in RegExp constructor frames).
1111  receiver_or_instance = isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
1112  }
1113  auto info = isolate_->factory()->NewCallSiteInfo(
1114  Cast<JSAny>(receiver_or_instance), function, code, offset, flags,
1115  parameters);
1116  elements_ = FixedArray::SetAndGrow(isolate_, elements_, index_++, info);
1117  skipped_prev_frame_ = false;
1118  }
1119 
1120  Isolate* isolate_;
1121  const FrameSkipMode mode_;
1122  int index_ = 0;
1123  const int limit_;
1124  const Handle<Object> caller_;
1125  bool skip_next_frame_;
1126  bool skipped_prev_frame_ = false;
1127  bool encountered_strict_function_ = false;
1128  Handle<FixedArray> elements_;
1129 };
1130 
1131 void CaptureAsyncStackTrace(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
1132  CallSiteBuilder* builder) {
1133  while (!builder->Full()) {
1134  // Check that the {promise} is not settled.
1135  if (promise->status() != Promise::kPending) return;
1136 
1137  // Check that we have exactly one PromiseReaction on the {promise}.
1138  if (!IsPromiseReaction(promise->reactions())) return;
1139  DirectHandle<PromiseReaction> reaction(
1140  Cast<PromiseReaction>(promise->reactions()), isolate);
1141  if (!IsSmi(reaction->next())) return;
1142 
1143  Handle<JSGeneratorObject> generator_object;
1144 
1145  if (TryGetAsyncGenerator(isolate, reaction).ToHandle(&generator_object)) {
1146  CHECK(generator_object->is_suspended());
1147 
1148  // Append async frame corresponding to the {generator_object}.
1149  builder->AppendAsyncFrame(generator_object);
1150 
1151  // Try to continue from here.
1152  if (IsJSAsyncFunctionObject(*generator_object)) {
1153  auto async_function_object =
1154  Cast<JSAsyncFunctionObject>(generator_object);
1155  promise = direct_handle(async_function_object->promise(), isolate);
1156  } else {
1157  auto async_generator_object =
1158  Cast<JSAsyncGeneratorObject>(generator_object);
1159  if (IsUndefined(async_generator_object->queue(), isolate)) return;
1160  DirectHandle<AsyncGeneratorRequest> async_generator_request(
1161  Cast<AsyncGeneratorRequest>(async_generator_object->queue()),
1162  isolate);
1163  promise = direct_handle(
1164  Cast<JSPromise>(async_generator_request->promise()), isolate);
1165  }
1166  } else if (IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, reaction->fulfill_handler(),
1167  Builtin::kPromiseAllResolveElementClosure)) {
1168  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function(
1169  Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->fulfill_handler()), isolate);
1170  DirectHandle<Context> context(function->context(), isolate);
1171  DirectHandle<JSFunction> combinator(
1172  context->native_context()->promise_all(), isolate);
1173  builder->AppendPromiseCombinatorFrame(function, combinator);
1174 
1175  if (IsNativeContext(*context)) {
1176  // NativeContext is used as a marker that the closure was already
1177  // called. We can't access the reject element context any more.
1178  return;
1179  }
1180 
1181  // Now peek into the Promise.all() resolve element context to
1182  // find the promise capability that's being resolved when all
1183  // the concurrent promises resolve.
1184  int const index =
1185  PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseAllResolveElementCapabilitySlot;
1186  DirectHandle<PromiseCapability> capability(
1187  Cast<PromiseCapability>(context->GetNoCell(index)), isolate);
1188  if (!IsJSPromise(capability->promise())) return;
1189  promise = direct_handle(Cast<JSPromise>(capability->promise()), isolate);
1190  } else if (IsBuiltinFunction(
1191  isolate, reaction->fulfill_handler(),
1192  Builtin::kPromiseAllSettledResolveElementClosure)) {
1193  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function(
1194  Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->fulfill_handler()), isolate);
1195  DirectHandle<Context> context(function->context(), isolate);
1196  DirectHandle<JSFunction> combinator(
1197  context->native_context()->promise_all_settled(), isolate);
1198  builder->AppendPromiseCombinatorFrame(function, combinator);
1199 
1200  if (IsNativeContext(*context)) {
1201  // NativeContext is used as a marker that the closure was already
1202  // called. We can't access the reject element context any more.
1203  return;
1204  }
1205 
1206  // Now peek into the Promise.allSettled() resolve element context to
1207  // find the promise capability that's being resolved when all
1208  // the concurrent promises resolve.
1209  int const index =
1210  PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseAllResolveElementCapabilitySlot;
1211  DirectHandle<PromiseCapability> capability(
1212  Cast<PromiseCapability>(context->GetNoCell(index)), isolate);
1213  if (!IsJSPromise(capability->promise())) return;
1214  promise = direct_handle(Cast<JSPromise>(capability->promise()), isolate);
1215  } else if (IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, reaction->reject_handler(),
1216  Builtin::kPromiseAnyRejectElementClosure)) {
1217  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function(
1218  Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->reject_handler()), isolate);
1219  DirectHandle<Context> context(function->context(), isolate);
1220  DirectHandle<JSFunction> combinator(
1221  context->native_context()->promise_any(), isolate);
1222  builder->AppendPromiseCombinatorFrame(function, combinator);
1223 
1224  if (IsNativeContext(*context)) {
1225  // NativeContext is used as a marker that the closure was already
1226  // called. We can't access the reject element context any more.
1227  return;
1228  }
1229 
1230  // Now peek into the Promise.any() reject element context to
1231  // find the promise capability that's being resolved when any of
1232  // the concurrent promises resolve.
1233  int const index = PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseAnyRejectElementCapabilitySlot;
1234  DirectHandle<PromiseCapability> capability(
1235  Cast<PromiseCapability>(context->GetNoCell(index)), isolate);
1236  if (!IsJSPromise(capability->promise())) return;
1237  promise = direct_handle(Cast<JSPromise>(capability->promise()), isolate);
1238  } else if (IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, reaction->fulfill_handler(),
1239  Builtin::kPromiseCapabilityDefaultResolve)) {
1240  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function(
1241  Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->fulfill_handler()), isolate);
1242  DirectHandle<Context> context(function->context(), isolate);
1243  promise = direct_handle(
1244  Cast<JSPromise>(context->GetNoCell(PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseSlot)),
1245  isolate);
1246  } else {
1247  // We have some generic promise chain here, so try to
1248  // continue with the chained promise on the reaction
1249  // (only works for native promise chains).
1250  Handle<HeapObject> promise_or_capability(
1251  reaction->promise_or_capability(), isolate);
1252  if (IsJSPromise(*promise_or_capability)) {
1253  promise = Cast<JSPromise>(promise_or_capability);
1254  } else if (IsPromiseCapability(*promise_or_capability)) {
1255  auto capability = Cast<PromiseCapability>(promise_or_capability);
1256  if (!IsJSPromise(capability->promise())) return;
1257  promise =
1258  direct_handle(Cast<JSPromise>(capability->promise()), isolate);
1259  } else {
1260  // Otherwise the {promise_or_capability} must be undefined here.
1261  CHECK(IsUndefined(*promise_or_capability, isolate));
1262  return;
1263  }
1264  }
1265  }
1266 }
1267 
1268 MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise> TryGetCurrentTaskPromise(Isolate* isolate) {
1269  Handle<Object> current_microtask = isolate->factory()->current_microtask();
1270  if (IsPromiseReactionJobTask(*current_microtask)) {
1271  auto promise_reaction_job_task =
1272  Cast<PromiseReactionJobTask>(current_microtask);
1273  // Check if the {reaction} has one of the known async function or
1274  // async generator continuations as its fulfill handler.
1275  if (IsBuiltinAsyncFulfillHandler(isolate,
1276  promise_reaction_job_task->handler()) ||
1277  IsBuiltinAsyncRejectHandler(isolate,
1278  promise_reaction_job_task->handler())) {
1279  // Now peek into the handlers' AwaitContext to get to
1280  // the JSGeneratorObject for the async function.
1281  DirectHandle<Context> context(
1282  Cast<JSFunction>(promise_reaction_job_task->handler())->context(),
1283  isolate);
1284  Handle<JSGeneratorObject> generator_object(
1285  Cast<JSGeneratorObject>(context->extension()), isolate);
1286  if (generator_object->is_executing()) {
1287  if (IsJSAsyncFunctionObject(*generator_object)) {
1288  auto async_function_object =
1289  Cast<JSAsyncFunctionObject>(generator_object);
1290  DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise(async_function_object->promise(),
1291  isolate);
1292  return promise;
1293  } else {
1294  auto async_generator_object =
1295  Cast<JSAsyncGeneratorObject>(generator_object);
1296  DirectHandle<Object> queue(async_generator_object->queue(), isolate);
1297  if (!IsUndefined(*queue, isolate)) {
1298  auto async_generator_request = Cast<AsyncGeneratorRequest>(queue);
1299  DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise(
1300  Cast<JSPromise>(async_generator_request->promise()), isolate);
1301  return promise;
1302  }
1303  }
1304  }
1305  } else {
1306 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1307  DirectHandle<WasmSuspenderObject> suspender;
1308  if (TryGetWasmSuspender(isolate, promise_reaction_job_task->handler())
1309  .ToHandle(&suspender)) {
1310  // The {promise_reaction_job_task} belongs to a suspended Wasm stack
1311  return direct_handle(suspender->promise(), isolate);
1312  }
1313 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1314 
1315  // The {promise_reaction_job_task} doesn't belong to an await (or
1316  // yield inside an async generator) or a suspended Wasm stack,
1317  // but we might still be able to find an async frame if we follow
1318  // along the chain of promises on the {promise_reaction_job_task}.
1319  DirectHandle<HeapObject> promise_or_capability(
1320  promise_reaction_job_task->promise_or_capability(), isolate);
1321  if (IsJSPromise(*promise_or_capability)) {
1322  DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise =
1323  Cast<JSPromise>(promise_or_capability);
1324  return promise;
1325  }
1326  }
1327  }
1328  return MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>();
1329 }
1330 
1331 void CaptureAsyncStackTrace(Isolate* isolate, CallSiteBuilder* builder) {
1332  DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise;
1333  if (TryGetCurrentTaskPromise(isolate).ToHandle(&promise)) {
1334  CaptureAsyncStackTrace(isolate, promise, builder);
1335  }
1336 }
1337 
1338 template <typename Visitor>
1339 void VisitStack(Isolate* isolate, Visitor* visitor,
1340  StackTrace::StackTraceOptions options = StackTrace::kDetailed) {
1341  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
1342  // Keep track if we visited a stack frame, but did not visit any summarized
1343  // frames. Either because the stack frame didn't create any summarized frames
1344  // or due to security origin.
1345  bool skipped_last_frame = true;
1346  for (StackFrameIterator it(isolate); !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
1347  StackFrame* frame = it.frame();
1348  switch (frame->type()) {
1349  case StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT:
1350  case StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT:
1351  case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION:
1352  case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_WITH_CATCH:
1353  case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS:
1354  case StackFrame::MAGLEV:
1355  case StackFrame::INTERPRETED:
1356  case StackFrame::BASELINE:
1357  case StackFrame::BUILTIN:
1358 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1359  case StackFrame::STUB:
1360  case StackFrame::WASM:
1361  case StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START:
1362 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1363  case StackFrame::WASM_INTERPRETER_ENTRY:
1364 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1365 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1366  {
1367  // A standard frame may include many summarized frames (due to
1368  // inlining).
1369  FrameSummaries summaries = CommonFrame::cast(frame)->Summarize();
1370  if (summaries.top_frame_is_construct_call && !skipped_last_frame) {
1371  visitor->SetPrevFrameAsConstructCall();
1372  }
1373  skipped_last_frame = true;
1374  for (auto summary = summaries.frames.rbegin();
1375  summary != summaries.frames.rend(); ++summary) {
1376  // Skip frames from other origins when asked to do so.
1377  if (!(options & StackTrace::kExposeFramesAcrossSecurityOrigins) &&
1378  !summary->native_context()->HasSameSecurityTokenAs(
1379  isolate->context())) {
1380  continue;
1381  }
1382  if (!visitor->Visit(*summary)) return;
1383  skipped_last_frame = false;
1384  }
1385  break;
1386  }
1387 
1388  default:
1389  break;
1390  }
1391  }
1392 }
1393 
1394 Handle<FixedArray> CaptureSimpleStackTrace(Isolate* isolate, int limit,
1395  FrameSkipMode mode,
1396  Handle<Object> caller) {
1397  TRACE_EVENT_BEGIN1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__,
1398  "maxFrameCount", limit);
1399 
1400 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1401  wasm::WasmCodeRefScope code_ref_scope;
1402 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1403 
1404  CallSiteBuilder builder(isolate, mode, limit, caller);
1405  VisitStack(isolate, &builder);
1406 
1407  // If --async-stack-traces are enabled and the "current microtask" is a
1408  // PromiseReactionJobTask, we try to enrich the stack trace with async
1409  // frames.
1410  if (v8_flags.async_stack_traces) {
1411  CaptureAsyncStackTrace(isolate, &builder);
1412  }
1413 
1414  Handle<FixedArray> stack_trace = builder.Build();
1415  TRACE_EVENT_END1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__,
1416  "frameCount", stack_trace->length());
1417  return stack_trace;
1418 }
1419 
1420 DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> GetDetailedStackTraceFromCallSiteInfos(
1421  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<FixedArray> call_site_infos, int limit) {
1422  auto frames = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1423  std::min(limit, call_site_infos->length()));
1424  int index = 0;
1425  for (int i = 0; i < call_site_infos->length() && index < limit; ++i) {
1426  DirectHandle<CallSiteInfo> call_site_info(
1427  Cast<CallSiteInfo>(call_site_infos->get(i)), isolate);
1428  if (call_site_info->IsAsync()) {
1429  break;
1430  }
1431  DirectHandle<Script> script;
1432  if (!CallSiteInfo::GetScript(isolate, call_site_info).ToHandle(&script) ||
1433  !script->IsSubjectToDebugging()) {
1434  continue;
1435  }
1436  DirectHandle<StackFrameInfo> stack_frame_info =
1437  isolate->factory()->NewStackFrameInfo(
1438  script, CallSiteInfo::GetSourcePosition(call_site_info),
1439  CallSiteInfo::GetFunctionDebugName(call_site_info),
1440  IsConstructor(*call_site_info));
1441  frames->set(index++, *stack_frame_info);
1442  }
1443  frames = FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate, frames, index);
1444  return isolate->factory()->NewStackTraceInfo(frames);
1445 }
1446 
1447 } // namespace
1448 
1449 MaybeDirectHandle<JSObject> Isolate::CaptureAndSetErrorStack(
1450  DirectHandle<JSObject> error_object, FrameSkipMode mode,
1451  Handle<Object> caller) {
1452  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__);
1453  Handle<UnionOf<Undefined, FixedArray>> call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack =
1454  factory()->undefined_value();
1455 
1456  // Capture the "simple stack trace" for the error.stack property,
1457  // which can be disabled by setting Error.stackTraceLimit to a non
1458  // number value or simply deleting the property. If the inspector
1459  // is active, and requests more stack frames than the JavaScript
1460  // program itself, we collect up to the maximum.
1461  int stack_trace_limit = 0;
1462  if (GetStackTraceLimit(this, &stack_trace_limit)) {
1463  int limit = stack_trace_limit;
1464  if (capture_stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_ &&
1465  !(stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_options_ &
1466  StackTrace::kExposeFramesAcrossSecurityOrigins)) {
1467  // Collect up to the maximum of what the JavaScript program and
1468  // the inspector want. There's a special case here where the API
1469  // can ask the stack traces to also include cross-origin frames,
1470  // in which case we collect a separate trace below. Note that
1471  // the inspector doesn't use this option, so we could as well
1472  // just deprecate this in the future.
1473  if (limit < stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_frame_limit_) {
1474  limit = stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_frame_limit_;
1475  }
1476  }
1477  call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack =
1478  CaptureSimpleStackTrace(this, limit, mode, caller);
1479  }
1480  DirectHandle<Object> error_stack = call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack;
1481 
1482  // Next is the inspector part: Depending on whether we got a "simple
1483  // stack trace" above and whether that's usable (meaning the API
1484  // didn't request to include cross-origin frames), we remember the
1485  // cap for the stack trace (either a positive limit indicating that
1486  // the Error.stackTraceLimit value was below what was requested via
1487  // the API, or a negative limit to indicate the opposite), or we
1488  // collect a "detailed stack trace" eagerly and stash that away.
1489  if (capture_stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_) {
1490  DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> stack_trace;
1491  if (IsUndefined(*call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack, this) ||
1492  (stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_options_ &
1493  StackTrace::kExposeFramesAcrossSecurityOrigins)) {
1494  stack_trace = CaptureDetailedStackTrace(
1495  stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_frame_limit_,
1496  stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_options_);
1497  } else {
1498  auto call_site_infos =
1499  Cast<FixedArray>(call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack);
1500  stack_trace = GetDetailedStackTraceFromCallSiteInfos(
1501  this, call_site_infos,
1502  stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_frame_limit_);
1503  if (stack_trace_limit < call_site_infos->length()) {
1504  call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack = FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(
1505  this, call_site_infos, stack_trace_limit);
1506  }
1507  // Notify the debugger.
1508  OnStackTraceCaptured(stack_trace);
1509  }
1510  error_stack = factory()->NewErrorStackData(
1511  call_site_infos_or_formatted_stack, stack_trace);
1512  }
1513 
1514  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1515  this,
1516  Object::SetProperty(this, error_object, factory()->error_stack_symbol(),
1517  error_stack, StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
1518  Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError)));
1519  return error_object;
1520 }
1521 
1522 Handle<StackTraceInfo> Isolate::GetDetailedStackTrace(
1523  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> maybe_error_object) {
1524  ErrorUtils::StackPropertyLookupResult lookup =
1525  ErrorUtils::GetErrorStackProperty(this, maybe_error_object);
1526  if (!IsErrorStackData(*lookup.error_stack)) return {};
1527  return handle(Cast<ErrorStackData>(lookup.error_stack)->stack_trace(), this);
1528 }
1529 
1530 Handle<FixedArray> Isolate::GetSimpleStackTrace(
1531  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> maybe_error_object) {
1532  ErrorUtils::StackPropertyLookupResult lookup =
1533  ErrorUtils::GetErrorStackProperty(this, maybe_error_object);
1534 
1535  if (IsFixedArray(*lookup.error_stack)) {
1536  return Cast<FixedArray>(lookup.error_stack);
1537  }
1538  if (!IsErrorStackData(*lookup.error_stack)) {
1539  return factory()->empty_fixed_array();
1540  }
1541  auto error_stack_data = Cast<ErrorStackData>(lookup.error_stack);
1542  if (!error_stack_data->HasCallSiteInfos()) {
1543  return factory()->empty_fixed_array();
1544  }
1545  return handle(error_stack_data->call_site_infos(), this);
1546 }
1547 
1548 Address Isolate::GetAbstractPC(int* line, int* column) {
1549  JavaScriptStackFrameIterator it(this);
1550 
1551  if (it.done()) {
1552  *line = -1;
1553  *column = -1;
1554  return kNullAddress;
1555  }
1556  JavaScriptFrame* frame = it.frame();
1557  DCHECK(!frame->is_builtin());
1558 
1559  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(frame->function()->shared(), this);
1560  SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(this, shared);
1561  int position = frame->position();
1562 
1563  Tagged<Object> maybe_script = frame->function()->shared()->script();
1564  if (IsScript(maybe_script)) {
1565  DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(maybe_script), this);
1566  Script::PositionInfo info;
1567  Script::GetPositionInfo(script, position, &info);
1568  *line = info.line + 1;
1569  *column = info.column + 1;
1570  } else {
1571  *line = position;
1572  *column = -1;
1573  }
1574 
1575  if (frame->is_unoptimized()) {
1576  UnoptimizedJSFrame* iframe = static_cast<UnoptimizedJSFrame*>(frame);
1577  Address bytecode_start =
1578  iframe->GetBytecodeArray()->GetFirstBytecodeAddress();
1579  return bytecode_start + iframe->GetBytecodeOffset();
1580  }
1581 
1582  return frame->pc();
1583 }

1585 namespace {
1586 
1587 class StackFrameBuilder {
1588  public:
1589  StackFrameBuilder(Isolate* isolate, int limit)
1590  : isolate_(isolate),
1591  frames_(isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array()),
1592  index_(0),
1593  limit_(limit) {}
1594 
1595  void SetPrevFrameAsConstructCall() {
1596  // Nothing to do.
1597  }
1598 
1599  bool Visit(FrameSummary& summary) {
1600  // Check if we have enough capacity left.
1601  if (index_ >= limit_) return false;
1602  // Skip frames that aren't subject to debugging.
1603  if (!summary.is_subject_to_debugging()) return true;
1604  DirectHandle<StackFrameInfo> frame = summary.CreateStackFrameInfo();
1605  frames_ = FixedArray::SetAndGrow(isolate_, frames_, index_++, frame);
1606  return true;
1607  }
1608 
1609  Handle<FixedArray> Build() {
1610  return FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate_, frames_, index_);
1611  }
1612 
1613  private:
1614  Isolate* isolate_;
1615  Handle<FixedArray> frames_;
1616  int index_;
1617  int limit_;
1618 };
1619 
1620 } // namespace
1621 
1622 DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> Isolate::CaptureDetailedStackTrace(
1623  int limit, StackTrace::StackTraceOptions options) {
1624  TRACE_EVENT_BEGIN1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__,
1625  "maxFrameCount", limit);
1626  StackFrameBuilder builder(this, limit);
1627  VisitStack(this, &builder, options);
1628  auto frames = builder.Build();
1629  TRACE_EVENT_END1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__,
1630  "frameCount", frames->length());
1631  auto stack_trace = factory()->NewStackTraceInfo(frames);
1632  OnStackTraceCaptured(stack_trace);
1633  return stack_trace;
1634 }

1636 namespace {
1637 
1638 class CurrentScriptNameStackVisitor {
1639  public:
1640  explicit CurrentScriptNameStackVisitor(Isolate* isolate)
1641  : isolate_(isolate) {}
1642 
1643  void SetPrevFrameAsConstructCall() {
1644  // Nothing to do.
1645  }
1646 
1647  bool Visit(FrameSummary& summary) {
1648  // Skip frames that aren't subject to debugging. Keep this in sync with
1649  // StackFrameBuilder::Visit so both visitors visit the same frames.
1650  if (!summary.is_subject_to_debugging()) return true;
1651 
1652  // Frames that are subject to debugging always have a valid script object.
1653  auto script = Cast<Script>(summary.script());
1654  Handle<Object> name_or_url_obj(script->GetNameOrSourceURL(), isolate_);
1655  if (!IsString(*name_or_url_obj)) return true;
1656 
1657  auto name_or_url = Cast<String>(name_or_url_obj);
1658  if (!name_or_url->length()) return true;
1659 
1660  name_or_url_ = name_or_url;
1661  return false;
1662  }
1663 
1664  DirectHandle<String> CurrentScriptNameOrSourceURL() const {
1665  return name_or_url_;
1666  }
1667 
1668  private:
1669  Isolate* const isolate_;
1670  Handle<String> name_or_url_;
1671 };
1672 
1673 class CurrentScriptStackVisitor {
1674  public:
1675  void SetPrevFrameAsConstructCall() {
1676  // Nothing to do.
1677  }
1678 
1679  bool Visit(FrameSummary& summary) {
1680  // Skip frames that aren't subject to debugging. Keep this in sync with
1681  // StackFrameBuilder::Visit so both visitors visit the same frames.
1682  if (!summary.is_subject_to_debugging()) return true;
1683 
1684  // Frames that are subject to debugging always have a valid script object.
1685  current_script_ = Cast<Script>(summary.script());
1686  return false;
1687  }
1688 
1689  MaybeDirectHandle<Script> CurrentScript() const { return current_script_; }
1690 
1691  private:
1692  MaybeHandle<Script> current_script_;
1693 };

1695 } // namespace

1704 MaybeDirectHandle<Script> Isolate::CurrentReferrerScript() {
1705  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.stack_trace"), __func__);
1706  CurrentScriptStackVisitor visitor{};
1707  VisitStack(this, &visitor);
1708  DirectHandle<Script> script;

1710  return MaybeDirectHandle<Script>();

1715 bool Isolate::GetStackTraceLimit(Isolate* isolate, int* result) {
1716  if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) return false;
1717  DirectHandle<JSObject> error = isolate->error_function();
1718 
1719  DirectHandle<String> key = isolate->factory()->stackTraceLimit_string();
1720  DirectHandle<Object> stack_trace_limit =
1721  JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(isolate, error, key);
1722  if (!IsNumber(*stack_trace_limit)) return false;
1723 
1724  // Ensure that limit is not negative.
1725  *result = std::max(
1726  FastD2IChecked(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*stack_trace_limit))), 0);
1727 
1728  if (*result != v8_flags.stack_trace_limit) {
1729  isolate->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kErrorStackTraceLimit);
1730  }
1731 
1732  return true;
1733 }
1734 
1735 void Isolate::PrintStack(FILE* out, PrintStackMode mode) {
1736  if (stack_trace_nesting_level_ == 0) {
1737  stack_trace_nesting_level_++;
1738  StringStream::ClearMentionedObjectCache(this);
1739  HeapStringAllocator allocator;
1740  StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
1741  incomplete_message_ = &accumulator;
1742  PrintStack(&accumulator, mode);
1743  accumulator.OutputToFile(out);
1744  InitializeLoggingAndCounters();
1745  accumulator.Log(this);
1746  incomplete_message_ = nullptr;
1747  stack_trace_nesting_level_ = 0;
1748  } else if (stack_trace_nesting_level_ == 1) {
1749  stack_trace_nesting_level_++;
1750  base::OS::PrintError(
1751  "\n\nAttempt to print stack while printing stack (double fault)\n");
1752  base::OS::PrintError(
1753  "If you are lucky you may find a partial stack dump on stdout.\n\n");
1754  incomplete_message_->OutputToFile(out);
1755  }
1756 }
1757 
1758 static void PrintFrames(Isolate* isolate, StringStream* accumulator,
1759  StackFrame::PrintMode mode) {
1760  StackFrameIterator it(isolate);
1761  for (int i = 0; !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
1762  it.frame()->Print(accumulator, mode, i++);
1763  }
1764 }
1765 
1766 void Isolate::PrintStack(StringStream* accumulator, PrintStackMode mode) {
1767  HandleScope scope(this);
1768  DCHECK(accumulator->IsMentionedObjectCacheClear(this));
1769 
1770  // Avoid printing anything if there are no frames.
1771  if (c_entry_fp(thread_local_top()) == 0) return;
1772 
1773  accumulator->Add(
1774  "\n==== JS stack trace =========================================\n\n");
1775  PrintFrames(this, accumulator, StackFrame::OVERVIEW);
1776  if (mode == kPrintStackVerbose) {
1777  accumulator->Add(
1778  "\n==== Details ================================================\n\n");
1779  PrintFrames(this, accumulator, StackFrame::DETAILS);
1780  accumulator->PrintMentionedObjectCache(this);
1781  }
1782  accumulator->Add("=====================\n\n");
1783 }

1785 void Isolate::SetFailedAccessCheckCallback(
1786  v8::FailedAccessCheckCallback callback) {
1787  thread_local_top()->failed_access_check_callback_ = callback;
1788 }
1789 
1790 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> Isolate::ReportFailedAccessCheck(
1791  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver) {
1792  if (!thread_local_top()->failed_access_check_callback_) {
1793  THROW_NEW_ERROR(this, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNoAccess));
1794  }
1795 
1796  DCHECK(IsAccessCheckNeeded(*receiver));
1797  DCHECK(!context().is_null());
1798 
1799  // Get the data object from access check info.
1800  HandleScope scope(this);
1801  DirectHandle<Object> data;
1802  {
1803  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1804  Tagged<AccessCheckInfo> access_check_info =
1805  AccessCheckInfo::Get(this, receiver);
1806  if (access_check_info.is_null()) {
1807  no_gc.Release();
1808  THROW_NEW_ERROR(this, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNoAccess));
1809  }
1810  data = direct_handle(access_check_info->data(), this);
1811  }
1812 
1813  {
1814  // Leaving JavaScript.
1815  VMState<EXTERNAL> state(this);
1816  thread_local_top()->failed_access_check_callback_(
1817  v8::Utils::ToLocal(receiver), v8::ACCESS_HAS, v8::Utils::ToLocal(data));
1818  }
1819  RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION(this, {});
1820  // Throw exception even the callback forgot to do so.
1821  THROW_NEW_ERROR(this, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNoAccess));
1822 }
1823 
1824 bool Isolate::MayAccess(DirectHandle<NativeContext> accessing_context,
1825  DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver) {
1826  DCHECK(IsJSGlobalProxy(*receiver) || IsAccessCheckNeeded(*receiver));
1827 
1828  // Check for compatibility between the security tokens in the
1829  // current lexical context and the accessed object.
1830 
1831  // During bootstrapping, callback functions are not enabled yet.
1832  if (bootstrapper()->IsActive()) return true;
1833  {
1834  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1835 
1836  if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*receiver)) {
1837  std::optional<Tagged<Object>> receiver_context =
1838  Cast<JSGlobalProxy>(*receiver)->GetCreationContext();
1839  if (!receiver_context) return false;
1840 
1841  if (*receiver_context == *accessing_context) return true;
1842 
1843  if (Cast<Context>(*receiver_context)->security_token() ==
1844  accessing_context->security_token())
1845  return true;
1846  }
1847  }
1848 
1849  HandleScope scope(this);
1850  DirectHandle<Object> data;
1851  v8::AccessCheckCallback callback = nullptr;
1852  {
1853  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1854  Tagged<AccessCheckInfo> access_check_info =
1855  AccessCheckInfo::Get(this, receiver);
1856  if (access_check_info.is_null()) return false;
1857  Tagged<Object> fun_obj = access_check_info->callback();
1858  callback = v8::ToCData<v8::AccessCheckCallback, kApiAccessCheckCallbackTag>(
1859  this, fun_obj);
1860  data = direct_handle(access_check_info->data(), this);
1861  }
1862 
1863  {
1864  // Leaving JavaScript.
1865  VMState<EXTERNAL> state(this);
1866  return callback(v8::Utils::ToLocal(accessing_context),
1867  v8::Utils::ToLocal(receiver), v8::Utils::ToLocal(data));
1868  }
1869 }
1870 
1871 Tagged<Object> Isolate::StackOverflow() {
1872  // Whoever calls this method should not have overflown the stack limit by too
1873  // much. Otherwise we risk actually running out of stack space.
1874  // We allow for up to 8kB overflow, because we typically allow up to 4KB
1875  // overflow per frame in generated code, but might call through more smaller
1876  // frames until we reach this method.
1877  // If this DCHECK fails, one of the frames on the stack should be augmented by
1878  // an additional stack check.
1879 #if defined(V8_USE_ADDRESS_SANITIZER) || defined(MEMORY_SANITIZER)
1880  // Allow for a bit more overflow in sanitizer builds, because C++ frames take
1881  // significantly more space there.
1882  DCHECK_GE(GetCurrentStackPosition(), stack_guard()->real_climit() - 64 * KB);
1883 #elif (defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32)) && \
1884  defined(USE_SIMULATOR)
1885  // Allow for more overflow on riscv simulator, because C++ frames take more
1886  // there.
1887  DCHECK_GE(GetCurrentStackPosition(), stack_guard()->real_climit() - 12 * KB);
1888 #elif defined(ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS) && V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_TRIVIAL_ABI
1889  // In this configuration, direct handles are not trivially copyable. This
1890  // prevents some C++ compiler optimizations and uses more stack space.
1891  DCHECK_GE(GetCurrentStackPosition(), stack_guard()->real_climit() - 10 * KB);
1892 #else
1893  DCHECK_GE(GetCurrentStackPosition(), stack_guard()->real_climit() - 8 * KB);
1894 #endif
1895 
1896  if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
1897  FATAL("Aborting on stack overflow");
1898  }
1899 
1900 #if USE_SIMULATOR
1901  // Adjust the stack limit back to the real limit in case it was temporarily
1902  // modified to reflect an overflow in the C stack (see
1903  // AdjustStackLimitForSimulator).
1904  stack_guard()->ResetStackLimitForSimulator();
1905 #endif
1906  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(this);
1907  HandleScope scope(this);
1908 
1909  DirectHandle<JSFunction> fun = range_error_function();
1910  DirectHandle<Object> msg = factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
1911  MessageFormatter::TemplateString(MessageTemplate::kStackOverflow));
1912  DirectHandle<Object> options = factory()->undefined_value();
1913  DirectHandle<Object> no_caller;
1914  DirectHandle<JSObject> exception;
1915  ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(
1916  this, exception,
1917  ErrorUtils::Construct(this, fun, fun, msg, options, SKIP_NONE, no_caller,
1918  ErrorUtils::StackTraceCollection::kEnabled));
1919  JSObject::AddProperty(this, exception, factory()->wasm_uncatchable_symbol(),
1920  factory()->true_value(), NONE);
1921 
1922  Throw(*exception);
1923 
1924 #ifdef VERIFY_HEAP
1925  if (v8_flags.verify_heap && v8_flags.stress_compaction) {
1926  heap()->CollectAllGarbage(GCFlag::kNoFlags,
1927  GarbageCollectionReason::kTesting);
1928  }
1929 #endif // VERIFY_HEAP
1930 
1931  return ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).exception();
1932 }
1933 
1934 Tagged<Object> Isolate::ThrowAt(DirectHandle<JSObject> exception,
1935  MessageLocation* location) {
1936  DirectHandle<Name> key_start_pos = factory()->error_start_pos_symbol();
1937  Object::SetProperty(this, exception, key_start_pos,
1938  direct_handle(Smi::FromInt(location->start_pos()), this),
1939  StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
1940  Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError))
1941  .Check();
1942 
1943  DirectHandle<Name> key_end_pos = factory()->error_end_pos_symbol();
1944  Object::SetProperty(this, exception, key_end_pos,
1945  direct_handle(Smi::FromInt(location->end_pos()), this),
1946  StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
1947  Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError))
1948  .Check();
1949 
1950  DirectHandle<Name> key_script = factory()->error_script_symbol();
1951  Object::SetProperty(this, exception, key_script, location->script(),
1952  StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
1953  Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError))
1954  .Check();
1955 
1956  return Throw(*exception, location);
1957 }

1969 void Isolate::RequestInterrupt(InterruptCallback callback, void* data) {
1970  ExecutionAccess access(this);
1971  api_interrupts_queue_.push(InterruptEntry(callback, data));
1972  stack_guard()->RequestApiInterrupt();
1973 }
1974 
1975 void Isolate::InvokeApiInterruptCallbacks() {
1976  RCS_SCOPE(this, RuntimeCallCounterId::kInvokeApiInterruptCallbacks);
1977  // Note: callback below should be called outside of execution access lock.
1978  while (true) {
1979  InterruptEntry entry;
1980  {
1981  ExecutionAccess access(this);
1982  if (api_interrupts_queue_.empty()) return;
1983  entry = api_interrupts_queue_.front();
1984  api_interrupts_queue_.pop();
1985  }
1986  VMState<EXTERNAL> state(this);
1987  HandleScope handle_scope(this);
1988  entry.first(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this), entry.second);
1989  }
1990 }

1992 void Isolate::RequestInvalidateNoProfilingProtector() {
1993  // This request might be triggered from arbitrary thread but protector
1994  // invalidation must happen on the main thread, so use Api interrupt
1995  // to achieve that.
1996  RequestInterrupt(
1997  [](v8::Isolate* isolate, void*) {
1998  Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(isolate);
1999  if (Protectors::IsNoProfilingIntact(i_isolate)) {
2000  Protectors::InvalidateNoProfiling(i_isolate);
2001  }
2002  },
2003  nullptr);
2004 }

2006 namespace {
2007 
2008 void ReportBootstrappingException(DirectHandle<Object> exception,
2009  MessageLocation* location) {
2010  base::OS::PrintError("Exception thrown during bootstrapping\n");
2011  if (location == nullptr || location->script().is_null()) return;
2012  // We are bootstrapping and caught an error where the location is set
2013  // and we have a script for the location.
2014  // In this case we could have an extension (or an internal error
2015  // somewhere) and we print out the line number at which the error occurred
2016  // to the console for easier debugging.
2017  int line_number =
2018  location->script()->GetLineNumber(location->start_pos()) + 1;
2019  if (IsString(*exception) && IsString(location->script()->name())) {
2020  base::OS::PrintError(
2021  "Extension or internal compilation error: %s in %s at line %d.\n",
2022  Cast<String>(*exception)->ToCString().get(),
2023  Cast<String>(location->script()->name())->ToCString().get(),
2024  line_number);
2025  } else if (IsString(location->script()->name())) {
2026  base::OS::PrintError(
2027  "Extension or internal compilation error in %s at line %d.\n",
2028  Cast<String>(location->script()->name())->ToCString().get(),
2029  line_number);
2030  } else if (IsString(*exception)) {
2031  base::OS::PrintError("Extension or internal compilation error: %s.\n",
2032  Cast<String>(*exception)->ToCString().get());
2033  } else {
2034  base::OS::PrintError("Extension or internal compilation error.\n");
2035  }
2036 #ifdef OBJECT_PRINT
2037  // Since comments and empty lines have been stripped from the source of
2038  // builtins, print the actual source here so that line numbers match.
2039  if (IsString(location->script()->source())) {
2040  DirectHandle<String> src(Cast<String>(location->script()->source()),
2041  Isolate::Current());
2042  PrintF("Failing script:");
2043  int len = src->length();
2044  if (len == 0) {
2045  PrintF(" <not available>\n");
2046  } else {
2047  PrintF("\n");
2048  line_number = 1;
2049  PrintF("%5d: ", line_number);
2050  for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
2051  uint16_t character = src->Get(i);
2052  PrintF("%c", character);
2053  if (character == '\n' && i < len - 2) {
2054  PrintF("%5d: ", ++line_number);
2055  }
2056  }
2057  PrintF("\n");
2058  }
2059  }
2060 #endif
2061 }
2062 
2063 } // anonymous namespace
2064 
2065 DirectHandle<JSMessageObject> Isolate::CreateMessageOrAbort(
2066  DirectHandle<Object> exception, MessageLocation* location) {
2067  DirectHandle<JSMessageObject> message_obj =
2068  CreateMessage(exception, location);
2069 
2070  // If the abort-on-uncaught-exception flag is specified, and if the
2071  // embedder didn't specify a custom uncaught exception callback,
2072  // or if the custom callback determined that V8 should abort, then
2073  // abort.
2074  // Cache the flag on a static so that we can modify the value looked up below
2075  // in the presence of read-only flags.
2076  static bool abort_on_uncaught_exception =
2077  v8_flags.abort_on_uncaught_exception;
2078  if (abort_on_uncaught_exception) {
2079  CatchType prediction = PredictExceptionCatcher();
2080  if ((prediction == NOT_CAUGHT || prediction == CAUGHT_BY_EXTERNAL) &&
2081  (!abort_on_uncaught_exception_callback_ ||
2082  abort_on_uncaught_exception_callback_(
2083  reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this)))) {
2084  // Prevent endless recursion.
2085  abort_on_uncaught_exception = false;
2086  // This flag is intended for use by JavaScript developers, so
2087  // print a user-friendly stack trace (not an internal one).
2088  PrintF(stderr, "%s\n\nFROM\n",
2089  MessageHandler::GetLocalizedMessage(this, message_obj).get());
2090  std::ostringstream stack_trace_stream;
2091  PrintCurrentStackTrace(stack_trace_stream);
2092  PrintF(stderr, "%s", stack_trace_stream.str().c_str());
2093  base::OS::Abort();
2094  }
2095  }
2096 
2097  return message_obj;
2098 }
2099 
2100 Tagged<Object> Isolate::Throw(Tagged<Object> raw_exception,
2101  MessageLocation* location) {
2102  if (has_exception()) {
2103  // A termination exception may have been thrown while preparing
2104  // {raw_exception}, e.g. by the near heap limit callback
2105  // (crbug.com/409487530).
2106  // In this case ignore the current error and propagate the termination
2107  // exception instead. Any other kind of exception is unexpected.
2108  DCHECK(IsTerminationException(exception()));
2109  return ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).exception();
2110  }
2111  DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsHole(raw_exception),
2112  raw_exception == ReadOnlyRoots{this}.termination_exception());
2113  CHECK(IsOnCentralStack());
2114 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2115  trap_handler::AssertThreadNotInWasm();
2116 #endif
2117 
2118  HandleScope scope(this);
2119  DirectHandle<Object> exception(raw_exception, this);
2120 
2121  if (v8_flags.print_all_exceptions) {
2122  PrintF("=========================================================\n");
2123  PrintF("Exception thrown:\n");
2124  if (location) {
2125  DirectHandle<Script> script = location->script();
2126  DirectHandle<Object> name(script->GetNameOrSourceURL(), this);
2127  PrintF("at ");
2128  if (IsString(*name) && Cast<String>(*name)->length() > 0) {
2129  Cast<String>(*name)->PrintOn(stdout);
2130  } else {
2131  PrintF("<anonymous>");
2132  }
2133 // Script::GetLineNumber and Script::GetColumnNumber can allocate on the heap to
2134 // initialize the line_ends array, so be careful when calling them.
2135 #ifdef DEBUG
2136  if (AllowGarbageCollection::IsAllowed()) {
2137 #else
2138  if ((false)) {
2139 #endif
2140  Script::PositionInfo start_pos;
2141  Script::PositionInfo end_pos;
2142  Script::GetPositionInfo(script, location->start_pos(), &start_pos);
2143  Script::GetPositionInfo(script, location->end_pos(), &end_pos);
2144  PrintF(", %d:%d - %d:%d\n", start_pos.line + 1, start_pos.column + 1,
2145  end_pos.line + 1, end_pos.column + 1);
2146  } else {
2147  PrintF(", line %d\n", script->GetLineNumber(location->start_pos()) + 1);
2148  }
2149  }
2150  Print(*exception);
2151  PrintF("Stack Trace:\n");
2152  PrintStack(stdout);
2153  PrintF("=========================================================\n");
2154  }
2155 
2156  // Determine whether a message needs to be created for the given exception
2157  // depending on the following criteria:
2158  // 1) External v8::TryCatch missing: Always create a message because any
2159  // JavaScript handler for a finally-block might re-throw to top-level.
2160  // 2) External v8::TryCatch exists: Only create a message if the handler
2161  // captures messages or is verbose (which reports despite the catch).
2162  // 3) ReThrow from v8::TryCatch: The message from a previous throw still
2163  // exists and we preserve it instead of creating a new message.
2164  bool requires_message = try_catch_handler() == nullptr ||
2165  try_catch_handler()->is_verbose_ ||
2166  try_catch_handler()->capture_message_;
2167  bool rethrowing_message = thread_local_top()->rethrowing_message_;
2168 
2169  thread_local_top()->rethrowing_message_ = false;
2170 
2171  // Notify debugger of exception.
2172  if (is_catchable_by_javascript(*exception)) {
2173  DirectHandle<Object> message(pending_message(), this);
2174  std::optional<Tagged<Object>> maybe_exception = debug()->OnThrow(exception);
2175  if (maybe_exception.has_value()) {
2176  return *maybe_exception;
2177  }
2178  // Restore the message in case it was clobbered by debugger.
2179  set_pending_message(*message);
2180  }
2181 
2182  // Generate the message if required.
2183  if (requires_message && !rethrowing_message) {
2184  MessageLocation computed_location;
2185  // If no location was specified we try to use a computed one instead.
2186  if (location == nullptr && ComputeLocation(&computed_location)) {
2187  location = &computed_location;
2188  }
2189  if (bootstrapper()->IsActive()) {
2190  // It's not safe to try to make message objects or collect stack traces
2191  // while the bootstrapper is active since the infrastructure may not have
2192  // been properly initialized.
2193  ReportBootstrappingException(exception, location);
2194  } else {
2195  DirectHandle<Object> message_obj =
2196  CreateMessageOrAbort(exception, location);
2197  set_pending_message(*message_obj);
2198  }
2199  }
2200 
2201  // Set the exception being thrown.
2202  set_exception(*exception);
2203  PropagateExceptionToExternalTryCatch(TopExceptionHandlerType(*exception));
2204 
2205  if (v8_flags.experimental_report_exceptions_from_callbacks &&
2206  exception_propagation_callback_ && !rethrowing_message &&
2207  !preprocessing_exception_) {
2208  // Don't preprocess exceptions that might happen inside
2209  // |exception_propagation_callback_|.
2210  preprocessing_exception_ = true;
2211  NotifyExceptionPropagationCallback();
2212  preprocessing_exception_ = false;
2213  }
2214  return ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).exception();
2215 }
2216 
2217 Tagged<Object> Isolate::ReThrow(Tagged<Object> exception) {
2218  DCHECK(!has_exception());
2219 
2220  // Set the exception being re-thrown.
2221  set_exception(exception);
2222  return ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).exception();
2223 }
2224 
2225 Tagged<Object> Isolate::ReThrow(Tagged<Object> exception,
2226  Tagged<Object> message) {
2227  DCHECK(!has_exception());
2228  DCHECK(!has_pending_message());
2229 
2230  set_pending_message(message);
2231  return ReThrow(exception);
2232 }
