2234 namespace {
2235 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2236 // This scope will set the thread-in-wasm flag after the execution of all
2237 // destructors. The thread-in-wasm flag is only set when the scope gets enabled.
2238 class SetThreadInWasmFlagScope {
2239  public:
2240  SetThreadInWasmFlagScope() { trap_handler::AssertThreadNotInWasm(); }
2241 
2242  ~SetThreadInWasmFlagScope() {
2243  if (enabled_) trap_handler::SetThreadInWasm();
2244  }
2245 
2246  void Enable() { enabled_ = true; }
2247 
2248  private:
2249  bool enabled_ = false;
2250 };
2251 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2252 } // namespace
2253 
2254 Tagged<Object> Isolate::UnwindAndFindHandler() {
2255  // TODO(v8:12676): Fix gcmole failures in this function.
2256  DisableGCMole no_gcmole;
2257  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2258 
2259  // The topmost_script_having_context value becomes outdated after frames
2260  // unwinding.
2261  clear_topmost_script_having_context();
2262 
2263 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2264  // Create the {SetThreadInWasmFlagScope} first in this function so that its
2265  // destructor gets called after all the other destructors. It is important
2266  // that the destructor sets the thread-in-wasm flag after all other
2267  // destructors. The other destructors may cause exceptions, e.g. ASan on
2268  // Windows, which would invalidate the thread-in-wasm flag when the wasm trap
2269  // handler handles such non-wasm exceptions.
2270  SetThreadInWasmFlagScope set_thread_in_wasm_flag_scope;
2271 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2272  Tagged<Object> exception = this->exception();
2273 
2274  auto FoundHandler = [&](StackFrameIterator& iter, Tagged<Context> context,
2275  Address instruction_start, intptr_t handler_offset,
2276  Address constant_pool_address, Address handler_sp,
2277  Address handler_fp, int num_frames_above_handler) {
2278  // Store information to be consumed by the CEntry.
2279  thread_local_top()->pending_handler_context_ = context;
2280  thread_local_top()->pending_handler_entrypoint_ =
2281  instruction_start + handler_offset;
2282  thread_local_top()->pending_handler_constant_pool_ = constant_pool_address;
2283  thread_local_top()->pending_handler_fp_ = handler_fp;
2284  thread_local_top()->pending_handler_sp_ = handler_sp;
2285  thread_local_top()->num_frames_above_pending_handler_ =
2286  num_frames_above_handler;
2287 
2288 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2289  // If the exception was caught in a different stack, process all
2290  // intermediate stack switches.
2291  // This cannot be done during unwinding because the stack switching state
2292  // must stay consistent with the thread local top (see crbug.com/406053619).
2293  wasm::StackMemory* active_stack = isolate_data_.active_stack();
2294  if (active_stack != nullptr) {
2295  wasm::StackMemory* parent = nullptr;
2296  Tagged<HeapObject> suspender = *roots_table().active_suspender();
2297  while (active_stack != iter.wasm_stack()) {
2298  parent = active_stack->jmpbuf()->parent;
2299  SBXCHECK_EQ(parent->jmpbuf()->state, wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive);
2300  SwitchStacks(active_stack, parent);
2301  // Unconditionally update the active suspender as well. This assumes
2302  // that suspenders contain exactly one stack each.
2303  // Note: this is only needed for --stress-wasm-stack-switching.
2304  // Otherwise the exception should have been caught by the JSPI builtin.
2305  // TODO(388533754): Revisit this for core stack-switching when the
2306  // suspender can encapsulate multiple stacks.
2307  suspender = Tagged<WasmSuspenderObject>::cast(suspender)->parent();
2308  parent->jmpbuf()->state = wasm::JumpBuffer::Active;
2309  RetireWasmStack(active_stack);
2310  active_stack = parent;
2311  }
2312  if (parent) {
2313  // We switched at least once, update the active continuation.
2314  isolate_data_.set_active_stack(active_stack);
2315  roots_table().slot(RootIndex::kActiveSuspender).store(suspender);
2316  }
2317  }
2318  // The unwinder is running on the central stack. If the target frame is in a
2319  // secondary stack, update the central stack flags and the stack limit.
2320  Address stack_address =
2321  handler_sp != kNullAddress ? handler_sp : handler_fp;
2322  if (!IsOnCentralStack(stack_address)) {
2323  thread_local_top()->is_on_central_stack_flag_ = false;
2324  iter.wasm_stack()->ShrinkTo(stack_address);
2325  uintptr_t limit =
2326  reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(iter.wasm_stack()->jslimit());
2327  stack_guard()->SetStackLimitForStackSwitching(limit);
2328  iter.wasm_stack()->clear_stack_switch_info();
2329  }
2330  // Regardless of the stack that the handler belongs to, these fields should
2331  // be cleared.
2332  thread_local_top()->secondary_stack_limit_ = 0;
2333  thread_local_top()->secondary_stack_sp_ = 0;
2334 #endif
2335 
2336  // Return and clear exception. The contract is that:
2337  // (1) the exception is stored in one place (no duplication), and
2338  // (2) within generated-code land, that one place is the return register.
2339  // If/when we unwind back into C++ (returning to the JSEntry stub,
2340  // or to Execution::CallWasm), the returned exception will be sent
2341  // back to isolate->set_exception(...).
2342  clear_internal_exception();
2343  return exception;
2344  };
2345 
2346  // Special handling of termination exceptions, uncatchable by JavaScript and
2347  // Wasm code, we unwind the handlers until the top ENTRY handler is found.
2348  bool catchable_by_js = is_catchable_by_javascript(exception);
2349  if (!catchable_by_js && !context().is_null()) {
2350  // Because the array join stack will not pop the elements when throwing the
2351  // uncatchable terminate exception, we need to clear the array join stack to
2352  // avoid leaving the stack in an invalid state.
2353  // See also CycleProtectedArrayJoin.
2354  raw_native_context()->set_array_join_stack(
2355  ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
2356  }
2357 
2358  // Compute handler and stack unwinding information by performing a full walk
2359  // over the stack and dispatching according to the frame type.
2360  int visited_frames = 0;
2361  for (StackFrameIterator iter(this, thread_local_top());;
2362  iter.Advance(), visited_frames++) {
2363 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2364  if (iter.frame()->type() == StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH) {
2365  if (catchable_by_js && iter.frame()->LookupCode()->builtin_id() !=
2366  Builtin::kJSToWasmStressSwitchStacksAsm) {
2367  Tagged<Code> code =
2368  builtins()->code(Builtin::kWasmReturnPromiseOnSuspendAsm);
2369  HandlerTable table(code);
2370  Address instruction_start =
2371  code->InstructionStart(this, iter.frame()->pc());
2372  int handler_offset = table.LookupReturn(0);
2373  return FoundHandler(iter, Context(), instruction_start, handler_offset,
2374  kNullAddress, iter.frame()->sp(),
2375  iter.frame()->fp(), visited_frames);
2376  } else {
2377  // Just walk across the stack switch here. We only process it once we
2378  // have reached the handler.
2379  continue;
2380  }
2381  }
2382 #endif
2383  // Handler must exist.
2384  DCHECK(!iter.done());
2385 
2386  StackFrame* frame = iter.frame();
2387 
2388  // The debugger implements the "restart frame" feature by throwing a
2389  // terminate exception. Check and if we need to restart `frame`,
2390  // jump into the `RestartFrameTrampoline` builtin instead of
2391  // a catch handler.
2392  // Optimized frames take a detour via the deoptimizer before also jumping
2393  // to the `RestartFrameTrampoline` builtin.
2394  if (debug()->ShouldRestartFrame(frame->id())) {
2395  CancelTerminateExecution();
2396  CHECK(!catchable_by_js);
2397  CHECK(frame->is_javascript());
2398 
2399  if (frame->is_optimized_js()) {
2400  Tagged<Code> code = frame->LookupCode();
2401  // The debugger triggers lazy deopt for the "to-be-restarted" frame
2402  // immediately when the CDP event arrives while paused.
2403  CHECK(code->marked_for_deoptimization());
2404  set_deoptimizer_lazy_throw(true);
2405 
2406  // Jump directly to the optimized frames return, to immediately fall
2407  // into the deoptimizer.
2408  const int offset =
2409  static_cast<int>(frame->pc() - code->instruction_start());
2410 
2411  // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures that
2412  // argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2413  // Note: Needed by the deoptimizer to rematerialize frames.
2414  Address return_sp = frame->fp() +
2415  StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp -
2416  code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize;
2417  return FoundHandler(iter, Context(), code->instruction_start(), offset,
2418  code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(),
2419  visited_frames);
2420  }
2421 
2422  debug()->clear_restart_frame();
2423  Tagged<Code> code = *BUILTIN_CODE(this, RestartFrameTrampoline);
2424  return FoundHandler(iter, Context(), code->instruction_start(), 0,
2425  code->constant_pool(), kNullAddress, frame->fp(),
2426  visited_frames);
2427  }
2428 
2429  switch (frame->type()) {
2430  case StackFrame::ENTRY:
2431  case StackFrame::CONSTRUCT_ENTRY: {
2432  // For JSEntry frames we always have a handler.
2433  StackHandler* handler = frame->top_handler();
2434 
2435  // Restore the next handler.
2436  thread_local_top()->handler_ = handler->next_address();
2437 
2438  // Gather information from the handler.
2439  Tagged<Code> code = frame->LookupCode();
2440  HandlerTable table(code);
2441  return FoundHandler(iter, Context(),
2442  code->InstructionStart(this, frame->pc()),
2443  table.LookupReturn(0), code->constant_pool(),
2444  handler->address() + StackHandlerConstants::kSize,
2445  0, visited_frames);
2446  }
2447 
2448 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2449  case StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY: {
2450 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2451  if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
2452  StackHandler* handler = frame->top_handler();
2453  thread_local_top()->handler_ = handler->next_address();
2454  Tagged<Code> code =
2455  frame->LookupCode(); // WasmInterpreterCWasmEntry.
2456 
2457  HandlerTable table(code);
2458  Address instruction_start = code->InstructionStart(this, frame->pc());
2459  // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures that
2460  // argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2461  Address return_sp = *reinterpret_cast<Address*>(
2462  frame->fp() + WasmInterpreterCWasmEntryConstants::kSPFPOffset);
2463  const int handler_offset = table.LookupReturn(0);
2464  if (trap_handler::IsThreadInWasm()) {
2465  trap_handler::ClearThreadInWasm();
2466  }
2467  return FoundHandler(iter, Context(), instruction_start,
2468  handler_offset, code->constant_pool(), return_sp,
2469  frame->fp(), visited_frames);
2470  }
2471 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2472 
2473  StackHandler* handler = frame->top_handler();
2474  thread_local_top()->handler_ = handler->next_address();
2475  Tagged<Code> code = frame->LookupCode();
2476  HandlerTable table(code);
2477  Address instruction_start = code->instruction_start();
2478  int return_offset = static_cast<int>(frame->pc() - instruction_start);
2479  int handler_offset = table.LookupReturn(return_offset);
2480  DCHECK_NE(-1, handler_offset);
2481  // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures that
2482  // argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2483  Address return_sp = frame->fp() +
2484  StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp -
2485  code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize;
2486  return FoundHandler(iter, Context(), instruction_start, handler_offset,
2487  code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(),
2488  visited_frames);
2489  }
2490 
2491 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2492  case StackFrame::WASM_INTERPRETER_ENTRY: {
2493  if (trap_handler::IsThreadInWasm()) {
2494  trap_handler::ClearThreadInWasm();
2495  }
2496  } break;
2497 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2498 
2499  case StackFrame::WASM:
2500  case StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START: {
2501  if (!is_catchable_by_wasm(exception)) break;
2502 
2503  WasmFrame* wasm_frame = static_cast<WasmFrame*>(frame);
2504  wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code =
2505  wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(this, frame->pc());
2506  int offset = wasm_frame->LookupExceptionHandlerInTable();
2507  if (offset < 0) break;
2508  // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures that
2509  // argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2510  // The stack slot count needs to be adjusted for Liftoff frames. It has
2511  // two components: the fixed frame slots, and the maximum number of
2512  // registers pushed on top of the frame in out-of-line code. We know
2513  // that we are not currently in an OOL call, because OOL calls don't
2514  // have exception handlers. So we subtract the OOL spill count from the
2515  // total stack slot count to compute the actual frame size:
2516  int stack_slots = wasm_code->stack_slots() - wasm_code->ool_spills();
2517  Address return_sp = frame->fp() +
2518  StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp -
2519  stack_slots * kSystemPointerSize;
2520 
2521 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2522  // Transitioning from JS To Wasm.
2523  if (v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms &&
2524  v8_flags.slow_histograms && !v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
2525  // Start measuring the time spent running Wasm for jitted Wasm.
2526  wasm_execution_timer()->Start();
2527  }
2528 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
2529 
2530  // This is going to be handled by WebAssembly, so we need to set the TLS
2531  // flag. The {SetThreadInWasmFlagScope} will set the flag after all
2532  // destructors have been executed.
2533  set_thread_in_wasm_flag_scope.Enable();
2534  return FoundHandler(iter, Context(), wasm_code->instruction_start(),
2535  offset, wasm_code->constant_pool(), return_sp,
2536  frame->fp(), visited_frames);
2537  }
2538 
2539  case StackFrame::WASM_LIFTOFF_SETUP: {
2540  // The WasmLiftoffFrameSetup builtin doesn't throw, and doesn't call
2541  // out to user code that could throw.
2542  UNREACHABLE();
2543  }
2544 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2545 
2546  case StackFrame::MAGLEV:
2547  case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS: {
2548  // For optimized frames we perform a lookup in the handler table.
2549  if (!catchable_by_js) break;
2550  OptimizedJSFrame* opt_frame = static_cast<OptimizedJSFrame*>(frame);
2551  int offset = opt_frame->LookupExceptionHandlerInTable(nullptr, nullptr);
2552  if (offset < 0) break;
2553  // The code might be an optimized code or a turbofanned builtin.
2554  Tagged<Code> code = frame->LookupCode();
2555  // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures
2556  // that argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2557  Address return_sp = frame->fp() +
2558  StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp -
2559  code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize;
2560 
2561  // TODO(bmeurer): Turbofanned BUILTIN frames appear as TURBOFAN_JS,
2562  // but do not have a code kind of TURBOFAN_JS.
2563  if (CodeKindCanDeoptimize(code->kind()) &&
2564  code->marked_for_deoptimization()) {
2565  // If the target code is lazy deoptimized, we jump to the original
2566  // return address, but we make a note that we are throwing, so
2567  // that the deoptimizer can do the right thing.
2568  offset = static_cast<int>(frame->pc() - code->instruction_start());
2569  set_deoptimizer_lazy_throw(true);
2570  }
2571 
2572  return FoundHandler(
2573  iter, Context(), code->InstructionStart(this, frame->pc()), offset,
2574  code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(), visited_frames);
2575  }
2576 
2577  case StackFrame::STUB: {
2578  // Some stubs are able to handle exceptions.
2579  if (!catchable_by_js) break;
2580  StubFrame* stub_frame = static_cast<StubFrame*>(frame);
2581 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2582  DCHECK_NULL(wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(this, frame->pc()));
2583 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2584 
2585  // The code might be a dynamically generated stub or a turbofanned
2586  // embedded builtin.
2587  Tagged<Code> code = stub_frame->LookupCode();
2588  if (!code->is_turbofanned() || !code->has_handler_table()) {
2589  break;
2590  }
2591 
2592  int offset = stub_frame->LookupExceptionHandlerInTable();
2593  if (offset < 0) break;
2594 
2595  // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures
2596  // that argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2597  Address return_sp = frame->fp() +
2598  StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp -
2599  code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize;
2600 
2601  return FoundHandler(
2602  iter, Context(), code->InstructionStart(this, frame->pc()), offset,
2603  code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(), visited_frames);
2604  }
2605 
2606  case StackFrame::INTERPRETED:
2607  case StackFrame::BASELINE: {
2608  // For interpreted frame we perform a range lookup in the handler table.
2609  if (!catchable_by_js) break;
2610  UnoptimizedJSFrame* js_frame = UnoptimizedJSFrame::cast(frame);
2611  int register_slots = UnoptimizedFrameConstants::RegisterStackSlotCount(
2612  js_frame->GetBytecodeArray()->register_count());
2613  int context_reg = 0; // Will contain register index holding context.
2614  int offset =
2615  js_frame->LookupExceptionHandlerInTable(&context_reg, nullptr);
2616  if (offset < 0) break;
2617  // Compute the stack pointer from the frame pointer. This ensures that
2618  // argument slots on the stack are dropped as returning would.
2619  // Note: This is only needed for interpreted frames that have been
2620  // materialized by the deoptimizer. If there is a handler frame
2621  // in between then {frame->sp()} would already be correct.
2622  Address return_sp = frame->fp() -
2623  InterpreterFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp -
2624  register_slots * kSystemPointerSize;
2625 
2626  // Patch the bytecode offset in the interpreted frame to reflect the
2627  // position of the exception handler. The special builtin below will
2628  // take care of continuing to dispatch at that position. Also restore
2629  // the correct context for the handler from the interpreter register.
2630  Tagged<Context> context =
2631  Cast<Context>(js_frame->ReadInterpreterRegister(context_reg));
2632  DCHECK(IsContext(context));
2633 
2634  if (frame->is_baseline()) {
2635  BaselineFrame* sp_frame = BaselineFrame::cast(js_frame);
2636  Tagged<Code> code = sp_frame->LookupCode();
2637  intptr_t pc_offset = sp_frame->GetPCForBytecodeOffset(offset);
2638  // Patch the context register directly on the frame, so that we don't
2639  // need to have a context read + write in the baseline code.
2640  sp_frame->PatchContext(context);
2641  return FoundHandler(iter, Context(), code->instruction_start(),
2642  pc_offset, code->constant_pool(), return_sp,
2643  sp_frame->fp(), visited_frames);
2644  } else {
2645  InterpretedFrame::cast(js_frame)->PatchBytecodeOffset(
2646  static_cast<int>(offset));
2647 
2648  Tagged<Code> code = *BUILTIN_CODE(this, InterpreterEnterAtBytecode);
2649  // We subtract a frame from visited_frames because otherwise the
2650  // shadow stack will drop the underlying interpreter entry trampoline
2651  // in which the handler runs.
2652  //
2653  // An interpreted frame cannot be the first frame we look at
2654  // because at a minimum, an exit frame into C++ has to separate
2655  // it and the context in which this C++ code runs.
2656  CHECK_GE(visited_frames, 1);
2657  return FoundHandler(iter, context, code->instruction_start(), 0,
2658  code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(),
2659  visited_frames - 1);
2660  }
2661  }
2662 
2663  case StackFrame::BUILTIN: {
2664  // For builtin frames we are guaranteed not to find a handler.
2665  if (catchable_by_js) {
2666  CHECK_EQ(-1, BuiltinFrame::cast(frame)->LookupExceptionHandlerInTable(
2667  nullptr, nullptr));
2668  }
2669  break;
2670  }
2671  case StackFrame::INTERNAL: {
2672  auto code = frame->GcSafeLookupCode();
2673  if (code->builtin_id() ==
2674  Builtin::kDeoptimizationEntry_LazyAfterFastCall) {
2675  // Deoptimization Entry builtin does the exception handling for the
2676  // fast API if the fast API caller was marked for deoptimization.
2677  // Therefore, even though `frame->fp()` says that we are coming from
2678  // the Deoptimization Entry builtin, we have to do the stack unwinding
2679  // as if we come from the fast call. The return address of the fast
2680  // call is still stored in the isolate, so we can just load it from
2681  // there.
2682  Address fast_call_pc = isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_pc();
2683  std::optional<Tagged<GcSafeCode>> result =
2684  inner_pointer_to_code_cache()->GetCacheEntry(fast_call_pc)->code;
2685 
2686  CHECK(!result->is_null());
2687 
2688  Tagged<GcSafeCode> caller_code = result.value();
2689  int caller_offset =
2690  caller_code->GetOffsetFromInstructionStart(this, fast_call_pc);
2691  // Check if there is actually an exception handler registered at the
2692  // return address of the fast call. If so, then we tell the
2693  // deoptimizer of the exception and just return the the Deotimization
2694  // Entry. Otherwise we iterate the stack further to find a handler.
2695  HandlerTable table(caller_code->UnsafeCastToCode());
2696  int handler_offset = table.LookupReturn(caller_offset);
2697  if (handler_offset < 0) {
2698  break;
2699  }
2700 
2701  // If the target code is lazy deoptimized, we jump to the original
2702  // return address, but we make a note that we are throwing, so
2703  // that the deoptimizer can do the right thing.
2704  int offset =
2705  static_cast<int>(frame->pc() - code->instruction_start());
2706  set_deoptimizer_lazy_throw(true);
2707 
2708  return FoundHandler(iter, Context(),
2709  code->InstructionStart(this, frame->pc()), offset,
2710  code->constant_pool(), frame->sp(), frame->fp(),
2711  visited_frames);
2712  }
2713  break;
2714  }
2715  case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_WITH_CATCH: {
2716  // Builtin continuation frames with catch can handle exceptions.
2717  if (!catchable_by_js) break;
2718  JavaScriptBuiltinContinuationWithCatchFrame* js_frame =
2719  JavaScriptBuiltinContinuationWithCatchFrame::cast(frame);
2720  js_frame->SetException(exception);
2721 
2722  // Reconstruct the stack pointer from the frame pointer.
2723  Address return_sp = js_frame->fp() - js_frame->GetSPToFPDelta();
2724  Tagged<Code> code = js_frame->LookupCode();
2725  return FoundHandler(iter, Context(), code->instruction_start(), 0,
2726  code->constant_pool(), return_sp, frame->fp(),
2727  visited_frames);
2728  }
2729 
2730  default:
2731  // All other types can not handle exception.
2732  break;
2733  }
2734 
2735  if (frame->is_optimized_js()) {
2736  // Remove per-frame stored materialized objects.
2737  bool removed = materialized_object_store_->Remove(frame->fp());
2738  USE(removed);
2739  // If there were any materialized objects, the code should be
2740  // marked for deopt.
2741  DCHECK_IMPLIES(removed, frame->LookupCode()->marked_for_deoptimization());
2742  }
2743  }
2744 
2745  UNREACHABLE();
2746 } // namespace internal
2747 
2748 namespace {
2749 
2750 class StackFrameSummaryIterator {
2751  public:
2752  explicit StackFrameSummaryIterator(Isolate* isolate)
2753  : stack_iterator_(isolate), summaries_(), index_(0) {
2754  InitSummaries();
2755  }
2756  void Advance() {
2757  if (index_ == 0) {
2758  summaries_.frames.clear();
2759  stack_iterator_.Advance();
2760  InitSummaries();
2761  } else {
2762  index_--;
2763  }
2764  }
2765  bool done() const { return stack_iterator_.done(); }
2766  StackFrame* frame() const { return stack_iterator_.frame(); }
2767  bool has_frame_summary() const { return index_ < summaries_.size(); }
2768  const FrameSummary& frame_summary() const {
2769  DCHECK(has_frame_summary());
2770  return summaries_.frames[index_];
2771  }
2772  Isolate* isolate() const { return stack_iterator_.isolate(); }
2773 
2774  private:
2775  void InitSummaries() {
2776  if (!done() && frame()->is_javascript()) {
2777  summaries_ = JavaScriptFrame::cast(frame())->Summarize();
2778  DCHECK_GT(summaries_.size(), 0);
2779  index_ = summaries_.size() - 1;
2780  }
2781  }
2782  StackFrameIterator stack_iterator_;
2783  FrameSummaries summaries_;
2784  int index_;
2785 };
2786 
2787 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction CatchPredictionFor(Builtin builtin_id) {
2788  switch (builtin_id) {
2789 #define CASE(Name) \
2790  case Builtin::k##Name: \
2791  return HandlerTable::PROMISE;
2792  BUILTIN_PROMISE_REJECTION_PREDICTION_LIST(CASE)
2793 #undef CASE
2794  default:
2795  return HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT;
2796  }
2797 }
2798 
2799 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction PredictExceptionFromBytecode(
2800  Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecode, int code_offset) {
2801  HandlerTable table(bytecode);
2802  int handler_index = table.LookupHandlerIndexForRange(code_offset);
2803  if (handler_index < 0) return HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT;
2804  return table.GetRangePrediction(handler_index);
2805 }
2806 
2807 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction PredictException(const FrameSummary& summary,
2808  Isolate* isolate) {
2809  if (!summary.IsJavaScript()) {
2810  // This can happen when WASM is inlined by TurboFan. For now we ignore
2811  // frames that are not JavaScript.
2812  // TODO(https://crbug.com/349588762): We should also check Wasm code
2813  // for exception handling.
2814  return HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT;
2815  }
2816  PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate);
2817  DirectHandle<AbstractCode> code = summary.AsJavaScript().abstract_code();
2818  if (code->kind(cage_base) == CodeKind::BUILTIN) {
2819  return CatchPredictionFor(code->GetCode()->builtin_id());
2820  }
2821 
2822  // Must have been constructed from a bytecode array.
2823  CHECK_EQ(CodeKind::INTERPRETED_FUNCTION, code->kind(cage_base));
2824  return PredictExceptionFromBytecode(code->GetBytecodeArray(),
2825  summary.code_offset());
2826 }
2827 
2828 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction PredictExceptionFromGenerator(
2829  DirectHandle<JSGeneratorObject> generator, Isolate* isolate) {
2830  return PredictExceptionFromBytecode(
2831  generator->function()->shared()->GetBytecodeArray(isolate),
2832  GetGeneratorBytecodeOffset(generator));
2833 }
2834 
2835 Isolate::CatchType ToCatchType(HandlerTable::CatchPrediction prediction) {
2836  switch (prediction) {
2837  case HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT:
2838  return Isolate::NOT_CAUGHT;
2839  case HandlerTable::CAUGHT:
2840  return Isolate::CAUGHT_BY_JAVASCRIPT;
2841  case HandlerTable::PROMISE:
2842  return Isolate::CAUGHT_BY_PROMISE;
2843  case HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT_ASYNC_AWAIT:
2844  case HandlerTable::ASYNC_AWAIT:
2845  return Isolate::CAUGHT_BY_ASYNC_AWAIT;
2846  default:
2847  UNREACHABLE();
2848  }
2849 }
2850 
2851 Isolate::CatchType PredictExceptionCatchAtFrame(
2852  const StackFrameSummaryIterator& iterator) {
2853  const StackFrame* frame = iterator.frame();
2854  switch (frame->type()) {
2855  case StackFrame::ENTRY:
2856  case StackFrame::CONSTRUCT_ENTRY: {
2857  Address external_handler =
2858  iterator.isolate()->thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_address();
2859  Address entry_handler = frame->top_handler()->next_address();
2860  // The exception has been externally caught if and only if there is an
2861  // external handler which is on top of the top-most JS_ENTRY handler.
2862  if (external_handler != kNullAddress &&
2863  !iterator.isolate()->try_catch_handler()->IsVerbose()) {
2864  if (entry_handler == kNullAddress || entry_handler > external_handler) {
2865  return Isolate::CAUGHT_BY_EXTERNAL;
2866  }
2867  }
2868  } break;
2869 
2870  // For JavaScript frames we perform a lookup in the handler table.
2871  case StackFrame::INTERPRETED:
2872  case StackFrame::BASELINE:
2873  case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS:
2874  case StackFrame::MAGLEV:
2875  case StackFrame::BUILTIN: {
2876  DCHECK(iterator.has_frame_summary());
2877  return ToCatchType(
2878  PredictException(iterator.frame_summary(), iterator.isolate()));
2879  }
2880 
2881  case StackFrame::STUB: {
2882  Tagged<Code> code = *frame->LookupCode();
2883  if (code->kind() != CodeKind::BUILTIN || !code->has_handler_table() ||
2884  !code->is_turbofanned()) {
2885  break;
2886  }
2887 
2888  return ToCatchType(CatchPredictionFor(code->builtin_id()));
2889  }
2890 
2891  case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_WITH_CATCH: {
2892  Tagged<Code> code = *frame->LookupCode();
2893  return ToCatchType(CatchPredictionFor(code->builtin_id()));
2894  }
2895 
2896  default:
2897  // All other types can not handle exception.
2898  break;
2899  }
2900  return Isolate::NOT_CAUGHT;
2901 }
2902 } // anonymous namespace
2903 
2904 Isolate::CatchType Isolate::PredictExceptionCatcher() {
2905  if (TopExceptionHandlerType(Tagged<Object>()) ==
2906  ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch) {
2907  return CAUGHT_BY_EXTERNAL;
2908  }
2909 
2910  // Search for an exception handler by performing a full walk over the stack.
2911  for (StackFrameSummaryIterator iter(this); !iter.done(); iter.Advance()) {
2912  Isolate::CatchType prediction = PredictExceptionCatchAtFrame(iter);
2913  if (prediction != NOT_CAUGHT) return prediction;
2914  }
2915 
2916  // Handler not found.
2917  return NOT_CAUGHT;
2918 }

2921  if (v8_flags.stack_trace_on_illegal) PrintStack(stdout);
2922  return Throw(ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).illegal_access_string());

2925 void Isolate::PrintCurrentStackTrace(
2926  std::ostream& out,
2927  PrintCurrentStackTraceFilterCallback should_include_frame_callback) {
2928  DirectHandle<FixedArray> frames = CaptureSimpleStackTrace(
2929  this, FixedArray::kMaxLength, SKIP_NONE, factory()->undefined_value());
2930 
2931  IncrementalStringBuilder builder(this);
2932  for (int i = 0; i < frames->length(); ++i) {
2933  DirectHandle<CallSiteInfo> frame(Cast<CallSiteInfo>(frames->get(i)), this);
2934 
2935  if (should_include_frame_callback) {
2936  Tagged<Object> raw_script_name = frame->GetScriptNameOrSourceURL();
2937  v8::Local<v8::String> script_name_local;
2938  v8::Isolate* v8_isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this);
2939 
2940  if (IsString(raw_script_name)) {
2941  DirectHandle<String> script_name =
2942  Handle<String>(Cast<String>(raw_script_name), this);
2943  script_name_local = v8::Utils::ToLocal(script_name);
2944  } else {
2945  script_name_local = v8::String::Empty(v8_isolate);
2946  }
2947 
2948  if (should_include_frame_callback(v8_isolate, script_name_local)) {
2949  SerializeCallSiteInfo(this, frame, &builder);
2950  } else {
2951  builder.AppendString("<redacted>");
2952  }
2953  } else {
2954  SerializeCallSiteInfo(this, frame, &builder);
2955  }
2956 
2957  if (i != frames->length() - 1) builder.AppendCharacter('\n');
2958  }
2959 
2960  DirectHandle<String> stack_trace = builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
2961  stack_trace->PrintOn(out);
2962 }

2964 bool Isolate::ComputeLocation(MessageLocation* target) {
2965  DebuggableStackFrameIterator it(this);
2966  if (it.done()) return false;
2967  // Compute the location from the function and the relocation info of the
2968  // baseline code. For optimized code this will use the deoptimization
2969  // information to get canonical location information.
2970 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2971  wasm::WasmCodeRefScope code_ref_scope;
2972 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2973  FrameSummary summary = it.GetTopValidFrame();
2974  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared;
2975  Handle<Object> script = summary.script();
2976  if (!IsScript(*script) ||
2977  IsUndefined(Cast<Script>(*script)->source(), this)) {
2978  return false;
2979  }
2980 
2981  if (summary.IsJavaScript()) {
2982  shared = handle(summary.AsJavaScript().function()->shared(), this);
2983  }
2984  if (summary.AreSourcePositionsAvailable()) {
2985  int pos = summary.SourcePosition();
2986  *target = MessageLocation(Cast<Script>(script), pos, pos + 1, shared);
2987  } else {
2988  *target =
2989  MessageLocation(Cast<Script>(script), shared, summary.code_offset());
2990  }
2991  return true;
2992 }
2993 
2994 bool Isolate::ComputeLocationFromException(MessageLocation* target,
2995  DirectHandle<Object> exception) {
2996  if (!IsJSObject(*exception)) return false;
2997 
2998  DirectHandle<Name> start_pos_symbol = factory()->error_start_pos_symbol();
2999  DirectHandle<Object> start_pos = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
3000  this, Cast<JSObject>(exception), start_pos_symbol);
3001  if (!IsSmi(*start_pos)) return false;
3002  int start_pos_value = Cast<Smi>(*start_pos).value();
3003 
3004  DirectHandle<Name> end_pos_symbol = factory()->error_end_pos_symbol();
3005  DirectHandle<Object> end_pos = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
3006  this, Cast<JSObject>(exception), end_pos_symbol);
3007  if (!IsSmi(*end_pos)) return false;
3008  int end_pos_value = Cast<Smi>(*end_pos).value();
3009 
3010  DirectHandle<Name> script_symbol = factory()->error_script_symbol();
3011  DirectHandle<Object> script = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
3012  this, Cast<JSObject>(exception), script_symbol);
3013  if (!IsScript(*script)) return false;
3014 
3015  Handle<Script> cast_script(Cast<Script>(*script), this);
3016  *target = MessageLocation(cast_script, start_pos_value, end_pos_value);
3017  return true;
3018 }

3020 bool Isolate::ComputeLocationFromSimpleStackTrace(
3021  MessageLocation* target, DirectHandle<Object> exception) {
3022  if (!IsJSReceiver(*exception)) {
3023  return false;
3024  }
3025  DirectHandle<FixedArray> call_site_infos =
3026  GetSimpleStackTrace(Cast<JSReceiver>(exception));
3027  for (int i = 0; i < call_site_infos->length(); ++i) {
3028  DirectHandle<CallSiteInfo> call_site_info(
3029  Cast<CallSiteInfo>(call_site_infos->get(i)), this);
3030  if (CallSiteInfo::ComputeLocation(call_site_info, target)) {
3031  return true;
3032  }
3033  }
3034  return false;
3035 }

3037 bool Isolate::ComputeLocationFromDetailedStackTrace(
3038  MessageLocation* target, DirectHandle<Object> exception) {
3039  if (!IsJSReceiver(*exception)) return false;
3040 
3041  DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> stack_trace =
3042  GetDetailedStackTrace(Cast<JSReceiver>(exception));
3043  if (stack_trace.is_null() || stack_trace->length() == 0) {
3044  return false;
3045  }
3046 
3047  DirectHandle<StackFrameInfo> info(stack_trace->get(0), this);
3048  const int pos = StackFrameInfo::GetSourcePosition(info);
3049  *target = MessageLocation(handle(info->script(), this), pos, pos + 1);
3050  return true;
3051 }

3053 Handle<JSMessageObject> Isolate::CreateMessage(DirectHandle<Object> exception,
3054  MessageLocation* location) {
3055  DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> stack_trace;
3056  if (capture_stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_) {
3057  if (IsJSObject(*exception)) {
3058  // First, check whether a stack trace is already present on this object.
3059  // It maybe an Error, or the embedder may have stored a stack trace using
3060  // Exception::CaptureStackTrace().
3061  // If the lookup fails, we fall through and capture the stack trace
3062  // at this throw site.
3063  stack_trace = GetDetailedStackTrace(Cast<JSObject>(exception));
3064  }
3065  if (stack_trace.is_null()) {
3066  // Not an error object, we capture stack and location at throw site.
3067  stack_trace = CaptureDetailedStackTrace(
3068  stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_frame_limit_,
3069  stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions_options_);
3070  }
3071  }
3072  MessageLocation computed_location;
3073  if (location == nullptr &&
3074  (ComputeLocationFromException(&computed_location, exception) ||
3075  ComputeLocationFromSimpleStackTrace(&computed_location, exception) ||
3076  ComputeLocation(&computed_location))) {
3077  location = &computed_location;
3078  }
3079 
3080  return MessageHandler::MakeMessageObject(this,
3081  MessageTemplate::kUncaughtException,
3082  location, exception, stack_trace);
3083 }
3084 
3085 Handle<JSMessageObject> Isolate::CreateMessageFromException(
3086  DirectHandle<Object> exception) {
3087  DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> stack_trace;
3088  if (IsJSError(*exception)) {
3089  stack_trace = GetDetailedStackTrace(Cast<JSObject>(exception));
3090  }
3091 
3092  MessageLocation* location = nullptr;
3093  MessageLocation computed_location;
3094  if (ComputeLocationFromException(&computed_location, exception) ||
3095  ComputeLocationFromDetailedStackTrace(&computed_location, exception)) {
3096  location = &computed_location;
3097  }
3098 
3099  return MessageHandler::MakeMessageObject(this,
3100  MessageTemplate::kPlaceholderOnly,
3101  location, exception, stack_trace);
3102 }
3103 
3104 Isolate::ExceptionHandlerType Isolate::TopExceptionHandlerType(
3105  Tagged<Object> exception) {
3106  DCHECK_NE(ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).the_hole_value(), exception);
3107 
3108  Address js_handler = Isolate::handler(thread_local_top());
3109  Address external_handler = thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_address();
3110 
3111  // A handler cannot be on top if it doesn't exist. For uncatchable exceptions,
3112  // the JavaScript handler cannot be on top.
3113  if (js_handler == kNullAddress || !is_catchable_by_javascript(exception)) {
3114  if (external_handler == kNullAddress) {
3115  return ExceptionHandlerType::kNone;
3116  }
3117  return ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch;
3118  }
3119 
3120  if (external_handler == kNullAddress) {
3121  return ExceptionHandlerType::kJavaScriptHandler;
3122  }
3123 
3124  // The exception has been externally caught if and only if there is an
3125  // external handler which is on top of the top-most JS_ENTRY handler.
3126  //
3127  // Note, that finally clauses would re-throw an exception unless it's aborted
3128  // by jumps in control flow (like return, break, etc.) and we'll have another
3129  // chance to set proper v8::TryCatch later.
3130  DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, external_handler);
3131  DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, js_handler);
3132  if (external_handler < js_handler) {
3133  return ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch;
3134  }
3135  return ExceptionHandlerType::kJavaScriptHandler;
3136 }

3138 std::vector<MemoryRange>* Isolate::GetCodePages() const {
3139  return code_pages_.load(std::memory_order_acquire);
3140 }
3141 
3142 void Isolate::SetCodePages(std::vector<MemoryRange>* new_code_pages) {
3143  code_pages_.store(new_code_pages, std::memory_order_release);
3144 }
3145 
3146 void Isolate::ReportPendingMessages(bool report) {
3147  Tagged<Object> exception_obj = exception();
3148  ExceptionHandlerType top_handler = TopExceptionHandlerType(exception_obj);
3149 
3150  // Try to propagate the exception to an external v8::TryCatch handler. If
3151  // propagation was unsuccessful, then we will get another chance at reporting
3152  // the pending message if the exception is re-thrown.
3153  bool has_been_propagated = PropagateExceptionToExternalTryCatch(top_handler);
3154  if (!has_been_propagated) return;
3155  if (!report) return;
3156 
3157  DCHECK(AllowExceptions::IsAllowed(this));
3158 
3159  // The embedder might run script in response to an exception.
3160  AllowJavascriptExecutionDebugOnly allow_script(this);
3161 
3162  // Clear the pending message object early to avoid endless recursion.
3163  Tagged<Object> message_obj = pending_message();
3164  clear_pending_message();
3165 
3166  // For uncatchable exceptions we do nothing. If needed, the exception and the
3167  // message have already been propagated to v8::TryCatch.
3168  if (!is_catchable_by_javascript(exception_obj)) return;
3169 
3170  // Determine whether the message needs to be reported to all message handlers
3171  // depending on whether the topmost external v8::TryCatch is verbose. We know
3172  // there's no JavaScript handler on top; if there was, we would've returned
3173  // early.
3174  DCHECK_NE(ExceptionHandlerType::kJavaScriptHandler, top_handler);
3175 
3176  bool should_report_exception;
3177  if (top_handler == ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch) {
3178  should_report_exception = try_catch_handler()->is_verbose_;
3179  } else {
3180  should_report_exception = true;
3181  }
3182 
3183  // Actually report the pending message to all message handlers.
3184  if (!IsTheHole(message_obj, this) && should_report_exception) {
3185  HandleScope scope(this);
3186  DirectHandle<JSMessageObject> message(Cast<JSMessageObject>(message_obj),
3187  this);
3188  Handle<Script> script(message->script(), this);
3189  // Clear the exception and restore it afterwards, otherwise
3190  // CollectSourcePositions will abort.
3191  {
3192  ExceptionScope exception_scope(this);
3193  JSMessageObject::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(this, message);
3194  }
3195  int start_pos = message->GetStartPosition();
3196  int end_pos = message->GetEndPosition();
3197  MessageLocation location(script, start_pos, end_pos);
3198  MessageHandler::ReportMessage(this, &location, message);
3199  }
3200 }
3201 
3202 namespace {
3203 bool ReceiverIsForwardingHandler(Isolate* isolate,
3204  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler) {
3205  // Recurse to the forwarding Promise (e.g. return false) due to
3206  // - await reaction forwarding to the throwaway Promise, which has
3207  // a dependency edge to the outer Promise.
3208  // - PromiseIdResolveHandler forwarding to the output of .then
3209  // - Promise.all/Promise.race forwarding to a throwaway Promise, which
3210  // has a dependency edge to the generated outer Promise.
3211  // Otherwise, this is a real reject handler for the Promise.
3212  DirectHandle<Symbol> key =
3213  isolate->factory()->promise_forwarding_handler_symbol();
3214  DirectHandle<Object> forwarding_handler =
3215  JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(isolate, handler, key);
3216  return !IsUndefined(*forwarding_handler, isolate);
3217 }
3218 
3219 bool WalkPromiseTreeInternal(
3220  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
3221  const std::function<void(Isolate::PromiseHandler)>& callback) {
3222  if (promise->status() != Promise::kPending) {
3223  // If a rejection reaches an exception that isn't pending, it will be
3224  // treated as caught.
3225  return true;
3226  }
3227 
3228  bool any_caught = false;
3229  bool any_uncaught = false;
3230  DirectHandle<Object> current(promise->reactions(), isolate);
3231  while (!IsSmi(*current)) {
3232  auto reaction = Cast<PromiseReaction>(current);
3233  DirectHandle<HeapObject> promise_or_capability(
3234  reaction->promise_or_capability(), isolate);
3235  if (!IsUndefined(*promise_or_capability, isolate)) {
3236  if (!IsJSPromise(*promise_or_capability)) {
3237  promise_or_capability = direct_handle(
3238  Cast<PromiseCapability>(promise_or_capability)->promise(), isolate);
3239  }
3240  if (IsJSPromise(*promise_or_capability)) {
3241  DirectHandle<JSPromise> next_promise =
3242  Cast<JSPromise>(promise_or_capability);
3243  bool caught = false;
3244  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> reject_handler;
3245  if (!IsUndefined(reaction->reject_handler(), isolate)) {
3246  reject_handler = direct_handle(
3247  Cast<JSReceiver>(reaction->reject_handler()), isolate);
3248  if (!ReceiverIsForwardingHandler(isolate, reject_handler) &&
3249  !IsBuiltinForwardingRejectHandler(isolate, *reject_handler)) {
3250  caught = true;
3251  }
3252  }
3253  // Pass each handler to the callback
3254  DirectHandle<JSGeneratorObject> async_function;
3255  if (TryGetAsyncGenerator(isolate, reaction).ToHandle(&async_function)) {
3256  caught = caught ||
3257  PredictExceptionFromGenerator(async_function, isolate) ==
3258  HandlerTable::CAUGHT;
3259  // Look at the async function, not the individual handlers
3260  callback({async_function->function()->shared(), true});
3261  } else {
3262  // Not an async function, look at individual handlers
3263  if (!IsUndefined(reaction->fulfill_handler(), isolate)) {
3264  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fulfill_handler(
3265  Cast<JSReceiver>(reaction->fulfill_handler()), isolate);
3266  if (!ReceiverIsForwardingHandler(isolate, fulfill_handler)) {
3267  if (IsBuiltinFunction(isolate, *fulfill_handler,
3268  Builtin::kPromiseThenFinally)) {
3269  // If this is the finally handler, get the wrapped callback
3270  // from the context to use instead
3271  DirectHandle<Context> context(
3272  Cast<JSFunction>(reaction->fulfill_handler())->context(),
3273  isolate);
3274  int const index =
3275  PromiseBuiltins::PromiseFinallyContextSlot::kOnFinallySlot;
3276  fulfill_handler = direct_handle(
3277  Cast<JSReceiver>(context->GetNoCell(index)), isolate);
3278  }
3279  if (IsJSFunction(*fulfill_handler)) {
3280  callback({Cast<JSFunction>(fulfill_handler)->shared(), true});
3281  }
3282  }
3283  }
3284  if (caught) {
3285  // We've already checked that this isn't undefined or
3286  // a forwarding handler
3287  if (IsJSFunction(*reject_handler)) {
3288  callback({Cast<JSFunction>(reject_handler)->shared(), true});
3289  }
3290  }
3291  }
3292  caught =
3293  caught || WalkPromiseTreeInternal(isolate, next_promise, callback);
3294  any_caught = any_caught || caught;
3295  any_uncaught = any_uncaught || !caught;
3296  }
3297  } else {
3298 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3299  DirectHandle<WasmSuspenderObject> suspender;
3300  if (TryGetWasmSuspender(isolate, reaction->fulfill_handler())
3301  .ToHandle(&suspender)) {
3302  // If in the future we support Wasm exceptions or ignore listing in
3303  // Wasm, we will need to iterate through these frames. For now, we
3304  // only care about the resulting promise.
3305  DirectHandle<JSPromise> next_promise(suspender->promise(), isolate);
3306  bool caught = WalkPromiseTreeInternal(isolate, next_promise, callback);
3307  any_caught = any_caught || caught;
3308  any_uncaught = any_uncaught || !caught;
3309  }
3310 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3311  }
3312  current = direct_handle(reaction->next(), isolate);
3313  }
3314 
3315  bool caught = any_caught && !any_uncaught;
3316 
3317  if (!caught) {
3318  // If there is an outer promise, follow that to see if it is caught.
3319  DirectHandle<Symbol> key = isolate->factory()->promise_handled_by_symbol();
3320  DirectHandle<Object> outer_promise_obj =
3321  JSObject::GetDataProperty(isolate, promise, key);
3322  if (IsJSPromise(*outer_promise_obj)) {
3323  return WalkPromiseTreeInternal(
3324  isolate, Cast<JSPromise>(outer_promise_obj), callback);
3325  }
3326  }
3327  return caught;
3328 }
3329 
3330 // Helper functions to scan for calls to .catch.
3331 using interpreter::Bytecode;
3332 using interpreter::Bytecodes;
3333 
3334 enum PromiseMethod { kThen, kCatch, kFinally, kInvalid };
3335 
3336 // Requires the iterator to be on a GetNamedProperty instruction
3337 PromiseMethod GetPromiseMethod(
3338  Isolate* isolate, const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
3339  DirectHandle<Object> object = iterator.GetConstantForIndexOperand(1, isolate);
3340  if (!IsString(*object)) {
3341  return kInvalid;
3342  }
3343  auto str = Cast<String>(object);
3344  if (str->Equals(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).then_string())) {
3345  return kThen;
3346  } else if (str->IsEqualTo(base::StaticCharVector("catch"))) {
3347  return kCatch;
3348  } else if (str->IsEqualTo(base::StaticCharVector("finally"))) {
3349  return kFinally;
3350  } else {
3351  return kInvalid;
3352  }
3353 }
3354 
3355 bool TouchesRegister(const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator,
3356  int index) {
3357  Bytecode bytecode = iterator.current_bytecode();
3358  int num_operands = Bytecodes::NumberOfOperands(bytecode);
3359  const interpreter::OperandType* operand_types =
3360  Bytecodes::GetOperandTypes(bytecode);
3361 
3362  for (int i = 0; i < num_operands; ++i) {
3363  if (Bytecodes::IsRegisterOperandType(operand_types[i])) {
3364  int base_index = iterator.GetRegisterOperand(i).index();
3365  int num_registers;
3366  if (Bytecodes::IsRegisterListOperandType(operand_types[i])) {
3367  num_registers = iterator.GetRegisterCountOperand(++i);
3368  } else {
3369  num_registers =
3370  Bytecodes::GetNumberOfRegistersRepresentedBy(operand_types[i]);
3371  }
3372 
3373  if (base_index <= index && index < base_index + num_registers) {
3374  return true;
3375  }
3376  }
3377  }
3378 
3379  if (Bytecodes::WritesImplicitRegister(bytecode)) {
3380  return iterator.GetStarTargetRegister().index() == index;
3381  }
3382 
3383  return false;
3384 }
3385 
3386 bool CallsCatchMethod(Isolate* isolate, Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array,
3387  int offset) {
3388  interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator iterator(bytecode_array, offset);
3389 
3390  while (!iterator.done()) {
3391  // We should be on a call instruction of some kind. While we could check
3392  // this, it may be difficult to create an exhaustive list of instructions
3393  // that could call, such as property getters, but at a minimum this
3394  // instruction should write to the accumulator.
3395  if (!Bytecodes::WritesAccumulator(iterator.current_bytecode())) {
3396  return false;
3397  }
3398 
3399  iterator.Advance();
3400  // While usually the next instruction is a Star, sometimes we store and
3401  // reload from context first.
3402  if (iterator.done()) {
3403  return false;
3404  }
3405  if (iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kStaCurrentContextSlot ||
3406  iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kStaCurrentContextSlotNoCell) {
3407  // Step over patterns like:
3408  // StaCurrentContextSlot[NoCell] [x]
3409  // LdaImmutableCurrentContextSlot/LdaCurrentContext[NoCell] [x]
3410  unsigned int slot = iterator.GetIndexOperand(0);
3411  iterator.Advance();
3412  if (!iterator.done() &&
3413  (iterator.current_bytecode() ==
3414  Bytecode::kLdaImmutableCurrentContextSlot ||
3415  iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kLdaCurrentContextSlot ||
3416  iterator.current_bytecode() ==
3417  Bytecode::kLdaCurrentContextSlotNoCell)) {
3418  if (iterator.GetIndexOperand(0) != slot) {
3419  return false;
3420  }
3421  iterator.Advance();
3422  }
3423  } else if (iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kStaContextSlot ||
3424  iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kStaContextSlotNoCell) {
3425  // Step over patterns like:
3426  // StaContextSlot[NoCell] r_x [y] [z]
3427  // LdaContextSlot[NoCell] r_x [y] [z]
3428  int context = iterator.GetRegisterOperand(0).index();
3429  unsigned int slot = iterator.GetIndexOperand(1);
3430  unsigned int depth = iterator.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(2);
3431  iterator.Advance();
3432  if (!iterator.done() &&
3433  (iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kLdaImmutableContextSlot ||
3434  iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kLdaContextSlot ||
3435  iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kLdaContextSlotNoCell)) {
3436  if (iterator.GetRegisterOperand(0).index() != context ||
3437  iterator.GetIndexOperand(1) != slot ||
3438  iterator.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(2) != depth) {
3439  return false;
3440  }
3441  iterator.Advance();
3442  }
3443  } else if (iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kStaLookupSlot) {
3444  // Step over patterns like:
3445  // StaLookupSlot [x] [_]
3446  // LdaLookupSlot [x]
3447  unsigned int slot = iterator.GetIndexOperand(0);
3448  iterator.Advance();
3449  if (!iterator.done() &&
3450  (iterator.current_bytecode() == Bytecode::kLdaLookupSlot ||
3451  iterator.current_bytecode() ==
3452  Bytecode::kLdaLookupSlotInsideTypeof)) {
3453  if (iterator.GetIndexOperand(0) != slot) {
3454  return false;
3455  }
3456  iterator.Advance();
3457  }
3458  }
3459 
3460  // Next instruction should be a Star (store accumulator to register)
3461  if (iterator.done() || !Bytecodes::IsAnyStar(iterator.current_bytecode())) {
3462  return false;
3463  }
3464  // The register it stores to will be assumed to be our promise
3465  int promise_register = iterator.GetStarTargetRegister().index();
3466 
3467  // TODO(crbug/40283993): Should we loop over non-matching instructions here
3468  // to allow code like
3469  // `const promise = foo(); console.log(...); promise.catch(...);`?
3470 
3471  iterator.Advance();
3472  // We should be on a GetNamedProperty instruction.
3473  if (iterator.done() ||
3474  iterator.current_bytecode() != Bytecode::kGetNamedProperty ||
3475  iterator.GetRegisterOperand(0).index() != promise_register) {
3476  return false;
3477  }
3478  PromiseMethod method = GetPromiseMethod(isolate, iterator);
3479  if (method == kInvalid) {
3480  return false;
3481  }
3482 
3483  iterator.Advance();
3484  // Next instruction should be a Star (save immediate to register)
3485  if (iterator.done() || !Bytecodes::IsAnyStar(iterator.current_bytecode())) {
3486  return false;
3487  }
3488  // This register contains the method we will eventually invoke
3489  int method_register = iterator.GetStarTargetRegister().index();
3490  if (method_register == promise_register) {
3491  return false;
3492  }
3493 
3494  // Now we step over multiple instructions creating the arguments for the
3495  // method.
3496  while (true) {
3497  iterator.Advance();
3498  if (iterator.done()) {
3499  return false;
3500  }
3501  Bytecode bytecode = iterator.current_bytecode();
3502  if (bytecode == Bytecode::kCallProperty1 ||
3503  bytecode == Bytecode::kCallProperty2) {
3504  // This is a call property call of the right size, but is it a call of
3505  // the method and on the promise?
3506  if (iterator.GetRegisterOperand(0).index() == method_register &&
3507  iterator.GetRegisterOperand(1).index() == promise_register) {
3508  // This is our method call, but does it catch?
3509  if (method == kCatch ||
3510  (method == kThen && bytecode == Bytecode::kCallProperty2)) {
3511  return true;
3512  }
3513  // Break out of the inner loop, continuing the outer loop. We
3514  // will use the same procedure to check for chained method calls.
3515  break;
3516  }
3517  }
3518 
3519  // Check for some instructions that should make us give up scanning.
3520  if (Bytecodes::IsJump(bytecode) || Bytecodes::IsSwitch(bytecode) ||
3521  Bytecodes::Returns(bytecode) ||
3522  Bytecodes::UnconditionallyThrows(bytecode)) {
3523  // Stop scanning at control flow instructions that aren't calls
3524  return false;
3525  }
3526 
3527  if (TouchesRegister(iterator, promise_register) ||
3528  TouchesRegister(iterator, method_register)) {
3529  // Stop scanning at instruction that unexpectedly interacts with one of
3530  // the registers we care about.
3531  return false;
3532  }
3533  }
3534  }
3535  return false;
3536 }
3537 
3538 bool CallsCatchMethod(const StackFrameSummaryIterator& iterator) {
3539  if (!iterator.frame()->is_javascript()) {
3540  return false;
3541  }
3542  if (iterator.frame_summary().IsJavaScript()) {
3543  auto& js_summary = iterator.frame_summary().AsJavaScript();
3544  if (IsBytecodeArray(*js_summary.abstract_code())) {
3545  if (CallsCatchMethod(iterator.isolate(),
3546  Cast<BytecodeArray>(js_summary.abstract_code()),
3547  js_summary.code_offset())) {
3548  return true;
3549  }
3550  }
3551  }
3552  return false;
3553 }
3554 
3555 } // namespace
3556 
3557 bool Isolate::WalkCallStackAndPromiseTree(
3558  MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise> rejected_promise,
3559  const std::function<void(PromiseHandler)>& callback) {
3560  bool is_promise_rejection = false;
3561 
3562  DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise;
3563  if (rejected_promise.ToHandle(&promise)) {
3564  is_promise_rejection = true;
3565  // If the promise has reactions, follow them and assume we are done. If
3566  // it has no reactions, assume promise is returned up the call stack and
3567  // trace accordingly. If the promise is not pending, it has no reactions
3568  // and is probably the result of a call to Promise.reject().
3569  if (promise->status() != Promise::kPending) {
3570  // Ignore this promise; set to null
3571  rejected_promise = MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>();
3572  } else if (IsSmi(promise->reactions())) {
3573  // Also check that there is no outer promise
3574  DirectHandle<Symbol> key = factory()->promise_handled_by_symbol();
3575  if (!IsJSPromise(*JSObject::GetDataProperty(this, promise, key))) {
3576  // Ignore this promise; set to null
3577  rejected_promise = MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>();
3578  }
3579  }
3580  }
3581 
3582  if (!is_promise_rejection && TopExceptionHandlerType(Tagged<Object>()) ==
3583  ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch) {
3584  return true; // caught by external
3585  }
3586 
3587  // Search for an exception handler by performing a full walk over the stack.
3588  for (StackFrameSummaryIterator iter(this); !iter.done(); iter.Advance()) {
3589  Isolate::CatchType prediction = PredictExceptionCatchAtFrame(iter);
3590 
3591  bool caught;
3592  if (rejected_promise.is_null()) {
3593  switch (prediction) {
3594  case NOT_CAUGHT:
3595  // Uncaught unless this is a promise rejection and the code will call
3596  // .catch()
3597  caught = is_promise_rejection && CallsCatchMethod(iter);
3598  break;
3599  case CAUGHT_BY_ASYNC_AWAIT:
3600  // Uncaught unless this is a promise rejection and the code will call
3601  // .catch()
3602  caught = is_promise_rejection && CallsCatchMethod(iter);
3603  // Exceptions turn into promise rejections here
3604  is_promise_rejection = true;
3605  break;
3606  case CAUGHT_BY_PROMISE:
3607  // Exceptions turn into promise rejections here
3608  // TODO(leese): Perhaps we can handle the case where the reject method
3609  // is called in the promise constructor and it is still on the stack
3610  // by ignoring all try/catches on the stack until we get to the right
3611  // CAUGHT_BY_PROMISE?
3612  is_promise_rejection = true;
3613  caught = false;
3614  break;
3615  case CAUGHT_BY_EXTERNAL:
3616  caught = !is_promise_rejection;
3617  break;
3618  case CAUGHT_BY_JAVASCRIPT:
3619  caught = true;
3620  // Unless this is a promise rejection and the function is not async...
3621  DCHECK(iter.has_frame_summary());
3622  const FrameSummary& summary = iter.frame_summary();
3623  if (is_promise_rejection && summary.IsJavaScript()) {
3624  // If the catch happens in an async function, assume it will
3625  // await this promise. Alternately, if the code will call .catch,
3626  // assume it is on this promise.
3627  caught = IsAsyncFunction(iter.frame_summary()
3628  .AsJavaScript()
3629  .function()
3630  ->shared()
3631  ->kind()) ||
3632  CallsCatchMethod(iter);
3633  }
3634  break;
3635  }
3636  } else {
3637  // The frame that calls the reject handler will not catch that promise
3638  // regardless of what else it does. We will trace where this rejection
3639  // goes according to its reaction callbacks, but we first need to handle
3640  // the topmost debuggable frame just to ensure there is a debuggable
3641  // frame and to permit ignore listing there.
3642  caught = false;
3643  }
3644 
3645  if (iter.frame()->is_javascript()) {
3646  bool debuggable = false;
3647  DCHECK(iter.has_frame_summary());
3648  const FrameSummary& summary = iter.frame_summary();
3649  if (summary.IsJavaScript()) {
3650  const auto& info = summary.AsJavaScript().function()->shared();
3651  if (info->IsSubjectToDebugging()) {
3652  callback({*info, false});
3653  debuggable = true;
3654  }
3655  }
3656 
3657  // Ignore the rest of the call stack if this is a rejection and the
3658  // promise has handlers; we will trace where the rejection goes instead
3659  // of where it came from.
3660  if (debuggable && !rejected_promise.is_null()) {
3661  break;
3662  }
3663  }
3664 
3665  if (caught) {
3666  return true;
3667  }
3668  }
3669 
3670  if (rejected_promise.is_null()) {
3671  // Now follow promises if this is a promise reaction job.
3672  rejected_promise = TryGetCurrentTaskPromise(this);
3673  }
3674 
3675  if (rejected_promise.ToHandle(&promise)) {
3676  return WalkPromiseTreeInternal(this, promise, callback);
3677  }
3678  // Nothing caught.
3679  return false;
3680 }

3698 void Isolate::InstallConditionalFeatures(DirectHandle<NativeContext> context) {
3699  DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global =
3700  direct_handle(context->global_object(), this);
3701  // If some fuzzer decided to make the global object non-extensible, then
3702  // we can't install any features (and would CHECK-fail if we tried).
3703  if (!global->map()->is_extensible()) return;
3704  DirectHandle<String> sab_name = factory()->SharedArrayBuffer_string();
3705  if (IsSharedArrayBufferConstructorEnabled(context)) {
3706  if (!JSObject::HasRealNamedProperty(this, global, sab_name)
3707  .FromMaybe(true)) {
3708  JSObject::AddProperty(this, global, factory()->SharedArrayBuffer_string(),
3709  shared_array_buffer_fun(), DONT_ENUM);
3710  }
3711  }
3712 }

3720  return sharedarraybuffer_constructor_enabled_callback()(api_context);
3721  }
3722  return false;
3723 }

3783 DirectHandle<NativeContext> Isolate::GetIncumbentContextSlow() {
3784  JavaScriptStackFrameIterator it(this);
3785 
3786  // 1st candidate: most-recently-entered author function's context
3787  // if it's newer than the last Context::BackupIncumbentScope entry.
3788  //
3789  // NOTE: This code assumes that the stack grows downward.
3790  Address top_backup_incumbent =
3791  top_backup_incumbent_scope()
3792  ? top_backup_incumbent_scope()->JSStackComparableAddressPrivate()
3793  : 0;
3794  if (!it.done() &&
3795  (!top_backup_incumbent || it.frame()->sp() < top_backup_incumbent)) {
3796  Tagged<Context> context = Cast<Context>(it.frame()->context());
3797  // If the topmost_script_having_context is set then it must be correct.
3798  if (DEBUG_BOOL && !topmost_script_having_context().is_null()) {
3799  DCHECK_EQ(topmost_script_having_context()->native_context(),
3800  context->native_context());
3801  }
3802  return DirectHandle<NativeContext>(context->native_context(), this);
3803  }
3804  DCHECK(topmost_script_having_context().is_null());
3805 
3806  // 2nd candidate: the last Context::Scope's incumbent context if any.
3807  if (top_backup_incumbent_scope()) {
3808  v8::Local<v8::Context> incumbent_context =
3809  top_backup_incumbent_scope()->backup_incumbent_context_;
3810  return Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*incumbent_context);
3811  }
3812 
3813  // Last candidate: the entered context or microtask context.
3814  // Given that there is no other author function is running, there must be
3815  // no cross-context function running, then the incumbent realm must match
3816  // the entry realm.
3817  v8::Local<v8::Context> entered_context =
3818  reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this)->GetEnteredOrMicrotaskContext();
3819  return Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*entered_context);
3820 }

3832  return from + sizeof(ThreadLocalTop);

3835 void Isolate::ReleaseSharedPtrs() {
3836  base::MutexGuard lock(&managed_ptr_destructors_mutex_);
3837  while (managed_ptr_destructors_head_) {
3838  ManagedPtrDestructor* l = managed_ptr_destructors_head_;
3839  ManagedPtrDestructor* n = nullptr;
3840  managed_ptr_destructors_head_ = nullptr;
3841  for (; l != nullptr; l = n) {
3842  l->external_memory_accounter_.Decrease(
3843  reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this), l->estimated_size_);
3844  l->destructor_(l->shared_ptr_ptr_);
3845  n = l->next_;
3846  delete l;
3847  }
3848  }
3849 }

3851 bool Isolate::IsBuiltinTableHandleLocation(Address* handle_location) {
3852  FullObjectSlot location(handle_location);
3853  FullObjectSlot first_root(builtin_table());
3854  FullObjectSlot last_root(first_root + Builtins::kBuiltinCount);
3855  if (location >= last_root) return false;
3856  if (location < first_root) return false;
3857  return true;
3858 }

3860 void Isolate::RegisterManagedPtrDestructor(ManagedPtrDestructor* destructor) {
3861  base::MutexGuard lock(&managed_ptr_destructors_mutex_);
3862  DCHECK_NULL(destructor->prev_);
3863  DCHECK_NULL(destructor->next_);
3864  if (managed_ptr_destructors_head_) {
3865  managed_ptr_destructors_head_->prev_ = destructor;
3866  }
3867  destructor->next_ = managed_ptr_destructors_head_;
3868  managed_ptr_destructors_head_ = destructor;
3869 }
3870 
3871 void Isolate::UnregisterManagedPtrDestructor(ManagedPtrDestructor* destructor) {
3872  base::MutexGuard lock(&managed_ptr_destructors_mutex_);
3873  if (destructor->prev_) {
3874  destructor->prev_->next_ = destructor->next_;
3875  } else {
3876  DCHECK_EQ(destructor, managed_ptr_destructors_head_);
3877  managed_ptr_destructors_head_ = destructor->next_;
3878  }
3879  if (destructor->next_) destructor->next_->prev_ = destructor->prev_;
3880  destructor->prev_ = nullptr;
3881  destructor->next_ = nullptr;
3882 }

3896  Address stack_base = reinterpret_cast<Address>(stack.end());

3916 
3917 void Isolate::SwitchStacks(wasm::StackMemory* from, wasm::StackMemory* to) {
3918  // Synchronize the stack limit with the active continuation for
3919  // stack-switching. This can be done before or after changing the stack
3920  // pointer itself, as long as we update both before the next stack check.
3921  // {StackGuard::SetStackLimitForStackSwitching} doesn't update the value of
3922  // the jslimit if it contains a sentinel value, and it is also thread-safe. So
3923  // if an interrupt is requested before, during or after this call, it will be
3924  // preserved and handled at the next stack check.
3925 
3926  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3927  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_stack_switching) {
3928  if (to->jmpbuf()->state == wasm::JumpBuffer::Suspended) {
3929  PrintF("Switch from stack %d to %d (resume/start)\n", from->id(),
3930  to->id());
3931  } else if (to->jmpbuf()->state == wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive) {
3932  PrintF("Switch from stack %d to %d (suspend/return)\n", from->id(),
3933  to->id());
3934  } else {
3935  UNREACHABLE();
3936  }
3937  }
3938  if (to->jmpbuf()->state == wasm::JumpBuffer::Suspended) {
3939  to->jmpbuf()->parent = from;
3940  } else {
3941  DCHECK_EQ(to->jmpbuf()->state, wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive);
3942  // TODO(388533754): This check won't hold anymore with core stack-switching.
3943  // Instead, we will need to validate all the intermediate stacks and also
3944  // check that they don't hold central stack frames.
3945  SBXCHECK_EQ(from->jmpbuf()->parent, to);
3946  }
3947  uintptr_t limit = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(to->jmpbuf()->stack_limit);
3948  stack_guard()->SetStackLimitForStackSwitching(limit);
3949  // Update the central stack info.
3950  if (to->jmpbuf()->state == wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive) {
3951  // When returning/suspending from a stack, the parent must be on
3952  // the central stack.
3953  // TODO(388533754): This assumption will not hold anymore with core
3954  // stack-switching, so we will need to revisit this.
3955  DCHECK(IsOnCentralStack(to->jmpbuf()->sp));
3956  thread_local_top()->is_on_central_stack_flag_ = true;
3957  thread_local_top()->central_stack_sp_ = to->jmpbuf()->sp;
3958  thread_local_top()->central_stack_limit_ =
3959  reinterpret_cast<Address>(to->jmpbuf()->stack_limit);
3960  } else {
3961  // A suspended stack cannot hold central stack frames.
3962  thread_local_top()->is_on_central_stack_flag_ = false;
3963  thread_local_top()->central_stack_sp_ = from->jmpbuf()->sp;
3964  thread_local_top()->central_stack_limit_ =
3965  reinterpret_cast<Address>(from->jmpbuf()->stack_limit);
3966  }
3967 }
3968 
3969 void Isolate::RetireWasmStack(wasm::StackMemory* stack) {
3970  stack->jmpbuf()->state = wasm::JumpBuffer::Retired;
3971  size_t index = stack->index();
3972  // We can only return from a stack that was still in the global list.
3973  DCHECK_LT(index, wasm_stacks().size());
3974  std::unique_ptr<wasm::StackMemory> stack_ptr =
3975  std::move(wasm_stacks()[index]);
3976  DCHECK_EQ(stack_ptr.get(), stack);
3977  if (index != wasm_stacks().size() - 1) {
3978  wasm_stacks()[index] = std::move(wasm_stacks().back());
3979  wasm_stacks()[index]->set_index(index);
3980  }
3981  wasm_stacks().pop_back();
3982  for (size_t i = 0; i < wasm_stacks().size(); ++i) {
3983  SLOW_DCHECK(wasm_stacks()[i]->index() == i);
3984  }
3985  stack_pool().Add(std::move(stack_ptr));
3986 }

3990 }

4024 class TracingAccountingAllocator : public AccountingAllocator {
4025  public:
4026  explicit TracingAccountingAllocator(Isolate* isolate)
4027  : AccountingAllocator(isolate) {}
4028  ~TracingAccountingAllocator() = default;
4029 
4030  protected:
4031  void TraceAllocateSegmentImpl(v8::internal::Segment* segment) override {
4032  base::MutexGuard lock(&mutex_);
4033  UpdateMemoryTrafficAndReportMemoryUsage(segment->total_size());
4034  }
4035 
4036  void TraceZoneCreationImpl(const Zone* zone) override {
4037  base::MutexGuard lock(&mutex_);
4038  active_zones_.insert(zone);
4039  nesting_depth_++;
4040  }
4041 
4042  void TraceZoneDestructionImpl(const Zone* zone) override {
4043  base::MutexGuard lock(&mutex_);
4044 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_PRECISE_ZONE_STATS
4045  if (v8_flags.trace_zone_type_stats) {
4046  type_stats_.MergeWith(zone->type_stats());
4047  }
4048 #endif
4049  UpdateMemoryTrafficAndReportMemoryUsage(zone->segment_bytes_allocated());
4050  active_zones_.erase(zone);
4051  nesting_depth_--;
4052 
4053 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_PRECISE_ZONE_STATS
4054  if (v8_flags.trace_zone_type_stats && active_zones_.empty()) {
4055  type_stats_.Dump();
4056  }
4057 #endif
4058  }
4059 
4060  private:
4061  void UpdateMemoryTrafficAndReportMemoryUsage(size_t memory_traffic_delta) {
4062  if (!v8_flags.trace_zone_stats &&
4063  !(TracingFlags::zone_stats.load(std::memory_order_relaxed) &
4064  v8::tracing::TracingCategoryObserver::ENABLED_BY_TRACING)) {
4065  // Don't print anything if the zone tracing was enabled only because of
4066  // v8_flags.trace_zone_type_stats.
4067  return;
4068  }
4069 
4070  memory_traffic_since_last_report_ += memory_traffic_delta;
4071  if (memory_traffic_since_last_report_ < v8_flags.zone_stats_tolerance)
4072  return;
4073  memory_traffic_since_last_report_ = 0;
4074 
4075  Dump(buffer_, true);
4076 
4077  {
4078  std::string trace_str = buffer_.str();
4079 
4080  if (v8_flags.trace_zone_stats) {
4081  PrintF(
4082  "{"
4083  "\"type\": \"v8-zone-trace\", "
4084  "\"stats\": %s"
4085  "}\n",
4086  trace_str.c_str());
4087  }
4088  if (V8_UNLIKELY(
4089  TracingFlags::zone_stats.load(std::memory_order_relaxed) &
4090  v8::tracing::TracingCategoryObserver::ENABLED_BY_TRACING)) {
4091  TRACE_EVENT_INSTANT1(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.zone_stats"),
4092  "V8.Zone_Stats", TRACE_EVENT_SCOPE_THREAD, "stats",
4093  TRACE_STR_COPY(trace_str.c_str()));
4094  }
4095  }
4096 
4097  // Clear the buffer.
4098  buffer_.str(std::string());
4099  }
4100 
4101  void Dump(std::ostringstream& out, bool dump_details) {
4102  // Note: Neither isolate nor zones are locked, so be careful with accesses
4103  // as the allocator is potentially used on a concurrent thread.
4104  double time = isolate()->time_millis_since_init();
4105  out << "{" << "\"isolate\": \"" << reinterpret_cast<void*>(isolate())
4106  << "\", " << "\"time\": " << time << ", ";
4107  size_t total_segment_bytes_allocated = 0;
4108  size_t total_zone_allocation_size = 0;
4109  size_t total_zone_freed_size = 0;
4110 
4111  if (dump_details) {
4112  // Print detailed zone stats if memory usage changes direction.
4113  out << "\"zones\": [";
4114  bool first = true;
4115  for (const Zone* zone : active_zones_) {
4116  size_t zone_segment_bytes_allocated = zone->segment_bytes_allocated();
4117  size_t zone_allocation_size = zone->allocation_size_for_tracing();
4118  size_t freed_size = zone->freed_size_for_tracing();
4119  if (first) {
4120  first = false;
4121  } else {
4122  out << ", ";
4123  }
4124  out << "{" << "\"name\": \"" << zone->name() << "\", "
4125  << "\"allocated\": " << zone_segment_bytes_allocated << ", "
4126  << "\"used\": " << zone_allocation_size << ", "
4127  << "\"freed\": " << freed_size << "}";
4128  total_segment_bytes_allocated += zone_segment_bytes_allocated;
4129  total_zone_allocation_size += zone_allocation_size;
4130  total_zone_freed_size += freed_size;
4131  }
4132  out << "], ";
4133  } else {
4134  // Just calculate total allocated/used memory values.
4135  for (const Zone* zone : active_zones_) {
4136  total_segment_bytes_allocated += zone->segment_bytes_allocated();
4137  total_zone_allocation_size += zone->allocation_size_for_tracing();
4138  total_zone_freed_size += zone->freed_size_for_tracing();
4139  }
4140  }
4141  out << "\"allocated\": " << total_segment_bytes_allocated << ", "
4142  << "\"used\": " << total_zone_allocation_size << ", "
4143  << "\"freed\": " << total_zone_freed_size << "}";
4144  }
4145 
4146  std::atomic<size_t> nesting_depth_{0};
4147 
4148  base::Mutex mutex_;
4149  std::unordered_set<const Zone*> active_zones_;
4150 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_PRECISE_ZONE_STATS
4151  TypeStats type_stats_;
4152 #endif
4153  std::ostringstream buffer_;
4154  // This value is increased on both allocations and deallocations.
4155  size_t memory_traffic_since_last_report_ = 0;
4156 };

4162 // static
4163 Isolate* Isolate::New() { return New(IsolateGroup::AcquireDefault()); }

4165 // static
4166 Isolate* Isolate::New(IsolateGroup* group) { return Allocate(group); }
4167 
4168 // static
4169 Isolate* Isolate::Allocate(IsolateGroup* group) {
4170  // v8::V8::Initialize() must be called before creating any isolates.
4171  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(V8::GetCurrentPlatform());
4172  // Allocate Isolate itself on C++ heap, ensuring page alignment.
4173  void* isolate_ptr = base::AlignedAlloc(sizeof(Isolate), kMinimumOSPageSize);
4174  // IsolateAllocator manages the virtual memory resources for the Isolate.
4175  Isolate* isolate = new (isolate_ptr) Isolate(group);
4176 
4177 #ifdef DEBUG
4178  non_disposed_isolates_++;
4179 #endif // DEBUG
4180 
4181  return isolate;
4182 }
4183 
4184 // static
4185 void Isolate::Delete(Isolate* isolate) {
4186  Deinitialize(isolate);
4187  Free(isolate);
4188 }
4189 
4190 // static
4191 void Isolate::Deinitialize(Isolate* isolate) {
4192  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate);
4193  // v8::V8::Dispose() must only be called after deleting all isolates.
4194  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(V8::GetCurrentPlatform());
4195  // Temporarily set this isolate as current so that various parts of
4196  // the isolate can access it in their destructors without having a
4197  // direct pointer. We don't use Enter/Exit here to avoid
4198  // initializing the thread data.
4199  PerIsolateThreadData* saved_data = isolate->CurrentPerIsolateThreadData();
4200  Isolate* saved_isolate = isolate->TryGetCurrent();
4201  SetIsolateThreadLocals(isolate, nullptr);
4202  isolate->set_thread_id(ThreadId::Current());
4203  isolate->heap()->SetStackStart();
4204 
4205  isolate->Deinit();
4206 
4207 #ifdef DEBUG
4208  non_disposed_isolates_--;
4209 #endif // DEBUG
4210 
4211  IsolateGroup* group = isolate->isolate_group();
4212  isolate->~Isolate();
4213  // Only release the group once all other Isolate members have been destroyed.
4214  group->Release();
4215 
4216  // Restore the previous current isolate.
4217  SetIsolateThreadLocals(saved_isolate, saved_data);
4218 }
4219 
4220 // static
4221 void Isolate::Free(Isolate* isolate) {
4222  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate);
4223  // Free the memory allocated for the Isolate.
4224  base::AlignedFree(isolate);
4225 }

4241 Isolate::Isolate(IsolateGroup* isolate_group)
4242  : isolate_data_(this, isolate_group),
4243  isolate_group_(isolate_group),
4244  id_(isolate_counter.fetch_add(1, std::memory_order_relaxed)),
4245  allocator_(new TracingAccountingAllocator(this)),
4246  traced_handles_(this),
4247  builtins_(this),
4248 #if defined(DEBUG) || defined(VERIFY_HEAP)
4249  num_active_deserializers_(0),
4250 #endif
4251  logger_(new Logger()),
4252  detailed_source_positions_for_profiling_(v8_flags.detailed_line_info),
4253  persistent_handles_list_(new PersistentHandlesList()),
4254  jitless_(v8_flags.jitless),
4255  next_unique_sfi_id_(0),
4256  next_module_async_evaluation_ordinal_(
4257  SourceTextModule::kFirstAsyncEvaluationOrdinal),
4258  cancelable_task_manager_(new CancelableTaskManager()),
4259 #if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
4260  etw_tracing_enabled_(false),
4261  etw_trace_interpreted_frames_(v8_flags.interpreted_frames_native_stack),
4262  etw_in_rundown_(false),
4263 #endif // V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING
4264  stack_size_(v8_flags.stack_size * KB) {
4265  TRACE_ISOLATE(constructor);
4266  CheckIsolateLayout();
4267 
4268  // ThreadManager is initialized early to support locking an isolate
4269  // before it is entered.
4270  thread_manager_ = new ThreadManager(this);
4271 
4272  handle_scope_data()->Initialize();
4273 
4274 #define ISOLATE_INIT_EXECUTE(type, name, initial_value) \
4275  name##_ = (initial_value);
4276  ISOLATE_INIT_LIST(ISOLATE_INIT_EXECUTE)
4277 #undef ISOLATE_INIT_EXECUTE
4278 
4279 #define ISOLATE_INIT_ARRAY_EXECUTE(type, name, length) \
4280  memset(name##_, 0, sizeof(type) * length);
4281  ISOLATE_INIT_ARRAY_LIST(ISOLATE_INIT_ARRAY_EXECUTE)
4282 #undef ISOLATE_INIT_ARRAY_EXECUTE
4283 
4284  InitializeLoggingAndCounters();
4285  debug_ = new Debug(this);
4286 
4287  InitializeDefaultEmbeddedBlob();
4288 
4289 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4290  // If we are in production V8 and not in mksnapshot we have to pass the
4291  // landing pad builtin to the WebAssembly TrapHandler.
4292  // TODO(ahaas): Isolate creation is the earliest point in time when builtins
4293  // are available, so we cannot set the landing pad earlier at the moment.
4294  // However, if builtins ever get loaded during process initialization time,
4295  // then the initialization of the trap handler landing pad should also go
4296  // there.
4297  // TODO(ahaas): The code of the landing pad does not have to be a builtin,
4298  // we could also just move it to the trap handler, and implement it e.g. with
4299  // inline assembly. It's not clear if that's worth it.
4300  if (Isolate::CurrentEmbeddedBlobCodeSize()) {
4301  Address landing_pad =
4302  Builtins::EmbeddedEntryOf(Builtin::kWasmTrapHandlerLandingPad);
4303  i::trap_handler::SetLandingPad(landing_pad);
4304  }
4305 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4306 
4307  MicrotaskQueue::SetUpDefaultMicrotaskQueue(this);
4308 }

4319  Internals::kTrustedPointerTableSize);

4325  Internals::kIsolateStackGuardOffset);

4328  Internals::kVariousBooleanFlagsOffset);

4331  Internals::kErrorMessageParamOffset);

4337  Internals::kBuiltinTier0TableOffset);

4340  Internals::kNewAllocationInfoOffset);

4343  Internals::kOldAllocationInfoOffset);

4346  Internals::kIsolateFastCCallCallerFpOffset);

4389  Internals::kIsolateSharedTrustedPointerTableAddressOffset);
4390
