4393  Internals::kIsolateCodePointerTableBaseAddressOffset);
4394 #endif
4395  static_assert(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(
4396  Isolate, isolate_data_.api_callback_thunk_argument_)) ==
4397  Internals::kIsolateApiCallbackThunkArgumentOffset);
4398  static_assert(
4399  static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(
4400  Isolate, isolate_data_.continuation_preserved_embedder_data_)) ==
4401  Internals::kContinuationPreservedEmbedderDataOffset);
4402 
4403  static_assert(static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(
4404  Isolate, isolate_data_.js_dispatch_table_base_)) ==
4405  Internals::kJSDispatchTableOffset);
4406 
4407  static_assert(
4408  static_cast<int>(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_.roots_table_)) ==
4409  Internals::kIsolateRootsOffset);
4410 
4411  CHECK(IsAligned(reinterpret_cast<Address>(&isolate_data_),
4412  kIsolateDataAlignment));
4413 
4414  static_assert(Internals::kStackGuardSize == sizeof(StackGuard));
4415  static_assert(Internals::kBuiltinTier0TableSize ==
4416  Builtins::kBuiltinTier0Count * kSystemPointerSize);
4417  static_assert(Internals::kBuiltinTier0EntryTableSize ==
4418  Builtins::kBuiltinTier0Count * kSystemPointerSize);
4419 
4420  // Ensure that certain hot IsolateData fields fall into the same CPU cache
4421  // line.
4422  constexpr size_t kCacheLineSize = 64;
4423  static_assert(OFFSET_OF(Isolate, isolate_data_) == 0);
4424 
4425  // Fields written on every CEntry/CallApiCallback/CallApiGetter call.
4426  // See MacroAssembler::EnterExitFrame/LeaveExitFrame.
4427  constexpr size_t kCEntryFPCacheLine = RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4428  OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, thread_local_top_.c_entry_fp_));
4429  static_assert(kCEntryFPCacheLine ==
4430  RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4431  OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, thread_local_top_.c_function_)));
4432  static_assert(kCEntryFPCacheLine ==
4433  RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4434  OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, thread_local_top_.context_)));
4435  static_assert(
4436  kCEntryFPCacheLine ==
4437  RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(OFFSET_OF(
4438  IsolateData, thread_local_top_.topmost_script_having_context_)));
4439  static_assert(kCEntryFPCacheLine ==
4440  RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4441  OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, thread_local_top_.last_api_entry_)));
4442 
4443  // Fields written on every MacroAssembler::CallCFunction call.
4444  static_assert(RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4445  OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, fast_c_call_caller_fp_)) ==
4446  RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(
4447  OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, fast_c_call_caller_pc_)));
4448 
4449  // LinearAllocationArea objects must not cross cache line boundary.
4450  static_assert(
4451  RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, new_allocation_info_)) ==
4452  RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, new_allocation_info_) +
4453  sizeof(LinearAllocationArea) - 1));
4454  static_assert(
4455  RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, old_allocation_info_)) ==
4456  RoundDown<kCacheLineSize>(OFFSET_OF(IsolateData, old_allocation_info_) +
4457  sizeof(LinearAllocationArea) - 1));
4458 }

4475 
4476 void Isolate::Deinit() {
4477  TRACE_ISOLATE(deinit);
4478 
4479 #if defined(V8_USE_PERFETTO)
4480  PerfettoLogger::UnregisterIsolate(this);
4481 #endif // defined(V8_USE_PERFETTO)
4482 
4483  // All client isolates should already be detached when the shared heap isolate
4484  // tears down.
4485  if (is_shared_space_isolate()) {
4486  global_safepoint()->AssertNoClientsOnTearDown();
4487  }
4488 
4489  if (has_shared_space() && !is_shared_space_isolate()) {
4490  IgnoreLocalGCRequests ignore_gc_requests(heap());
4491  main_thread_local_heap()->ExecuteMainThreadWhileParked([this]() {
4492  shared_space_isolate()->global_safepoint()->clients_mutex_.Lock();
4493  });
4494  }
4495 
4496  // We start with the heap tear down so that releasing managed objects does
4497  // not cause a GC.
4498  heap_.StartTearDown();
4499 
4500  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4501  IgnoreLocalGCRequests ignore_gc_requests(heap());
4502 
4503 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY && V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
4504  if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
4505  wasm::WasmInterpreter::NotifyIsolateDisposal(this);
4506  } else if (v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms &&
4507  v8_flags.slow_histograms) {
4508  wasm_execution_timer_->Terminate();
4509  }
4510 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY && V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
4511 
4512  tracing_cpu_profiler_.reset();
4513  if (v8_flags.stress_sampling_allocation_profiler > 0) {
4514  heap()->heap_profiler()->StopSamplingHeapProfiler();
4515  }
4516 
4517  metrics_recorder_->NotifyIsolateDisposal();
4518  recorder_context_id_map_.clear();
4519 
4520  FutexEmulation::IsolateDeinit(this);
4521  if (v8_flags.harmony_struct) {
4522  JSSynchronizationPrimitive::IsolateDeinit(this);
4523  } else {
4524  DCHECK(async_waiter_queue_nodes_.empty());
4525  }
4526 
4527  debug()->Unload();
4528 
4529 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4530  wasm::GetWasmEngine()->DeleteCompileJobsOnIsolate(this);
4531 
4532  BackingStore::RemoveSharedWasmMemoryObjects(this);
4533 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4534 
4535  if (concurrent_recompilation_enabled()) {
4536  optimizing_compile_dispatcher_->StartTearDown();
4537  }
4538 
4539  if (v8_flags.print_deopt_stress) {
4540  PrintF(stdout, "=== Stress deopt counter: %" PRIu64 "\n",
4541  stress_deopt_count_);
4542  }
4543 
4544  // We must stop the logger before we tear down other components.
4545  sampler::Sampler* sampler = v8_file_logger_->sampler();
4546  if (sampler && sampler->IsActive()) sampler->Stop();
4547  v8_file_logger_->StopProfilerThread();
4548 
4549  FreeThreadResources();
4550 
4551  // Stop concurrent tasks before destroying resources since they might still
4552  // use those.
4553  cancelable_task_manager()->CancelAndWait();
4554 
4555  // Delete any remaining RegExpResultVector instances.
4556  for (int32_t* v : active_dynamic_regexp_result_vectors_) {
4557  delete[] v;
4558  }
4559  active_dynamic_regexp_result_vectors_.clear();
4560 
4561  // Cancel all compiler tasks.
4562 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SPARKPLUG
4563  delete baseline_batch_compiler_;
4564  baseline_batch_compiler_ = nullptr;
4565 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SPARKPLUG
4566 
4567 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
4568  delete maglev_concurrent_dispatcher_;
4569  maglev_concurrent_dispatcher_ = nullptr;
4570 #endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
4571 
4572  if (lazy_compile_dispatcher_) {
4573  lazy_compile_dispatcher_->AbortAll();
4574  lazy_compile_dispatcher_.reset();
4575  }
4576 
4577  if (concurrent_recompilation_enabled()) {
4578  optimizing_compile_dispatcher_->FinishTearDown();
4579  delete optimizing_compile_dispatcher_;
4580  optimizing_compile_dispatcher_ = nullptr;
4581  }
4582 
4583  // At this point there are no more background threads left in this isolate.
4584  heap_.safepoint()->AssertMainThreadIsOnlyThread();
4585 
4586  // Tear down data that requires the shared heap before detaching.
4587  heap_.TearDownWithSharedHeap();
4588  DumpAndResetBuiltinsProfileData();
4589 
4590  // Detach from the shared heap isolate and then unlock the mutex.
4591  if (has_shared_space() && !is_shared_space_isolate()) {
4592  GlobalSafepoint* global_safepoint =
4593  this->shared_space_isolate()->global_safepoint();
4594  global_safepoint->RemoveClient(this);
4595  global_safepoint->clients_mutex_.Unlock();
4596  }
4597 
4598  shared_space_isolate_.reset();
4599 
4600  // Since there are no other threads left, we can lock this mutex without any
4601  // ceremony. This signals to the tear down code that we are in a safepoint.
4602  base::RecursiveMutexGuard safepoint(&heap_.safepoint()->local_heaps_mutex_);
4603 
4604  ReleaseSharedPtrs();
4605 
4606  builtins_.TearDown();
4607  bootstrapper_->TearDown();
4608 
4609  if (tiering_manager_ != nullptr) {
4610  delete tiering_manager_;
4611  tiering_manager_ = nullptr;
4612  }
4613 
4614 #if USE_SIMULATOR
4615  delete simulator_data_;
4616  simulator_data_ = nullptr;
4617 #endif
4618 
4619  // After all concurrent tasks are stopped, we know for sure that stats aren't
4620  // updated anymore.
4621  DumpAndResetStats();
4622 
4623  // Contains zones that should be released to the page pool before the heap is
4624  // torn down.
4625  delete ast_string_constants_;
4626  ast_string_constants_ = nullptr;
4627 
4628  heap_.TearDown();
4629  isolate_group()->RemoveIsolate(this);
4630 
4631  delete inner_pointer_to_code_cache_;
4632  inner_pointer_to_code_cache_ = nullptr;
4633 
4634  main_thread_local_isolate_.reset();
4635 
4636  FILE* logfile = v8_file_logger_->TearDownAndGetLogFile();
4637  if (logfile != nullptr) base::Fclose(logfile);
4638 
4639 #if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
4640  if (v8_flags.enable_etw_stack_walking ||
4641  v8_flags.enable_etw_by_custom_filter_only) {
4642  ETWJITInterface::RemoveIsolate(this);
4643  }
4644 #endif // defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
4645 
4646 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4647  wasm::GetWasmEngine()->RemoveIsolate(this);
4648 
4649  delete wasm_code_look_up_cache_;
4650  wasm_code_look_up_cache_ = nullptr;
4651 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4652 
4653  TearDownEmbeddedBlob();
4654 
4655  delete interpreter_;
4656  interpreter_ = nullptr;
4657 
4658  delete logger_;
4659  logger_ = nullptr;
4660 
4661  delete root_index_map_;
4662  root_index_map_ = nullptr;
4663 
4664  delete compiler_zone_;
4665  compiler_zone_ = nullptr;
4666  compiler_cache_ = nullptr;
4667 
4668  SetCodePages(nullptr);
4669 
4670  ClearSerializerData();
4671 
4672  if (OwnsStringTables()) {
4673  string_forwarding_table()->TearDown();
4674  } else {
4675  DCHECK_NULL(string_table_.get());
4676  DCHECK_NULL(string_forwarding_table_.get());
4677  }
4678 
4679  if (!is_shared_space_isolate()) {
4680  DCHECK_NULL(shared_struct_type_registry_.get());
4681  }
4682 
4683 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
4684  external_pointer_table().TearDownSpace(
4685  heap()->young_external_pointer_space());
4686  external_pointer_table().TearDownSpace(heap()->old_external_pointer_space());

4696  delete isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_;
4697  isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_ = nullptr;
4698  delete shared_external_pointer_space_;
4699  shared_external_pointer_space_ = nullptr;
4700  }

4702  cpp_heap_pointer_table().TearDown();
4703 #endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
4704 
4705 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4706  trusted_pointer_table().TearDownSpace(heap()->trusted_pointer_space());
4707  trusted_pointer_table().TearDown();
4708  if (owns_shareable_data()) {
4709  shared_trusted_pointer_table().TearDownSpace(
4710  shared_trusted_pointer_space());
4711  shared_trusted_pointer_table().TearDown();

4713  isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_ = nullptr;

4846 void Isolate::InitializeThreadLocal() {

4849  // and thus pointer compression schemes might have cage base value unset.
4850  // So, allow heap access here to let the checks work.

4855 
4856 void Isolate::SetTerminationOnExternalTryCatch() {
4857  DCHECK_IMPLIES(v8_flags.strict_termination_checks,
4858  is_execution_terminating());
4859  if (try_catch_handler() == nullptr) return;
4860  try_catch_handler()->can_continue_ = false;
4861  try_catch_handler()->exception_ = reinterpret_cast<void*>(
4862  ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).termination_exception().ptr());
4863 }
4864 
4865 bool Isolate::PropagateExceptionToExternalTryCatch(
4866  ExceptionHandlerType top_handler) {
4867  Tagged<Object> exception = this->exception();
4868 
4869  if (top_handler == ExceptionHandlerType::kJavaScriptHandler) return false;
4870  if (top_handler == ExceptionHandlerType::kNone) return true;
4871 
4872  DCHECK_EQ(ExceptionHandlerType::kExternalTryCatch, top_handler);
4873  if (!is_catchable_by_javascript(exception)) {
4874  SetTerminationOnExternalTryCatch();
4875  } else {
4876  v8::TryCatch* handler = try_catch_handler();
4877  DCHECK(IsJSMessageObject(pending_message()) ||
4878  IsTheHole(pending_message(), this));
4879  handler->can_continue_ = true;
4880  handler->exception_ = reinterpret_cast<void*>(exception.ptr());
4881  // Propagate to the external try-catch only if we got an actual message.
4882  if (!has_pending_message()) return true;
4883  handler->message_obj_ = reinterpret_cast<void*>(pending_message().ptr());
4884  }
4885  return true;
4886 }
4887 
4888 namespace {
4889 
4890 inline Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> GetTargetFunctionTemplateInfo(
4891  const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
4892  Tagged<Object> target = FunctionCallbackArguments::GetTarget(info);
4893  if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(target)) {
4894  return Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(target);
4895  }
4896  CHECK(Is<JSFunction>(target));
4897  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = Cast<JSFunction>(target)->shared();
4898  return shared_info->api_func_data();
4899 }
4900 
4901 } // namespace
4902 
4903 void Isolate::NotifyExceptionPropagationCallback() {
4904  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(exception_propagation_callback_);
4905 
4906  // Try to figure out whether the exception was thrown directly from an
4907  // Api callback and if it's the case then call the
4908  // |exception_propagation_callback_| with relevant data.
4909 
4910  ExternalCallbackScope* ext_callback_scope = external_callback_scope();
4911  StackFrameIterator it(this);
4912 
4913  if (it.done() && !ext_callback_scope) {
4914  // The exception was thrown directly by embedder code without crossing
4915  // "C++ -> JS" or "C++ -> Api callback" boundary.
4916  return;
4917  }
4918  if (it.done() ||
4919  (ext_callback_scope &&
4920  ext_callback_scope->JSStackComparableAddress() < it.frame()->fp())) {
4921  // There were no crossings of "C++ -> JS" boundary at all or they happened
4922  // earlier than the last crossing of the "C++ -> Api callback" boundary.
4923  // In this case all the data about Api callback is available in the
4924  // |ext_callback_scope| object.
4925  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(ext_callback_scope);
4926  v8::ExceptionContext kind = ext_callback_scope->exception_context();
4927  switch (kind) {
4928  case v8::ExceptionContext::kConstructor:
4929  case v8::ExceptionContext::kOperation: {
4930  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(ext_callback_scope->callback_info());
4931  auto callback_info =
4932  reinterpret_cast<const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>*>(
4933  ext_callback_scope->callback_info());
4934 
4935  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver =
4936  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*callback_info->This());
4937  DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info(
4938  GetTargetFunctionTemplateInfo(*callback_info), this);
4939  ReportExceptionFunctionCallback(receiver, function_template_info, kind);
4940  return;
4941  }
4942  case v8::ExceptionContext::kAttributeGet:
4943  case v8::ExceptionContext::kAttributeSet:
4944  case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedQuery:
4945  case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedGetter:
4946  case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedDescriptor:
4947  case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedSetter:
4948  case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedDefiner:
4949  case v8::ExceptionContext::kIndexedDeleter:
4950  case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedQuery:
4951  case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedGetter:
4952  case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedDescriptor:
4953  case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedSetter:
4954  case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedDefiner:
4955  case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedDeleter:
4956  case v8::ExceptionContext::kNamedEnumerator: {
4957  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(ext_callback_scope->callback_info());
4958  auto callback_info =
4959  reinterpret_cast<const v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<v8::Value>*>(
4960  ext_callback_scope->callback_info());
4961 
4962  // Allow usages of v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<T>::Holder() for now.
4963  // TODO(https://crbug.com/333672197): remove.
4964  START_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
4965 
4966  DirectHandle<Object> holder =
4967  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*callback_info->Holder());
4968  Handle<Object> maybe_name =
4969  PropertyCallbackArguments::GetPropertyKeyHandle(*callback_info);
4970  DirectHandle<Name> name =
4971  IsSmi(*maybe_name)
4972  ? factory()->SizeToString(
4973  PropertyCallbackArguments::GetPropertyIndex(
4974  *callback_info))
4975  : Cast<Name>(maybe_name);
4976  DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*holder));
4977 
4978  // Allow usages of v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<T>::Holder() for now.
4979  // TODO(https://crbug.com/333672197): remove.
4980  END_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
4981 
4982  // Currently we call only ApiGetters from JS code.
4983  ReportExceptionPropertyCallback(Cast<JSReceiver>(holder), name, kind);
4984  return;
4985  }
4986 
4987  case v8::ExceptionContext::kUnknown:
4988  DCHECK_WITH_MSG(kind != v8::ExceptionContext::kUnknown,
4989  "ExternalCallbackScope should not use "
4990  "v8::ExceptionContext::kUnknown exception context");
4991  return;
4992  }
4993  UNREACHABLE();
4994  }
4995 
4996  // There were no crossings of "C++ -> Api callback" boundary or they
4997  // happened before crossing the "C++ -> JS" boundary.
4998  // In this case all the data about Api callback is available in the
4999  // topmost "JS -> Api callback" frame (ApiCallbackExitFrame or
5000  // ApiAccessorExitFrame).
5001  DCHECK(!it.done());
5002  StackFrame::Type frame_type = it.frame()->type();
5003  switch (frame_type) {
5004  case StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT: {
5005  ApiCallbackExitFrame* frame = ApiCallbackExitFrame::cast(it.frame());
5006  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver(Cast<JSReceiver>(frame->receiver()),
5007  this);
5008  DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info =
5009  frame->GetFunctionTemplateInfo();
5010 
5011  v8::ExceptionContext callback_kind =
5012  frame->IsConstructor() ? v8::ExceptionContext::kConstructor
5013  : v8::ExceptionContext::kOperation;
5014  ReportExceptionFunctionCallback(receiver, function_template_info,
5015  callback_kind);
5016  return;
5017  }
5018  case StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT: {
5019  ApiAccessorExitFrame* frame = ApiAccessorExitFrame::cast(it.frame());
5020 
5021  DirectHandle<Object> holder(frame->holder(), this);
5022  DirectHandle<Name> name(frame->property_name(), this);
5023  DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*holder));
5024 
5025  // Currently we call only ApiGetters from JS code.
5026  ReportExceptionPropertyCallback(Cast<JSReceiver>(holder), name,
5027  v8::ExceptionContext::kAttributeGet);
5028  return;
5029  }
5030  case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS:
5031  // This must be a fast Api call.
5032  CHECK(it.frame()->InFastCCall());
5033  // TODO(ishell): support fast Api calls.
5034  return;
5035  case StackFrame::EXIT:
5036  case StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT:
5037  // This is a regular runtime function or C++ builtin.
5038  return;
5039 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5040  case StackFrame::WASM:
5041  case StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START:
5042  // No more info.
5043  return;
5044 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5045  default:
5046  // Other types are not expected, so just hard-crash.
5047  CHECK_NE(frame_type, frame_type);
5048  }
5049 }
5050 
5051 void Isolate::ReportExceptionFunctionCallback(
5052  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
5053  DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function,
5054  v8::ExceptionContext exception_context) {
5055  DCHECK(exception_context == v8::ExceptionContext::kConstructor ||
5056  exception_context == v8::ExceptionContext::kOperation);
5057  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(exception_propagation_callback_);
5058 
5059  // Ignore exceptions that we can't extend.
5060  if (!IsJSReceiver(this->exception())) return;
5061  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> exception(Cast<JSReceiver>(this->exception()), this);
5062 
5063  DirectHandle<Object> maybe_message(pending_message(), this);
5064 
5065  DirectHandle<String> property_name =
5066  IsUndefined(function->class_name(), this)
5067  ? factory()->empty_string()
5068  : Handle<String>(Cast<String>(function->class_name()), this);
5069  DirectHandle<String> interface_name =
5070  IsUndefined(function->interface_name(), this)
5071  ? factory()->empty_string()
5072  : Handle<String>(Cast<String>(function->interface_name()), this);
5073  if (exception_context != ExceptionContext::kConstructor) {
5074  exception_context =
5075  static_cast<ExceptionContext>(function->exception_context());
5076  }
5077 
5078  {
5079  v8::Isolate* v8_isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this);
5080  // Ignore any exceptions thrown inside the callback and rethrow the
5081  // original exception/message.
5082  TryCatch try_catch(v8_isolate);
5083 
5084  exception_propagation_callback_(v8::ExceptionPropagationMessage(
5085  v8_isolate, v8::Utils::ToLocal(exception),
5086  v8::Utils::ToLocal(interface_name), v8::Utils::ToLocal(property_name),
5087  exception_context));
5088 
5089  try_catch.Reset();
5090  }
5091  ReThrow(*exception, *maybe_message);
5092 }
5093 
5094 void Isolate::ReportExceptionPropertyCallback(
5095  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> holder, DirectHandle<Name> name,
5096  v8::ExceptionContext exception_context) {
5097  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(exception_propagation_callback_);
5098 
5099  if (!IsJSReceiver(this->exception())) return;
5100  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> exception(Cast<JSReceiver>(this->exception()), this);
5101 
5102  DirectHandle<Object> maybe_message(pending_message(), this);
5103 
5104  DirectHandle<String> property_name;
5105  std::ignore = Name::ToFunctionName(this, name).ToHandle(&property_name);
5106  DirectHandle<String> interface_name =
5107  JSReceiver::GetConstructorName(this, holder);
5108 
5109  {
5110  v8::Isolate* v8_isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this);
5111  // Ignore any exceptions thrown inside the callback and rethrow the
5112  // original exception/message.
5113  TryCatch try_catch(v8_isolate);
5114 
5115  exception_propagation_callback_(v8::ExceptionPropagationMessage(
5116  v8_isolate, v8::Utils::ToLocal(exception),
5117  v8::Utils::ToLocal(interface_name), v8::Utils::ToLocal(property_name),
5118  exception_context));
5119 
5120  try_catch.Reset();
5121  }
5122  ReThrow(*exception, *maybe_message);
5123 }
5124

5126  ExceptionPropagationCallback callback) {
5127  exception_propagation_callback_ = callback;
5128 }

5143 namespace {

5145 void FinalizeBuiltinCodeObjects(Isolate* isolate) {
5146  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate->embedded_blob_code());
5147  DCHECK_NE(0, isolate->embedded_blob_code_size());
5148  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate->embedded_blob_data());
5149  DCHECK_NE(0, isolate->embedded_blob_data_size());
5150 
5151  EmbeddedData d = EmbeddedData::FromBlob(isolate);
5152  HandleScope scope(isolate);
5153  static_assert(Builtins::kAllBuiltinsAreIsolateIndependent);
5154  for (Builtin builtin = Builtins::kFirst; builtin <= Builtins::kLast;
5155  ++builtin) {
5156  DirectHandle<Code> old_code = isolate->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
5157  // Note that `old_code.instruction_start` might point to `old_code`'s
5158  // InstructionStream which might be GCed once we replace the old code
5159  // with the new code.
5160  Address instruction_start = d.InstructionStartOf(builtin);
5161  DirectHandle<Code> new_code =
5162  isolate->factory()->NewCodeObjectForEmbeddedBuiltin(old_code,
5163  instruction_start);
5164 
5165  // From this point onwards, the old builtin code object is unreachable and
5166  // will be collected by the next GC.
5167  isolate->builtins()->set_code(builtin, *new_code);
5168  }
5169 }
5170 
5171 #ifdef DEBUG
5172 bool IsolateIsCompatibleWithEmbeddedBlob(Isolate* isolate) {
5173  EmbeddedData d = EmbeddedData::FromBlob(isolate);
5174  return (d.IsolateHash() == isolate->HashIsolateForEmbeddedBlob());
5175 }
5176 #endif // DEBUG
5177 
5178 } // namespace

5180 void Isolate::InitializeDefaultEmbeddedBlob() {
5181  const uint8_t* code = DefaultEmbeddedBlobCode();
5182  uint32_t code_size = DefaultEmbeddedBlobCodeSize();
5183  const uint8_t* data = DefaultEmbeddedBlobData();
5184  uint32_t data_size = DefaultEmbeddedBlobDataSize();
5185 
5186  if (StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() != nullptr) {
5187  base::MutexGuard guard(current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_.Pointer());
5188  // Check again now that we hold the lock.
5189  if (StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() != nullptr) {
5190  code = StickyEmbeddedBlobCode();
5191  code_size = StickyEmbeddedBlobCodeSize();
5192  data = StickyEmbeddedBlobData();
5193  data_size = StickyEmbeddedBlobDataSize();
5194  current_embedded_blob_refs_++;
5195  }
5196  }
5197 
5198  if (code_size == 0) {
5199  CHECK_EQ(0, data_size);
5200  } else {
5201  SetEmbeddedBlob(code, code_size, data, data_size);
5202  }
5203 }
5204 
5205 void Isolate::CreateAndSetEmbeddedBlob() {
5206  base::MutexGuard guard(current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_.Pointer());
5207 
5208  PrepareBuiltinSourcePositionMap();
5209 
5210  // If a sticky blob has been set, we reuse it.
5211  if (StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() != nullptr) {
5212  CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_code(), StickyEmbeddedBlobCode());
5213  CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_data(), StickyEmbeddedBlobData());
5214  CHECK_EQ(CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode(), StickyEmbeddedBlobCode());
5215  CHECK_EQ(CurrentEmbeddedBlobData(), StickyEmbeddedBlobData());
5216  } else {
5217  // Create and set a new embedded blob.
5218  uint8_t* code;
5219  uint32_t code_size;
5220  uint8_t* data;
5221  uint32_t data_size;
5222  OffHeapInstructionStream::CreateOffHeapOffHeapInstructionStream(
5223  this, &code, &code_size, &data, &data_size);
5224 
5225  CHECK_EQ(0, current_embedded_blob_refs_);
5226  const uint8_t* const_code = const_cast<const uint8_t*>(code);
5227  const uint8_t* const_data = const_cast<const uint8_t*>(data);
5228  SetEmbeddedBlob(const_code, code_size, const_data, data_size);
5229  current_embedded_blob_refs_++;
5230 
5231  SetStickyEmbeddedBlob(code, code_size, data, data_size);
5232  }
5233 
5234  MaybeRemapEmbeddedBuiltinsIntoCodeRange();
5235  FinalizeBuiltinCodeObjects(this);
5236 }
5237 
5238 void Isolate::InitializeIsShortBuiltinCallsEnabled() {
5239  if (V8_SHORT_BUILTIN_CALLS_BOOL && v8_flags.short_builtin_calls) {
5240 #if defined(V8_OS_ANDROID)
5241  // On Android, the check is not operative to detect memory, and re-embedded
5242  // builtins don't have a memory cost.
5243  is_short_builtin_calls_enabled_ = true;
5244 #else
5245  // Check if the system has more than 4GB of physical memory by comparing the
5246  // old space size with respective threshold value.
5247  is_short_builtin_calls_enabled_ = (heap_.MaxOldGenerationSize() >=
5248  kShortBuiltinCallsOldSpaceSizeThreshold);
5249 #endif // defined(V8_OS_ANDROID)
5250  // Additionally, enable if there is already a process-wide CodeRange that
5251  // has re-embedded builtins.
5252  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
5253  CodeRange* code_range = isolate_group()->GetCodeRange();
5254  if (code_range && code_range->embedded_blob_code_copy() != nullptr) {
5255  is_short_builtin_calls_enabled_ = true;
5256  }
5257  }
5258  if (V8_ENABLE_NEAR_CODE_RANGE_BOOL) {
5259  // The short builtin calls could still be enabled if allocated code range
5260  // is close enough to embedded builtins so that the latter could be
5261  // reached using pc-relative (short) calls/jumps.
5262  is_short_builtin_calls_enabled_ |=
5263  GetShortBuiltinsCallRegion().contains(heap_.code_region());
5264  }
5265  }
5266 }
5267 
5268 void Isolate::MaybeRemapEmbeddedBuiltinsIntoCodeRange() {
5269  if (!is_short_builtin_calls_enabled() || !RequiresCodeRange()) {
5270  return;
5271  }
5272  if (V8_ENABLE_NEAR_CODE_RANGE_BOOL &&
5273  GetShortBuiltinsCallRegion().contains(heap_.code_region())) {
5274  // The embedded builtins are within the pc-relative reach from the code
5275  // range, so there's no need to remap embedded builtins.
5276  return;
5277  }
5278 
5279  CHECK_NOT_NULL(embedded_blob_code_);
5280  CHECK_NE(embedded_blob_code_size_, 0);
5281 
5282  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(heap_.code_range_);
5283  embedded_blob_code_ = heap_.code_range_->RemapEmbeddedBuiltins(
5284  this, embedded_blob_code_, embedded_blob_code_size_);
5285  CHECK_NOT_NULL(embedded_blob_code_);
5286  // The un-embedded code blob is already a part of the registered code range
5287  // so it's not necessary to register it again.
5288 }
5289 
5290 void Isolate::TearDownEmbeddedBlob() {
5291  // Nothing to do in case the blob is embedded into the binary or unset.
5292  if (StickyEmbeddedBlobCode() == nullptr) return;
5293 
5294  if (!is_short_builtin_calls_enabled()) {
5295  CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_code(), StickyEmbeddedBlobCode());
5296  CHECK_EQ(embedded_blob_data(), StickyEmbeddedBlobData());
5297  }
5298  CHECK_EQ(CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode(), StickyEmbeddedBlobCode());
5299  CHECK_EQ(CurrentEmbeddedBlobData(), StickyEmbeddedBlobData());
5300 
5301  base::MutexGuard guard(current_embedded_blob_refcount_mutex_.Pointer());
5302  current_embedded_blob_refs_--;
5303  if (current_embedded_blob_refs_ == 0 && enable_embedded_blob_refcounting_) {
5304  // We own the embedded blob and are the last holder. Free it.
5305  OffHeapInstructionStream::FreeOffHeapOffHeapInstructionStream(
5306  const_cast<uint8_t*>(CurrentEmbeddedBlobCode()),
5307  embedded_blob_code_size(),
5308  const_cast<uint8_t*>(CurrentEmbeddedBlobData()),
5309  embedded_blob_data_size());
5310  ClearEmbeddedBlob();
5311  }
5312 }

5330 static std::string ToHexString(uintptr_t address) {
5331  std::stringstream stream_address;
5332  stream_address << "0x" << std::hex << address;
5333  return stream_address.str();
5334 }

5337 void Isolate::AddCrashKeysForIsolateAndHeapPointers() {
5338  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(add_crash_key_callback_);
5339 
5340  const uintptr_t isolate_address = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(this);
5341  add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kIsolateAddress,
5342  ToHexString(isolate_address));
5343 
5344  const uintptr_t ro_space_firstpage_address =
5345  heap()->read_only_space()->FirstPageAddress();
5346  add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kReadonlySpaceFirstPageAddress,
5347  ToHexString(ro_space_firstpage_address));
5348 
5349  const uintptr_t old_space_firstpage_address =
5350  heap()->old_space()->FirstPageAddress();
5351  add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kOldSpaceFirstPageAddress,
5352  ToHexString(old_space_firstpage_address));
5353 
5354  if (heap()->code_range_base()) {
5355  const uintptr_t code_range_base_address = heap()->code_range_base();
5356  add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kCodeRangeBaseAddress,
5357  ToHexString(code_range_base_address));
5358  }
5359 
5360  if (heap()->code_space()->first_page()) {
5361  const uintptr_t code_space_firstpage_address =
5362  heap()->code_space()->FirstPageAddress();
5363  add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kCodeSpaceFirstPageAddress,
5364  ToHexString(code_space_firstpage_address));
5365  }
5366  const v8::StartupData* data = Snapshot::DefaultSnapshotBlob();
5367  // TODO(cbruni): Implement strategy to infrequently collect this.
5368  const uint32_t v8_snapshot_checksum_calculated = 0;
5369  add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kSnapshotChecksumCalculated,
5370  ToHexString(v8_snapshot_checksum_calculated));
5371  const uint32_t v8_snapshot_checksum_expected =
5372  Snapshot::GetExpectedChecksum(data);
5373  add_crash_key_callback_(v8::CrashKeyId::kSnapshotChecksumExpected,
5374  ToHexString(v8_snapshot_checksum_expected));
5375 }

5418 void Isolate::VerifyStaticRoots() {
5419 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
5420 #define STATIC_ROOTS_FAILED_MSG \
5421  "Read-only heap layout changed. Run `tools/dev/gen-static-roots.py` to " \
5422  "update static-roots.h."
5423  static_assert(static_cast<int>(RootIndex::kReadOnlyRootsCount) ==
5424  StaticReadOnlyRootsPointerTable.size(),
5425  STATIC_ROOTS_FAILED_MSG);
5426  auto& roots = roots_table();
5427  RootIndex idx = RootIndex::kFirstReadOnlyRoot;
5428  for (Tagged_t cmp_ptr : StaticReadOnlyRootsPointerTable) {
5429  Address the_root = roots[idx];
5430  Address ptr = V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(cmp_ptr);
5431  CHECK_WITH_MSG(the_root == ptr, STATIC_ROOTS_FAILED_MSG);
5432  ++idx;
5433  }
5434 
5435  idx = RootIndex::kFirstReadOnlyRoot;
5436 #define CHECK_NAME(_1, _2, CamelName) \
5437  CHECK_WITH_MSG(StaticReadOnlyRoot::k##CamelName == \
5438  V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(roots[idx]), \
5439  STATIC_ROOTS_FAILED_MSG); \
5440  ++idx;
5441  STRONG_READ_ONLY_ROOT_LIST(CHECK_NAME)
5442 #undef CHECK_NAME
5443 
5444  // Check if instance types to map range mappings are still valid.
5445  //
5446  // Is##type(map) may be computed by checking if the map pointer lies in a
5447  // statically known range of addresses, whereas Is##type(instance_type) is the
5448  // definitive source of truth. If they disagree it means that a particular
5449  // entry in InstanceTypeChecker::kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRangeList is out
5450  // of date. This can also happen if an instance type is starting to be used by
5451  // more maps.
5452  //
5453  // If this check fails either re-arrange allocations in the read-only heap
5454  // such that the static map range is restored (consult static-roots.h for a
5455  // sorted list of addresses) or remove the offending entry from the list.
5456  for (idx = RootIndex::kFirstRoot; idx <= RootIndex::kLastRoot; ++idx) {
5457  Tagged<Object> obj = roots_table().slot(idx).load(this);
5458  if (obj.ptr() == kNullAddress || !IsMap(obj)) continue;
5459  Tagged<Map> map = Cast<Map>(obj);
5460 
5461 #define INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_SINGLE(type, _) \
5462  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::Is##type(map), \
5463  InstanceTypeChecker::Is##type(map->instance_type()));
5464  INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKERS_SINGLE(INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_SINGLE)
5465 #undef INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_SINGLE
5466 
5467 #define INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE(type, _1, _2) \
5468  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::Is##type(map), \
5469  InstanceTypeChecker::Is##type(map->instance_type()));
5470  INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKERS_RANGE(INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE)
5471 #undef INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE
5472 
5473  // This limit is used in various places as a fast IsJSReceiver check.
5474  CHECK_IMPLIES(
5475  InstanceTypeChecker::IsPrimitiveHeapObject(map->instance_type()),
5476  V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(map.ptr()) <
5477  InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit);
5478  CHECK_IMPLIES(InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(map->instance_type()),
5479  V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(map.ptr()) >=
5480  InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit);
5481  CHECK(InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit <
5482  read_only_heap()->read_only_space()->Size());
5483 
5484  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(map->instance_type())) {
5485  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(map),
5486  InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(map->instance_type()));
5487  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsSeqString(map),
5488  InstanceTypeChecker::IsSeqString(map->instance_type()));
5489  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsExternalString(map),
5490  InstanceTypeChecker::IsExternalString(map->instance_type()));
5491  CHECK_EQ(
5492  InstanceTypeChecker::IsUncachedExternalString(map),
5493  InstanceTypeChecker::IsUncachedExternalString(map->instance_type()));
5494  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsInternalizedString(map),
5495  InstanceTypeChecker::IsInternalizedString(map->instance_type()));
5496  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsConsString(map),
5497  InstanceTypeChecker::IsConsString(map->instance_type()));
5498  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsSlicedString(map),
5499  InstanceTypeChecker::IsSlicedString(map->instance_type()));
5500  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsThinString(map),
5501  InstanceTypeChecker::IsThinString(map->instance_type()));
5502  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsOneByteString(map),
5503  InstanceTypeChecker::IsOneByteString(map->instance_type()));
5504  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsTwoByteString(map),
5505  InstanceTypeChecker::IsTwoByteString(map->instance_type()));
5506  CHECK_EQ(InstanceTypeChecker::IsSharedString(map),
5507  InstanceTypeChecker::IsSharedString(map->instance_type()));
5508  }
5509  }
5510 
5511  // Sanity check the API
5512  CHECK_EQ(
5513  v8::internal::Internals::GetRoot(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this),
5514  static_cast<int>(RootIndex::kNullValue)),
5515  ReadOnlyRoots(this).null_value().ptr());
5516 #undef STATIC_ROOTS_FAILED_MSG
5517 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
5518 }
5519 
5520 bool Isolate::Init(SnapshotData* startup_snapshot_data,
5521  SnapshotData* read_only_snapshot_data,
5522  SnapshotData* shared_heap_snapshot_data, bool can_rehash) {
5523  TRACE_ISOLATE(init);
5524 
5525 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_SHARED_CAGE
5526  CHECK_EQ(V8HeapCompressionScheme::base(), cage_base());
5527 #endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_SHARED_CAGE
5528 
5529  const bool create_heap_objects = (shared_heap_snapshot_data == nullptr);
5530  // We either have both or none.
5531  DCHECK_EQ(create_heap_objects, startup_snapshot_data == nullptr);
5532  DCHECK_EQ(create_heap_objects, read_only_snapshot_data == nullptr);
5533 
5534  EnableRoAllocationForSnapshotScope enable_ro_allocation(this);
5535 
5536  base::ElapsedTimer timer;
5537  if (create_heap_objects && v8_flags.profile_deserialization) timer.Start();
5538 
5539  time_millis_at_init_ = heap_.MonotonicallyIncreasingTimeInMs();
5540 
5541  task_runner_ = V8::GetCurrentPlatform()->GetForegroundTaskRunner(
5542  reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this));
5543 
5544  isolate_group()->AddIsolate(this);
5545  Isolate* const use_shared_space_isolate =
5546  isolate_group()->shared_space_isolate();
5547 
5548  CHECK_IMPLIES(is_shared_space_isolate_, V8_CAN_CREATE_SHARED_HEAP_BOOL);
5549 
5550  stress_deopt_count_ = v8_flags.deopt_every_n_times;
5551  force_slow_path_ = v8_flags.force_slow_path;
5552 
5553  flush_denormals_ = base::FPU::GetFlushDenormals();
5554 
5555  has_fatal_error_ = false;
5556 
5557  // The initialization process does not handle memory exhaustion.
5558  AlwaysAllocateScope always_allocate(heap());
5559 
5560 #define ASSIGN_ELEMENT(CamelName, hacker_name) \
5561  isolate_addresses_[IsolateAddressId::k##CamelName##Address] = \
5562  reinterpret_cast<Address>(hacker_name##_address());
5563  FOR_EACH_ISOLATE_ADDRESS_NAME(ASSIGN_ELEMENT)
5564 #undef ASSIGN_ELEMENT
5565 
5566  // We need to initialize code_pages_ before any on-heap code is allocated to
5567  // make sure we record all code allocations.
5568  InitializeCodeRanges();
5569 
5570  compilation_cache_ = new CompilationCache(this);
5571  descriptor_lookup_cache_ = new DescriptorLookupCache();
5572  global_handles_ = new GlobalHandles(this);
5573  eternal_handles_ = new EternalHandles();
5574  bootstrapper_ = new Bootstrapper(this);
5575  handle_scope_implementer_ = new HandleScopeImplementer(this);
5576  load_stub_cache_ = new StubCache(this);
5577  store_stub_cache_ = new StubCache(this);
5578  define_own_stub_cache_ = new StubCache(this);
5579  materialized_object_store_ = new MaterializedObjectStore(this);
5580  regexp_stack_ = new RegExpStack();
5581  isolate_data()->set_regexp_static_result_offsets_vector(
5582  jsregexp_static_offsets_vector());
5583  date_cache_ = new DateCache();
5584  interpreter_ = new interpreter::Interpreter(this);
5585  bigint_processor_ = bigint::Processor::New(new BigIntPlatform(this));
5586 
5587  if (is_shared_space_isolate_) {
5588  global_safepoint_ = std::make_unique<GlobalSafepoint>(this);
5589  }
5590 
5591  if (v8_flags.lazy_compile_dispatcher) {
5592  lazy_compile_dispatcher_ = std::make_unique<LazyCompileDispatcher>(
5593  this, V8::GetCurrentPlatform(), v8_flags.stack_size);
5594  }
5595 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SPARKPLUG
5596  baseline_batch_compiler_ = new baseline::BaselineBatchCompiler(this);
5597 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SPARKPLUG
5598 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
5599  maglev_concurrent_dispatcher_ = new maglev::MaglevConcurrentDispatcher(this);
5600 #endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
5601 
5602 #if USE_SIMULATOR
5603  simulator_data_ = new SimulatorData;
5604 #endif
5605 
5606  // Enable logging before setting up the heap
5607  v8_file_logger_->SetUp(this);
5608 
5609  metrics_recorder_ = std::make_shared<metrics::Recorder>();
5610 
5611  {
5612  // Ensure that the thread has a valid stack guard. The v8::Locker object
5613  // will ensure this too, but we don't have to use lockers if we are only
5614  // using one thread.
5615  ExecutionAccess lock(this);
5616  stack_guard()->InitThread(lock);
5617  }
5618 
5619  // Create LocalIsolate/LocalHeap for the main thread and set state to Running.
5620  main_thread_local_isolate_.reset(new LocalIsolate(this, ThreadKind::kMain));
5621 
5622  {
5623  IgnoreLocalGCRequests ignore_gc_requests(heap());
5624  main_thread_local_heap()->Unpark();
5625  }
5626 
5627  // Requires a LocalHeap to be set up to register a GC epilogue callback.
5628  inner_pointer_to_code_cache_ = new InnerPointerToCodeCache(this);
5629 
5630 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5631  wasm_code_look_up_cache_ = new wasm::WasmCodeLookupCache;
5632 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5633 
5634  // Lock clients_mutex_ in order to prevent shared GCs from other clients
5635  // during deserialization.
5636  std::optional<base::RecursiveMutexGuard> clients_guard;
5637 
5638  if (use_shared_space_isolate && !is_shared_space_isolate()) {
5639  clients_guard.emplace(
5640  &use_shared_space_isolate->global_safepoint()->clients_mutex_);
5641  use_shared_space_isolate->global_safepoint()->AppendClient(this);
5642  }
5643 
5644  shared_space_isolate_ = use_shared_space_isolate;
5645 
5646  isolate_data_.is_shared_space_isolate_flag_ = is_shared_space_isolate();
5647  isolate_data_.uses_shared_heap_flag_ = has_shared_space();
5648 
5649  if (use_shared_space_isolate && !is_shared_space_isolate() &&
5650  use_shared_space_isolate->heap()
5651  ->incremental_marking()
5652  ->IsMajorMarking()) {
5653  heap_.SetIsMarkingFlag(true);
5654  }
5655 
5656  // Set up the object heap.
5657  DCHECK(!heap_.HasBeenSetUp());
5658  heap_.SetUp(main_thread_local_heap());
5659  InitializeIsShortBuiltinCallsEnabled();
5660  if (!create_heap_objects) {
5661  // Must be done before deserializing RO space, since RO space may contain
5662  // builtin Code objects which point into the (potentially remapped)
5663  // embedded blob.
5664  MaybeRemapEmbeddedBuiltinsIntoCodeRange();
5665  }
5666  {
5667  // Must be done before deserializing RO space since the deserialization
5668  // process refers to these data structures.
5669  isolate_data_.external_reference_table()->InitIsolateIndependent(
5670  isolate_group()->external_ref_table());
5671 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5672  external_pointer_table().Initialize();
5673  external_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5674  heap()->read_only_external_pointer_space());
5675  external_pointer_table().AttachSpaceToReadOnlySegments(
5676  heap()->read_only_external_pointer_space());
5677  external_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5678  heap()->young_external_pointer_space());
5679  external_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5680  heap()->old_external_pointer_space());
5681  cpp_heap_pointer_table().Initialize();
5682  cpp_heap_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(heap()->cpp_heap_pointer_space());
5683 #endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5684 
5685 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5686  trusted_pointer_table().Initialize();
5687  trusted_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(heap()->trusted_pointer_space());
5688 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5689  }
5690  isolate_group()->SetupReadOnlyHeap(this, read_only_snapshot_data, can_rehash);
5691  heap_.SetUpSpaces(isolate_data_.new_allocation_info_,
5692  isolate_data_.old_allocation_info_);
5693 
5694  DCHECK_EQ(this, Isolate::Current());
5695  PerIsolateThreadData* const current_data = CurrentPerIsolateThreadData();
5696  DCHECK_EQ(current_data->isolate(), this);
5697  SetIsolateThreadLocals(this, current_data);
5698 
5699  if (OwnsStringTables()) {
5700  string_table_ = std::make_unique<StringTable>(this);
5701  string_forwarding_table_ = std::make_unique<StringForwardingTable>(this);
5702  } else {
5703  // Only refer to shared string table after attaching to the shared isolate.
5704  DCHECK(has_shared_space());
5705  DCHECK(!is_shared_space_isolate());
5706  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(string_table());
5707  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(string_forwarding_table());
5708  }
5709 
5710 #ifdef V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
5711  {
5712  VirtualMemoryCage* code_cage;
5713  if (heap_.code_range()) {
5714  code_cage = heap_.code_range();
5715  } else {
5716  CHECK(jitless_);
5717  // In jitless mode the code space pages will be allocated in the main
5718  // pointer compression cage.
5719  code_cage = isolate_group_->GetPtrComprCage();
5720  }
5721  code_cage_base_ = ExternalCodeCompressionScheme::PrepareCageBaseAddress(
5722  code_cage->base());
5723  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_MULTIPLE_CAGES_BOOL) {
5724  // .. now that it's available, initialize the thread-local base.
5725  ExternalCodeCompressionScheme::InitBase(code_cage_base_);
5726  }
5727  CHECK_EQ(ExternalCodeCompressionScheme::base(), code_cage_base_);
5728 
5729  // Ensure that ExternalCodeCompressionScheme is applicable to all objects
5730  // stored in the code cage.
5731  using ComprScheme = ExternalCodeCompressionScheme;
5732  Address base = code_cage->base() + kHeapObjectTag;
5733  Address last = base + code_cage->size() - kTaggedSize;
5734  Address upper_bound = base + kPtrComprCageReservationSize - kTaggedSize;
5735  PtrComprCageBase code_cage_base{code_cage_base_};
5736  CHECK_EQ(base,
5737  ComprScheme::DecompressTagged(ComprScheme::CompressAny(base)));
5738  CHECK_EQ(last,
5739  ComprScheme::DecompressTagged(ComprScheme::CompressAny(last)));
5740  CHECK_EQ(upper_bound, ComprScheme::DecompressTagged(
5741  ComprScheme::CompressAny(upper_bound)));
5742  }
5743 #endif // V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
5744 
5745  isolate_data_.external_reference_table()->Init(this);
5746 
5747 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5748  if (owns_shareable_data()) {
5749  isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_ = new ExternalPointerTable();
5750  shared_external_pointer_space_ = new ExternalPointerTable::Space();
5751  shared_external_pointer_table().Initialize();
5752  shared_external_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5753  shared_external_pointer_space());
5754  } else {
5755  DCHECK(has_shared_space());
5756  isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_ =
5757  shared_space_isolate()->isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_;
5758  shared_external_pointer_space_ =
5759  shared_space_isolate()->shared_external_pointer_space_;
5760  }
5761 #endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5762 
5763 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5764  IsolateGroup::current()->code_pointer_table()->InitializeSpace(
5765  heap()->code_pointer_space());
5766  if (owns_shareable_data()) {
5767  isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_ = new TrustedPointerTable();
5768  shared_trusted_pointer_space_ = new TrustedPointerTable::Space();
5769  shared_trusted_pointer_table().Initialize();
5770  shared_trusted_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5771  shared_trusted_pointer_space());
5772  } else {
5773  DCHECK(has_shared_space());
5774  isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_ =
5775  shared_space_isolate()->isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_;
5776  shared_trusted_pointer_space_ =
5777  shared_space_isolate()->shared_trusted_pointer_space_;
5778  }
5779 
5780 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5781 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5782  IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->InitializeSpace(
5783  heap()->js_dispatch_table_space());
5784 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5785 
5786 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5787  wasm::GetWasmEngine()->AddIsolate(this);
5788 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5789 
5790 #if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
5791  if (v8_flags.enable_etw_stack_walking ||
5792  v8_flags.enable_etw_by_custom_filter_only) {
5793  ETWJITInterface::AddIsolate(this);
5794  }
5795 #endif // defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
5796 
5797  if (setup_delegate_ == nullptr) {
5798  setup_delegate_ = new SetupIsolateDelegate;
5799  }
5800 
5801  if (!v8_flags.inline_new) heap_.DisableInlineAllocation();
5802 
5803  if (!setup_delegate_->SetupHeap(this, create_heap_objects)) {
5804  V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(this, "heap object creation");
5805  }
5806 
5807  if (create_heap_objects) {
5808  // Terminate the startup and shared heap object caches so we can iterate.
5809  startup_object_cache_.push_back(ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
5810  shared_heap_object_cache_.push_back(ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
5811  }
5812 
5813  InitializeThreadLocal();
5814 
5815  // Profiler has to be created after ThreadLocal is initialized
5816  // because it makes use of interrupts.
5817  tracing_cpu_profiler_.reset(new TracingCpuProfilerImpl(this));
5818 
5819  bootstrapper_->Initialize(create_heap_objects);
5820 
5821  if (create_heap_objects) {
5822  builtins_constants_table_builder_ = new BuiltinsConstantsTableBuilder(this);
5823 
5824  if (v8_flags.concurrent_builtin_generation) {
5825  optimizing_compile_dispatcher_ = new OptimizingCompileDispatcher(
5826  this, isolate_group_->optimizing_compile_task_executor());
5827  optimizing_compile_dispatcher_->set_finalize(false);
5828  }
5829 
5830  setup_delegate_->SetupBuiltins(this, true);
5831 
5832  if (v8_flags.concurrent_builtin_generation) {
5833  delete optimizing_compile_dispatcher_;
5834  optimizing_compile_dispatcher_ = nullptr;
5835  }
5836 
5837  builtins_constants_table_builder_->Finalize();
5838  delete builtins_constants_table_builder_;
5839  builtins_constants_table_builder_ = nullptr;
5840 
5841  CreateAndSetEmbeddedBlob();
5842  } else {
5843  setup_delegate_->SetupBuiltins(this, false);
5844  }
5845 
5846  // Initialize custom memcopy and memmove functions (must happen after
5847  // embedded blob setup).
5848  init_memcopy_functions();
5849 
5850  if ((v8_flags.trace_turbo || v8_flags.trace_turbo_graph ||
5851  v8_flags.turbo_profiling) &&
5852  !v8_flags.concurrent_turbo_tracing) {
5853  PrintF("Concurrent recompilation has been disabled for tracing.\n");
5854  } else if (OptimizingCompileDispatcher::Enabled()) {
5855  optimizing_compile_dispatcher_ = new OptimizingCompileDispatcher(
5856  this, isolate_group_->optimizing_compile_task_executor());
5857  }
5858 
5859  // Initialize before deserialization since collections may occur,
5860  // clearing/updating ICs (and thus affecting tiering decisions).
5861  tiering_manager_ = new TieringManager(this);
5862 
5863  if (!create_heap_objects) {
5864  // If we are deserializing, read the state into the now-empty heap.
5865  SharedHeapDeserializer shared_heap_deserializer(
5866  this, shared_heap_snapshot_data, can_rehash);
5867  shared_heap_deserializer.DeserializeIntoIsolate();
5868 
5869  StartupDeserializer startup_deserializer(this, startup_snapshot_data,
5870  can_rehash);
5871  startup_deserializer.DeserializeIntoIsolate();
5872  }
5873  InitializeBuiltinJSDispatchTable();
5874  if (DEBUG_BOOL) VerifyStaticRoots();
5875  load_stub_cache_->Initialize();
5876  store_stub_cache_->Initialize();
5877  define_own_stub_cache_->Initialize();
5878  interpreter_->Initialize();
5879  heap_.NotifyDeserializationComplete();
5880 
5881  delete setup_delegate_;
5882  setup_delegate_ = nullptr;
5883 
5884  Builtins::InitializeIsolateDataTables(this);
5885 
5886  // Extra steps in the logger after the heap has been set up.
5887  v8_file_logger_->LateSetup(this);
5888 
5889 #ifdef DEBUG
5890  // Verify that the current heap state (usually deserialized from the snapshot)
5891  // is compatible with the embedded blob. If this DCHECK fails, we've likely
5892  // loaded a snapshot generated by a different V8 version or build-time
5893  // configuration.
5894  if (!IsolateIsCompatibleWithEmbeddedBlob(this)) {
5895  FATAL(
5896  "The Isolate is incompatible with the embedded blob. This is usually "
5897  "caused by incorrect usage of mksnapshot. When generating custom "
5898  "snapshots, embedders must ensure they pass the same flags as during "
5899  "the V8 build process (e.g.: --turbo-instruction-scheduling).");
5900  }
5901 #endif // DEBUG
5902 
5903  if (v8_flags.print_builtin_code) builtins()->PrintBuiltinCode();
5904  if (v8_flags.print_builtin_size) builtins()->PrintBuiltinSize();
5905 
5906  // Finish initialization of ThreadLocal after deserialization is done.
5907  clear_exception();
5908  clear_pending_message();
5909 
5910  // Quiet the heap NaN if needed on target platform.
5911  if (!create_heap_objects)
5912  Assembler::QuietNaN(ReadOnlyRoots(this).nan_value());
5913 
5914  if (v8_flags.trace_turbo) {
5915  // Create an empty file.
5916  std::ofstream(GetTurboCfgFileName(this).c_str(), std::ios_base::trunc);
5917  }
5918 
5919  isolate_data_.continuation_preserved_embedder_data_ =
5920  *factory()->undefined_value();
5921 
5922  {
5923  HandleScope scope(this);
5924  ast_string_constants_ = new AstStringConstants(this, HashSeed(this));
5925  }
5926 
5927  initialized_from_snapshot_ = !create_heap_objects;
5928 
5929  if (v8_flags.stress_sampling_allocation_profiler > 0) {
5930  uint64_t sample_interval = v8_flags.stress_sampling_allocation_profiler;
5931  int stack_depth = 128;
5932  v8::HeapProfiler::SamplingFlags sampling_flags =
5933  v8::HeapProfiler::SamplingFlags::kSamplingForceGC;
5934  heap()->heap_profiler()->StartSamplingHeapProfiler(
5935  sample_interval, stack_depth, sampling_flags);
5936  }
5937 
5938  if (create_heap_objects && v8_flags.profile_deserialization) {
5939  double ms = timer.Elapsed().InMillisecondsF();
5940  PrintF("[Initializing isolate from scratch took %0.3f ms]\n", ms);
5941  }
5942 
5943  if (initialized_from_snapshot_) {
5944  SLOW_DCHECK(SharedFunctionInfo::UniqueIdsAreUnique(this));
5945  }
5946 
5947  if (v8_flags.harmony_struct) {
5948  // Initialize or get the struct type registry shared by all isolates.
5949  if (is_shared_space_isolate()) {
5950  shared_struct_type_registry_ =
5951  std::make_unique<SharedStructTypeRegistry>();
5952  } else {
5953  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(shared_struct_type_registry());
5954  }
5955  }
5956 
5957 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5958 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
5959  // Protect the payload of wasm null.
5960  if (!page_allocator()->DecommitPages(
5961  reinterpret_cast<void*>(factory()->wasm_null()->payload()),
5962  WasmNull::kSize - kTaggedSize)) {
5963  V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(this, "decommitting WasmNull payload");
5964  }
5965 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
5966 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5967 
5968  // Isolate initialization allocates long living objects that should be
5969  // pretenured to old space.
5970  DCHECK_IMPLIES(heap()->new_space(), heap()->new_space()->Size() == 0);
5971  DCHECK_IMPLIES(heap()->new_lo_space(), heap()->new_lo_space()->Size() == 0);
5972  DCHECK_EQ(heap()->gc_count(), 0);
5973 
5974 #if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
5975  if (v8_flags.enable_etw_stack_walking ||
5976  v8_flags.enable_etw_by_custom_filter_only) {
5977  ETWJITInterface::MaybeSetHandlerNow(this);
5978  }
5979 #endif // defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
5980 
5981 #if defined(V8_USE_PERFETTO)
5982  PerfettoLogger::RegisterIsolate(this);
5983 #endif // defined(V8_USE_PERFETTO)
5984 
5985  initialized_ = true;
5986 
5987  return true;
5988 }
5989 
5990 void Isolate::Enter() {
5991  Isolate* current_isolate = nullptr;
5992  PerIsolateThreadData* current_data = CurrentPerIsolateThreadData();
5993 
5994 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
5995  // No different thread must have entered the isolate. Allow re-entering.
5996  ThreadId thread_id = ThreadId::Current();
5997  if (current_thread_id_.IsValid()) {
5998  CHECK_EQ(current_thread_id_, thread_id);
5999  } else {
6000  CHECK_EQ(0, current_thread_counter_);
6001  current_thread_id_ = thread_id;
6002  }
6003  current_thread_counter_++;
6004 #endif
6005 
6006  // Set the stack start for the main thread that enters the isolate.
6007  heap()->SetStackStart();
6008 
6009  if (current_data != nullptr) {
6010  current_isolate = current_data->isolate_;
6011  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_isolate);
6012  if (current_isolate == this) {
6013  DCHECK(Current() == this);
6014  auto entry_stack = entry_stack_.load();
6015  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(entry_stack);
6016  DCHECK(entry_stack->previous_thread_data == nullptr ||
6017  entry_stack->previous_thread_data->thread_id() ==
6018  ThreadId::Current());
6019  // Same thread re-enters the isolate, no need to re-init anything.
6020  entry_stack->entry_count++;
6021  return;
6022  }
6023  }
6024 
6025  PerIsolateThreadData* data = FindOrAllocatePerThreadDataForThisThread();
6026  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(data);
6027  DCHECK(data->isolate_ == this);
6028 
6029  EntryStackItem* item =
6030  new EntryStackItem(current_data, current_isolate, entry_stack_);
6031  entry_stack_ = item;
6032 
6033  SetIsolateThreadLocals(this, data);
6034 
6035  // In case it's the first time some thread enters the isolate.
6036  set_thread_id(data->thread_id());
6037 }
6038 
6039 void Isolate::Exit() {
6040  auto current_entry_stack = entry_stack_.load();
6041  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_entry_stack);
6042  DCHECK(current_entry_stack->previous_thread_data == nullptr ||
6043  current_entry_stack->previous_thread_data->thread_id() ==
6044  ThreadId::Current());
6045 
6046 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
6047  // The current thread must have entered the isolate.
6048  CHECK_EQ(current_thread_id_, ThreadId::Current());
6049  if (--current_thread_counter_ == 0) current_thread_id_ = ThreadId::Invalid();
6050 #endif
6051 
6052  if (--current_entry_stack->entry_count > 0) return;
6053 
6054  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(CurrentPerIsolateThreadData());
6055  DCHECK(CurrentPerIsolateThreadData()->isolate_ == this);
6056 
6057  // Pop the stack.
6058  entry_stack_ = current_entry_stack->previous_item;
6059 
6060  PerIsolateThreadData* previous_thread_data =
6061  current_entry_stack->previous_thread_data;
6062  Isolate* previous_isolate = current_entry_stack->previous_isolate;
6063 
6064  delete current_entry_stack;
6065 
6066  // Reinit the current thread for the isolate it was running before this one.
6067  SetIsolateThreadLocals(previous_isolate, previous_thread_data);
6068 }
6069 
6070 OptimizingCompileDispatcher* Isolate::SetOptimizingCompileDispatcherForTesting(
6071  OptimizingCompileDispatcher* dispatcher) {
6072  return std::exchange(optimizing_compile_dispatcher_, dispatcher);
6073 }
6074 
6075 std::unique_ptr<PersistentHandles> Isolate::NewPersistentHandles() {
6076  return std::make_unique<PersistentHandles>(this);
6077 }
6078 
6079 void Isolate::DumpAndResetStats() {
6080  if (v8_flags.trace_turbo_stack_accesses) {
6081  StdoutStream os;
6082  uint64_t total_loads = 0;
6083  uint64_t total_stores = 0;
6084  os << "=== Stack access counters === " << std::endl;
6085  if (!stack_access_count_map) {
6086  os << "No stack accesses in optimized/wasm functions found.";
6087  } else {
6088  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(stack_access_count_map);
6089  os << "Number of optimized/wasm stack-access functions: "
6090  << stack_access_count_map->size() << std::endl;
6091  for (auto it = stack_access_count_map->cbegin();
6092  it != stack_access_count_map->cend(); it++) {
6093  std::string function_name((*it).first);
6094  std::pair<uint64_t, uint64_t> per_func_count = (*it).second;
6095  os << "Name: " << function_name << ", Loads: " << per_func_count.first
6096  << ", Stores: " << per_func_count.second << std::endl;
6097  total_loads += per_func_count.first;
6098  total_stores += per_func_count.second;
6099  }
6100  os << "Total Loads: " << total_loads << ", Total Stores: " << total_stores
6101  << std::endl;
6102  stack_access_count_map = nullptr;
6103  }
6104  }
6105  if (turbo_statistics_ != nullptr) {
6106  DCHECK(v8_flags.turbo_stats || v8_flags.turbo_stats_nvp);
6107  StdoutStream os;
6108  if (v8_flags.turbo_stats) {
6109  AsPrintableStatistics ps = {"Turbofan", *turbo_statistics_, false};
6110  os << ps << std::endl;
6111  }
6112  if (v8_flags.turbo_stats_nvp) {
6113  AsPrintableStatistics ps = {"Turbofan", *turbo_statistics_, true};
6114  os << ps << std::endl;
6115  }
6116  turbo_statistics_.reset();
6117  }
6118 
6119 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
6120  if (maglev_statistics_ != nullptr) {
6121  DCHECK(v8_flags.maglev_stats || v8_flags.maglev_stats_nvp);
6122  StdoutStream os;
6123  if (v8_flags.maglev_stats) {
6124  AsPrintableStatistics ps = {"Maglev", *maglev_statistics_, false};
6125  os << ps << std::endl;
6126  }
6127  if (v8_flags.maglev_stats_nvp) {
6128  AsPrintableStatistics ps = {"Maglev", *maglev_statistics_, true};
6129  os << ps << std::endl;
6130  }
6131  maglev_statistics_.reset();
6132  }
6133 #endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
6134 
6135 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6136  // TODO(7424): There is no public API for the {WasmEngine} yet. So for now we
6137  // just dump and reset the engines statistics together with the Isolate.
6138  if (v8_flags.turbo_stats_wasm) {
6139  wasm::GetWasmEngine()->DumpAndResetTurboStatistics();
6140  }
6141 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6142 
6143  if (v8_flags.trace_number_string_cache) {
6144  PrintNumberStringCacheStats("DumpAndResetStats", true);
6145  }
6146 
6147 #if V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6148  if (V8_UNLIKELY(TracingFlags::runtime_stats.load(std::memory_order_relaxed) ==
6149  v8::tracing::TracingCategoryObserver::ENABLED_BY_NATIVE)) {
6150  counters()->worker_thread_runtime_call_stats()->AddToMainTable(
6151  counters()->runtime_call_stats());
6152  counters()->runtime_call_stats()->Print();
6153  counters()->runtime_call_stats()->Reset();
6154  }
6155 #endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6156 }
6157 
6158 void Isolate::DumpAndResetBuiltinsProfileData() {
6159  if (BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->HasData(this)) {
6160  if (v8_flags.turbo_profiling_output) {
6161  FILE* f = std::fopen(v8_flags.turbo_profiling_output, "w");
6162  if (f == nullptr) {
6163  FATAL("Unable to open file \"%s\" for writing.\n",
6164  v8_flags.turbo_profiling_output.value());
6165  }
6166  OFStream pgo_stream(f);
6167  BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->Log(this, pgo_stream);
6168  } else {
6169  StdoutStream out;
6170  BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->Print(this, out);
6171  }
6172  BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->ResetCounts(this);
6173  } else {
6174  // Only log builtins PGO data if v8 was built with
6175  // v8_enable_builtins_profiling=true
6176  CHECK_NULL(v8_flags.turbo_profiling_output);
6177  }
6178 }

6180 void Isolate::IncreaseConcurrentOptimizationPriority(
6181  CodeKind kind, Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> function) {
6182  DCHECK_EQ(kind, CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS);
6183  optimizing_compile_dispatcher()->Prioritize(function);
6184 }
6185 
6186 void Isolate::AbortConcurrentOptimization(BlockingBehavior behavior) {
6187  if (concurrent_recompilation_enabled()) {
6188  DisallowGarbageCollection no_recursive_gc;
6189  optimizing_compile_dispatcher()->Flush(behavior);
6190  }
6191 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV

6248 bool Isolate::NeedsSourcePositions() const {
6249  return
6250  // Static conditions.
6251  v8_flags.trace_deopt || v8_flags.trace_turbo ||
6252  v8_flags.trace_turbo_graph || v8_flags.turbo_profiling ||
6253  v8_flags.print_maglev_code || v8_flags.perf_prof || v8_flags.log_maps ||
6254  v8_flags.log_ic || v8_flags.log_function_events ||
6255  v8_flags.heap_snapshot_on_oom ||
6256  // Dynamic conditions; changing any of these conditions triggers source
6257  // position collection for the entire heap
6258  // (CollectSourcePositionsForAllBytecodeArrays).
6259  is_profiling() || debug_->is_active() || v8_file_logger_->is_logging();

6262 void Isolate::SetFeedbackVectorsForProfilingTools(Tagged<Object> value) {
6263  DCHECK(IsUndefined(value, this) || IsArrayList(value));
6264  heap()->set_feedback_vectors_for_profiling_tools(value);
6265 }
6266 
6267 void Isolate::MaybeInitializeVectorListFromHeap() {
6268  if (!IsUndefined(heap()->feedback_vectors_for_profiling_tools(), this)) {
6269  // Already initialized, return early.
6270  DCHECK(IsArrayList(heap()->feedback_vectors_for_profiling_tools()));
6271  return;
6272  }
6273 
6274  // Collect existing feedback vectors.
6275  DirectHandleVector<FeedbackVector> vectors(this);
6276 
6277  {
6278  HeapObjectIterator heap_iterator(heap());
6279  for (Tagged<HeapObject> current_obj = heap_iterator.Next();
6280  !current_obj.is_null(); current_obj = heap_iterator.Next()) {
6281  if (!IsFeedbackVector(current_obj)) continue;
6282 
6283  Tagged<FeedbackVector> vector = Cast<FeedbackVector>(current_obj);
6284  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = vector->shared_function_info();
6285 
6286  // No need to preserve the feedback vector for non-user-visible functions.
6287  if (!shared->IsSubjectToDebugging()) continue;
6288 
6289  vectors.emplace_back(vector, this);
6290  }
6291  }
6292 
6293  // Add collected feedback vectors to the root list lest we lose them to GC.
6294  DirectHandle<ArrayList> list =
6295  ArrayList::New(this, static_cast<int>(vectors.size()));
6296  for (const auto& vector : vectors) list = ArrayList::Add(this, list, vector);
6297  SetFeedbackVectorsForProfilingTools(*list);
6298 }

6307 void Isolate::IncreaseDateCacheStampAndInvalidateProtector() {
6308  // There's no need to update stamp and invalidate the protector since there
6309  // were no JSDate instances created yet and thus such a configuration change
6310  // is not observable anyway.
6311  if (!isolate_data()->is_date_cache_used_) return;
6312 
6313  if (isolate_data()->date_cache_stamp_ < Smi::kMaxValue) {
6314  ++isolate_data()->date_cache_stamp_;
6315  } else {
6316  isolate_data()->date_cache_stamp_ = 1;
6317  }
6318 
6319  if (Protectors::IsNoDateTimeConfigurationChangeIntact(this)) {
6320  Protectors::InvalidateNoDateTimeConfigurationChange(this);
6321  }
6322 }

6324 Isolate::KnownPrototype Isolate::IsArrayOrObjectOrStringPrototype(
6325  Tagged<JSObject> object) {
6326  Tagged<Map> metamap = object->map(this)->map(this);
6327  Tagged<NativeContext> native_context = metamap->native_context();
6328  if (native_context->initial_object_prototype() == object) {
6329  return KnownPrototype::kObject;
6330  } else if (native_context->initial_array_prototype() == object) {
6331  return KnownPrototype::kArray;
6332  } else if (native_context->initial_string_prototype() == object) {
6333  return KnownPrototype::kString;
6334  }
6335  return KnownPrototype::kNone;
6336 }
6337 
6338 bool Isolate::IsInCreationContext(Tagged<JSObject> object, uint32_t index) {
6339  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6340  Tagged<Map> metamap = object->map(this)->map(this);
6341  // Filter out native-context independent objects.
6342  if (metamap == ReadOnlyRoots(this).meta_map()) return false;
6343  Tagged<NativeContext> native_context = metamap->native_context();
6344  return native_context->GetNoCell(index) == object;
6345 }

6347 void Isolate::UpdateNoElementsProtectorOnSetElement(
6348  DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
6349  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6350  if (!object->map()->is_prototype_map()) return;
6351  if (!Protectors::IsNoElementsIntact(this)) return;
6352  KnownPrototype obj_type = IsArrayOrObjectOrStringPrototype(*object);
6353  if (obj_type == KnownPrototype::kNone) return;
6354  if (obj_type == KnownPrototype::kObject) {
6355  this->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kObjectPrototypeHasElements);
6356  } else if (obj_type == KnownPrototype::kArray) {
6357  this->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kArrayPrototypeHasElements);
6358  }
6359  Protectors::InvalidateNoElements(this);
6360 }
6361 
6362 void Isolate::UpdateProtectorsOnSetPrototype(
6363  DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<Object> new_prototype) {
6364  UpdateNoElementsProtectorOnSetPrototype(object);
6365  UpdateTypedArraySpeciesLookupChainProtectorOnSetPrototype(object);
6366  UpdateNumberStringNotRegexpLikeProtectorOnSetPrototype(object);
6367  UpdateStringWrapperToPrimitiveProtectorOnSetPrototype(object, new_prototype);
6368 }
6369 
6370 void Isolate::UpdateTypedArraySpeciesLookupChainProtectorOnSetPrototype(
6371  DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
6372  // Setting the __proto__ of TypedArray constructor could change TypedArray's
6373  // @@species. So we need to invalidate the @@species protector.
6374  if (IsTypedArrayConstructor(*object) &&
6375  Protectors::IsTypedArraySpeciesLookupChainIntact(this)) {
6376  Protectors::InvalidateTypedArraySpeciesLookupChain(this);
6377  }
6378 }
6379 
6380 void Isolate::UpdateNumberStringNotRegexpLikeProtectorOnSetPrototype(
6381  DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
6382  if (!Protectors::IsNumberStringNotRegexpLikeIntact(this)) {
6383  return;
6384  }
6385  // We need to protect the prototype chain of `Number.prototype` and
6386  // `String.prototype`.
6387  // Since `Object.prototype.__proto__` is not writable, we can assume it
6388  // doesn't occur here. We detect `Number.prototype` and `String.prototype` by
6389  // checking for a prototype that is a JSPrimitiveWrapper. This is a safe
6390  // approximation. Using JSPrimitiveWrapper as prototype should be
6391  // sufficiently rare.
6392  DCHECK(!IsJSObjectPrototype(*object));
6393  if (object->map()->is_prototype_map() && (IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(*object))) {
6394  Protectors::InvalidateNumberStringNotRegexpLike(this);
6395  }
6396 }
6397 
6398 void Isolate::UpdateStringWrapperToPrimitiveProtectorOnSetPrototype(
6399  DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<Object> new_prototype) {
6400  if (!Protectors::IsStringWrapperToPrimitiveIntact(this)) {
6401  return;
6402  }
6403 
6404  // We can have a custom @@toPrimitive on a string wrapper also if we subclass
6405  // String and the subclass (or one of its subclasses) defines its own
6406  // @@toPrimitive. Thus we invalidate the protector whenever we detect
6407  // subclassing String - it should be reasonably rare.
6408  if (IsStringWrapper(*object) || IsStringWrapper(*new_prototype)) {
6409  Protectors::InvalidateStringWrapperToPrimitive(this);
6410  }
6411 }

6444 int Isolate::GenerateIdentityHash(uint32_t mask) {
6445  int hash;
6446  int attempts = 0;
6447  do {
6448  hash = random_number_generator()->NextInt() & mask;
6449  } while (hash == 0 && attempts++ < 30);
6450  return hash != 0 ? hash : 1;
6451 }

6461 DirectHandle<Symbol> Isolate::SymbolFor(RootIndex dictionary_index,
6462  Handle<String> name,
6463  bool private_symbol) {
6464  DirectHandle<String> key = factory()->InternalizeString(name);
6465  Handle<RegisteredSymbolTable> dictionary =
6466  Cast<RegisteredSymbolTable>(root_handle(dictionary_index));
6467  InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(this, key);
6468  DirectHandle<Symbol> symbol;
6469  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
6470  symbol =
6471  private_symbol ? factory()->NewPrivateSymbol() : factory()->NewSymbol();
6472  symbol->set_description(*key);
6473  dictionary = RegisteredSymbolTable::Add(this, dictionary, key, symbol);
6474 
6475  switch (dictionary_index) {
6476  case RootIndex::kPublicSymbolTable:
6477  symbol->set_is_in_public_symbol_table(true);
6478  heap()->set_public_symbol_table(*dictionary);
6479  break;
6480  case RootIndex::kApiSymbolTable:
6481  heap()->set_api_symbol_table(*dictionary);
6482  break;
6483  case RootIndex::kApiPrivateSymbolTable:
6484  heap()->set_api_private_symbol_table(*dictionary);
6485  break;
6486  default:
6487  UNREACHABLE();
6488  }
6489  } else {
6490  symbol =
6491  DirectHandle<Symbol>(Cast<Symbol>(dictionary->ValueAt(entry)), this);
6492  }
6493  return symbol;
6494 }

6524 
6525 void Isolate::FireCallCompletedCallbackInternal(
6526  MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
6527  DCHECK(thread_local_top()->CallDepthIsZero());
6528 
6529  bool perform_checkpoint =
6530  microtask_queue &&
6531  microtask_queue->microtasks_policy() == v8::MicrotasksPolicy::kAuto &&
6532  !is_execution_terminating();
6533 
6534  v8::Isolate* isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this);
6535  if (perform_checkpoint) microtask_queue->PerformCheckpoint(isolate);
6536 
6537  if (call_completed_callbacks_.empty()) return;
6538  // Fire callbacks. Increase call depth to prevent recursive callbacks.
6539  v8::Isolate::SuppressMicrotaskExecutionScope suppress(isolate);
6540  std::vector<CallCompletedCallback> callbacks(call_completed_callbacks_);
6541  for (auto& callback : callbacks) {
6542  callback(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this));
6543  }
6544 }

6546 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6547 void Isolate::WasmInitJSPIFeature() {
6548  if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless) return;
6549 
6550  if (isolate_data_.active_stack() == nullptr) {
6551  wasm::StackMemory* stack(wasm::StackMemory::GetCentralStackView(this));
6552  stack->jmpbuf()->state = wasm::JumpBuffer::Active;
6553  this->wasm_stacks().emplace_back(stack);
6554  stack->set_index(0);
6555  if (v8_flags.trace_wasm_stack_switching) {
6556  PrintF("Set up native stack object (limit: %p, base: %p)\n",
6557  stack->jslimit(), reinterpret_cast<void*>(stack->base()));
6558  }
6559  HandleScope scope(this);
6560  isolate_data_.set_active_stack(stack);
6561  }
6562 }
6563 #endif
