6586 MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise> NewRejectedPromise(
6587  Isolate* isolate, v8::Local<v8::Context> api_context,
6588  DirectHandle<Object> exception) {
6589  v8::Local<v8::Promise::Resolver> resolver;
6590  API_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, resolver,
6591  v8::Promise::Resolver::New(api_context),
6592  MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>());
6593 
6594  MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6595  isolate, resolver->Reject(api_context, v8::Utils::ToLocal(exception)),
6596  MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>());
6597 
6598  v8::Local<v8::Promise> promise = resolver->GetPromise();
6599  return v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*promise);
6600 }
6601 
6602 } // namespace
6603 
6604 MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise> Isolate::RunHostImportModuleDynamicallyCallback(
6605  MaybeDirectHandle<Script> maybe_referrer, Handle<Object> specifier,
6606  ModuleImportPhase phase,
6607  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> maybe_import_options_argument) {
6608  DCHECK(!is_execution_terminating());
6609  v8::Local<v8::Context> api_context = v8::Utils::ToLocal(native_context());
6610 
6611  switch (phase) {
6612  case ModuleImportPhase::kEvaluation:
6613  if (host_import_module_dynamically_callback_ == nullptr &&
6614  host_import_module_with_phase_dynamically_callback_ == nullptr) {
6615  DirectHandle<Object> exception = factory()->NewError(
6616  error_function(), MessageTemplate::kUnsupported);
6617  return NewRejectedPromise(this, api_context, exception);
6618  }
6619  break;
6620  case ModuleImportPhase::kSource:
6621  if (host_import_module_with_phase_dynamically_callback_ == nullptr) {
6622  DirectHandle<Object> exception = factory()->NewError(
6623  error_function(), MessageTemplate::kUnsupported);
6624  return NewRejectedPromise(this, api_context, exception);
6625  }
6626  break;
6627  }
6628 
6629  DirectHandle<String> specifier_str;
6630  MaybeDirectHandle<String> maybe_specifier = Object::ToString(this, specifier);
6631  if (!maybe_specifier.ToHandle(&specifier_str)) {
6632  if (is_execution_terminating()) {
6633  return MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>();
6634  }
6635  DirectHandle<Object> exception(this->exception(), this);
6636  clear_exception();
6637  return NewRejectedPromise(this, api_context, exception);
6638  }
6639  DCHECK(!has_exception());
6640 
6641  v8::Local<v8::Promise> promise;
6642  DirectHandle<FixedArray> import_attributes_array;
6643  if (!GetImportAttributesFromArgument(maybe_import_options_argument)
6644  .ToHandle(&import_attributes_array)) {
6645  if (is_execution_terminating()) {
6646  return MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>();
6647  }
6648  DirectHandle<Object> exception(this->exception(), this);
6649  clear_exception();
6650  return NewRejectedPromise(this, api_context, exception);
6651  }
6652  DirectHandle<FixedArray> host_defined_options;
6653  DirectHandle<Object> resource_name;
6654  if (maybe_referrer.is_null()) {
6655  host_defined_options = factory()->empty_fixed_array();
6656  resource_name = factory()->null_value();
6657  } else {
6658  DirectHandle<Script> referrer = maybe_referrer.ToHandleChecked();
6659  host_defined_options =
6660  direct_handle(referrer->host_defined_options(), this);
6661  resource_name = direct_handle(referrer->name(), this);
6662  }
6663 
6664  switch (phase) {
6665  case ModuleImportPhase::kEvaluation:
6666  // TODO(42204365): Deprecate HostImportModuleDynamicallyCallback once
6667  // HostImportModuleWithPhaseDynamicallyCallback is stable.
6668  if (host_import_module_with_phase_dynamically_callback_ != nullptr) {
6669  API_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6670  this, promise,
6671  host_import_module_with_phase_dynamically_callback_(
6672  api_context, v8::Utils::ToLocal(host_defined_options),
6673  v8::Utils::ToLocal(resource_name),
6674  v8::Utils::ToLocal(specifier_str), phase,
6675  ToApiHandle<v8::FixedArray>(import_attributes_array)),
6676  MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>());
6677  } else {
6678  API_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6679  this, promise,
6680  host_import_module_dynamically_callback_(
6681  api_context, v8::Utils::ToLocal(host_defined_options),
6682  v8::Utils::ToLocal(resource_name),
6683  v8::Utils::ToLocal(specifier_str),
6684  ToApiHandle<v8::FixedArray>(import_attributes_array)),
6685  MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>());
6686  }
6687  break;
6688  case ModuleImportPhase::kSource:
6689  CHECK(v8_flags.js_source_phase_imports);
6690  CHECK_NOT_NULL(host_import_module_with_phase_dynamically_callback_);
6691  API_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6692  this, promise,
6693  host_import_module_with_phase_dynamically_callback_(
6694  api_context, v8::Utils::ToLocal(host_defined_options),
6695  v8::Utils::ToLocal(resource_name),
6696  v8::Utils::ToLocal(specifier_str), phase,
6697  ToApiHandle<v8::FixedArray>(import_attributes_array)),
6698  MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>());
6699  break;
6700  default:
6701  UNREACHABLE();
6702  }
6703 
6704  return v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*promise);
6705 }
6706 
6707 MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray> Isolate::GetImportAttributesFromArgument(
6708  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> maybe_import_options_argument) {
6709  DirectHandle<FixedArray> import_attributes_array =
6710  factory()->empty_fixed_array();
6711  DirectHandle<Object> import_options_argument;
6712  if (!maybe_import_options_argument.ToHandle(&import_options_argument) ||
6713  IsUndefined(*import_options_argument)) {
6714  return import_attributes_array;
6715  }
6716 
6717  // The parser shouldn't have allowed the second argument to import() if
6718  // the flag wasn't enabled.
6719  DCHECK(v8_flags.harmony_import_attributes);
6720 
6721  if (!IsJSReceiver(*import_options_argument)) {
6722  this->Throw(
6723  *factory()->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonObjectImportArgument));
6724  return MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>();
6725  }
6726 
6727  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> import_options_argument_receiver =
6728  Cast<JSReceiver>(import_options_argument);
6729 
6730  DirectHandle<Object> import_attributes_object;
6731 
6732  if (v8_flags.harmony_import_attributes) {
6733  DirectHandle<Name> with_key = factory()->with_string();
6734  if (!JSReceiver::GetProperty(this, import_options_argument_receiver,
6735  with_key)
6736  .ToHandle(&import_attributes_object)) {
6737  // This can happen if the property has a getter function that throws
6738  // an error.
6739  return MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>();
6740  }
6741  }
6742 
6743  // If there is no 'with' option in the options bag, it's not an error. Just do
6744  // the import() as if no attributes were provided.
6745  if (IsUndefined(*import_attributes_object)) return import_attributes_array;
6746 
6747  if (!IsJSReceiver(*import_attributes_object)) {
6748  this->Throw(
6749  *factory()->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonObjectAttributesOption));
6750  return MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>();
6751  }
6752 
6753  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> import_attributes_object_receiver =
6754  Cast<JSReceiver>(import_attributes_object);
6755 
6756  DirectHandle<FixedArray> attribute_keys;
6757  if (!KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(this, import_attributes_object_receiver,
6758  KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly, ENUMERABLE_STRINGS,
6759  GetKeysConversion::kConvertToString)
6760  .ToHandle(&attribute_keys)) {
6761  // This happens if the attributes object is a Proxy whose ownKeys() or
6762  // getOwnPropertyDescriptor() trap throws.
6763  return MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>();
6764  }
6765 
6766  bool has_non_string_attribute = false;
6767 
6768  // The attributes will be passed to the host in the form: [key1,
6769  // value1, key2, value2, ...].
6770  constexpr size_t kAttributeEntrySizeForDynamicImport = 2;
6771  import_attributes_array = factory()->NewFixedArray(static_cast<int>(
6772  attribute_keys->length() * kAttributeEntrySizeForDynamicImport));
6773  for (int i = 0; i < attribute_keys->length(); i++) {
6774  DirectHandle<String> attribute_key(Cast<String>(attribute_keys->get(i)),
6775  this);
6776  DirectHandle<Object> attribute_value;
6777  if (!Object::GetPropertyOrElement(this, import_attributes_object_receiver,
6778  attribute_key)
6779  .ToHandle(&attribute_value)) {
6780  // This can happen if the property has a getter function that throws
6781  // an error.
6782  return MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>();
6783  }
6784 
6785  if (!IsString(*attribute_value)) {
6786  has_non_string_attribute = true;
6787  }
6788 
6789  import_attributes_array->set((i * kAttributeEntrySizeForDynamicImport),
6790  *attribute_key);
6791  import_attributes_array->set((i * kAttributeEntrySizeForDynamicImport) + 1,
6792  *attribute_value);
6793  }
6794 
6795  if (has_non_string_attribute) {
6796  this->Throw(*factory()->NewTypeError(
6797  MessageTemplate::kNonStringImportAttributeValue));
6798  return MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>();
6799  }
6800 
6801  return import_attributes_array;
6802 }

6999 void Isolate::RunPromiseHook(PromiseHookType type,
7000  DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
7001  DirectHandle<Object> parent) {
7002  if (!HasIsolatePromiseHooks()) return;

7004  promise_hook_(type, v8::Utils::PromiseToLocal(promise),
7005  v8::Utils::ToLocal(parent));

7007 
7008 void Isolate::OnAsyncFunctionSuspended(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
7009  DirectHandle<JSPromise> parent) {
7010  DCHECK(!promise->has_async_task_id());
7011  RunAllPromiseHooks(PromiseHookType::kInit, promise, parent);
7012  if (HasAsyncEventDelegate()) {
7013  DCHECK_NE(nullptr, async_event_delegate_);
7014  current_async_task_id_ =
7015  JSPromise::GetNextAsyncTaskId(current_async_task_id_);
7016  promise->set_async_task_id(current_async_task_id_);
7017  async_event_delegate_->AsyncEventOccurred(debug::kDebugAwait,
7018  promise->async_task_id(), false);
7019  }
7020 }
7021 
7022 void Isolate::OnPromiseThen(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise) {
7023  if (!HasAsyncEventDelegate()) return;
7024  Maybe<debug::DebugAsyncActionType> action_type =
7025  Nothing<debug::DebugAsyncActionType>();
7026  for (JavaScriptStackFrameIterator frame_it(this); !frame_it.done();
7027  frame_it.Advance()) {
7028  std::vector<Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>> infos;
7029  frame_it.frame()->GetFunctions(&infos);
7030  for (auto it = infos.rbegin(); it != infos.rend(); ++it) {
7031  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info = *it;
7032  if (info->HasBuiltinId()) {
7033  // We should not report PromiseThen and PromiseCatch which is called
7034  // indirectly, e.g. Promise.all calls Promise.then internally.
7035  switch (info->builtin_id()) {
7036  case Builtin::kPromisePrototypeCatch:
7037  action_type = Just(debug::kDebugPromiseCatch);
7038  continue;
7039  case Builtin::kPromisePrototypeFinally:
7040  action_type = Just(debug::kDebugPromiseFinally);
7041  continue;
7042  case Builtin::kPromisePrototypeThen:
7043  action_type = Just(debug::kDebugPromiseThen);
7044  continue;
7045  default:
7046  return;
7047  }
7048  }
7049  if (info->IsUserJavaScript() && action_type.IsJust()) {
7050  DCHECK(!promise->has_async_task_id());
7051  current_async_task_id_ =
7052  JSPromise::GetNextAsyncTaskId(current_async_task_id_);
7053  promise->set_async_task_id(current_async_task_id_);
7054  async_event_delegate_->AsyncEventOccurred(action_type.FromJust(),
7055  promise->async_task_id(),
7056  debug()->IsBlackboxed(info));
7057  }
7058  return;
7059  }
7060  }
7061 }
7062 
7063 void Isolate::OnPromiseBefore(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise) {
7064  RunPromiseHook(PromiseHookType::kBefore, promise,
7065  factory()->undefined_value());
7066  if (HasAsyncEventDelegate()) {
7067  if (promise->has_async_task_id()) {
7068  async_event_delegate_->AsyncEventOccurred(
7069  debug::kDebugWillHandle, promise->async_task_id(), false);
7070  }
7071  }
7072 }
7073 
7074 void Isolate::OnPromiseAfter(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise) {
7075  RunPromiseHook(PromiseHookType::kAfter, promise,
7076  factory()->undefined_value());
7077  if (HasAsyncEventDelegate()) {
7078  if (promise->has_async_task_id()) {
7079  async_event_delegate_->AsyncEventOccurred(
7080  debug::kDebugDidHandle, promise->async_task_id(), false);
7081  }
7082  }
7083 }

7085 void Isolate::OnStackTraceCaptured(DirectHandle<StackTraceInfo> stack_trace) {

7091 
7092 void Isolate::OnTerminationDuringRunMicrotasks() {
7093  DCHECK(is_execution_terminating());
7094  // This performs cleanup for when RunMicrotasks (in
7095  // builtins-microtask-queue-gen.cc) is aborted via a termination exception.
7096  // This has to be kept in sync with the code in said file. Currently this
7097  // includes:
7098  //
7099  // (1) Resetting the |current_microtask| slot on the Isolate to avoid leaking
7100  // memory (and also to keep |current_microtask| not being undefined as an
7101  // indicator that we're currently pumping the microtask queue).
7102  // (2) Empty the promise stack to avoid leaking memory.
7103  // (3) If the |current_microtask| is a promise reaction or resolve thenable
7104  // job task, then signal the async event delegate and debugger that the
7105  // microtask finished running.
7106  //
7107 
7108  // Reset the |current_microtask| global slot.
7109  DirectHandle<Microtask> current_microtask(
7110  Cast<Microtask>(heap()->current_microtask()), this);
7111  heap()->set_current_microtask(ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
7112 
7113  if (IsPromiseReactionJobTask(*current_microtask)) {
7114  auto promise_reaction_job_task =
7115  Cast<PromiseReactionJobTask>(current_microtask);
7116  DirectHandle<HeapObject> promise_or_capability(
7117  promise_reaction_job_task->promise_or_capability(), this);
7118  if (IsPromiseCapability(*promise_or_capability)) {
7119  promise_or_capability = direct_handle(
7120  Cast<PromiseCapability>(promise_or_capability)->promise(), this);
7121  }
7122  if (IsJSPromise(*promise_or_capability)) {
7123  OnPromiseAfter(Cast<JSPromise>(promise_or_capability));
7124  }
7125  } else if (IsPromiseResolveThenableJobTask(*current_microtask)) {
7126  auto promise_resolve_thenable_job_task =
7127  Cast<PromiseResolveThenableJobTask>(current_microtask);
7128  DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise_to_resolve(
7129  promise_resolve_thenable_job_task->promise_to_resolve(), this);
7130  OnPromiseAfter(promise_to_resolve);
7131  }
7132 
7133  SetTerminationOnExternalTryCatch();
7134 }

7153 void Isolate::CountUsage(v8::Isolate::UseCounterFeature feature) {

7156 
7157 void Isolate::CountUsage(
7158  base::Vector<const v8::Isolate::UseCounterFeature> features) {
7159  // The counter callback
7160  // - may cause the embedder to call into V8, which is not generally possible
7161  // during GC.
7162  // - requires a current native context, which may not always exist.
7163  // TODO(jgruber): Consider either removing the native context requirement in
7164  // blink, or passing it to the callback explicitly.
7165  if (heap_.gc_state() == Heap::NOT_IN_GC && !context().is_null()) {
7166  DCHECK(IsContext(context()));
7167  DCHECK(IsNativeContext(context()->native_context()));
7168  if (use_counter_callback_) {
7169  HandleScope handle_scope(this);
7170  for (auto feature : features) {
7171  use_counter_callback_(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this), feature);
7172  }
7173  }
7174  } else {
7175  heap_.IncrementDeferredCounts(features);
7176  }
7177 }

7184  std::ostringstream os;
7185  os << "turbo-" << base::OS::GetCurrentProcessId() << "-";
7186  if (isolate != nullptr) {
7187  os << isolate->id();
7188  } else {
7189  os << "any";
7190  }
7191  os << ".cfg";
7192  return os.str();
7193 }

7195 // Heap::detached_contexts tracks detached contexts as pairs
7196 // (the context, number of GC since the context was detached).
7197 void Isolate::AddDetachedContext(DirectHandle<Context> context) {
7198  HandleScope scope(this);
7199  Handle<WeakArrayList> detached_contexts = factory()->detached_contexts();
7200  detached_contexts = WeakArrayList::AddToEnd(
7201  this, detached_contexts, MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(context),
7202  Smi::zero());
7203  heap()->set_detached_contexts(*detached_contexts);
7204 }
7205 
7206 void Isolate::CheckDetachedContextsAfterGC() {
7207  HandleScope scope(this);
7208  DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> detached_contexts =
7209  factory()->detached_contexts();
7210  int length = detached_contexts->length();
7211  if (length == 0) return;
7212  int new_length = 0;
7213  for (int i = 0; i < length; i += 2) {
7214  Tagged<MaybeObject> context = detached_contexts->Get(i);
7215  DCHECK(context.IsWeakOrCleared());
7216  if (!context.IsCleared()) {
7217  int mark_sweeps = detached_contexts->Get(i + 1).ToSmi().value();
7218  detached_contexts->Set(new_length, context);
7219  detached_contexts->Set(new_length + 1, Smi::FromInt(mark_sweeps + 1));
7220  new_length += 2;
7221  }
7222  }
7223  detached_contexts->set_length(new_length);
7224  while (new_length < length) {
7225  detached_contexts->Set(new_length, Smi::zero());
7226  ++new_length;
7227  }
7228 
7229  if (v8_flags.trace_detached_contexts) {
7230  PrintF("%d detached contexts are collected out of %d\n",
7231  length - new_length, length);
7232  for (int i = 0; i < new_length; i += 2) {
7233  Tagged<MaybeObject> context = detached_contexts->Get(i);
7234  int mark_sweeps = detached_contexts->Get(i + 1).ToSmi().value();
7235  DCHECK(context.IsWeakOrCleared());
7236  if (mark_sweeps > 3) {
7237  PrintF("detached context %p\n survived %d GCs (leak?)\n",
7238  reinterpret_cast<void*>(context.ptr()), mark_sweeps);
7239  }
7240  }
7241  }
7242 }
7243 
7244 void Isolate::DetachGlobal(DirectHandle<Context> env) {
7245  counters()->errors_thrown_per_context()->AddSample(
7246  env->native_context()->GetErrorsThrown());
7247 
7248  ReadOnlyRoots roots(this);
7249  DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy(env->global_proxy(), this);
7250  // NOTE: Turbofan's JSNativeContextSpecialization and Maglev depend on
7251  // DetachGlobal causing a map change.
7252  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(this, global_proxy, factory()->null_value());
7253  // Detach the global object from the native context by making its map
7254  // contextless (use the global metamap instead of the contextful one).
7255  global_proxy->map()->set_map(this, roots.meta_map());
7256  global_proxy->map()->set_constructor_or_back_pointer(roots.null_value(),
7257  kRelaxedStore);
7258  if (v8_flags.track_detached_contexts) AddDetachedContext(env);
7259  DCHECK(global_proxy->IsDetached());
7260 
7261  env->native_context()->set_microtask_queue(this, nullptr);
7262 }

7264 void Isolate::SetIsLoading(bool is_loading) {

7270  if (v8_flags.trace_rail) {
7271  // TODO(crbug.com/373688984): Switch to a trace flag for loading state.
7272  PrintIsolate(this, "RAIL mode: %s\n", is_loading ? "LOAD" : "ANIMATION");
7273  }
7274 }

7288 void Isolate::PrintWithTimestamp(const char* format, ...) {

7290  base::OS::Print("[%d:%p:%d] %8.0f ms: ", base::OS::GetCurrentProcessId(),
7291  static_cast<void*>(this), id(), time_millis_since_init());

7297 
7298 void Isolate::SetIdle(bool is_idle) {
7299  StateTag state = current_vm_state();
7300  if (js_entry_sp() != kNullAddress) return;
7301  DCHECK(state == EXTERNAL || state == IDLE);
7302  if (is_idle) {
7303  set_current_vm_state(IDLE);
7304  } else if (state == IDLE) {
7305  set_current_vm_state(EXTERNAL);
7306  }
7307 }
7308 
7309 void Isolate::CollectSourcePositionsForAllBytecodeArrays() {
7310  if (!initialized_) return;
7311 
7312  HandleScope scope(this);
7313  std::vector<Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>> sfis;
7314  {
7315  HeapObjectIterator iterator(heap());
7316  for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj = iterator.Next(); !obj.is_null();
7317  obj = iterator.Next()) {
7318  if (!IsSharedFunctionInfo(obj)) continue;
7319  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(obj);
7320  // If the script is a Smi, then the SharedFunctionInfo is in
7321  // the process of being deserialized.
7322  Tagged<Object> script = sfi->raw_script(kAcquireLoad);
7323  if (IsSmi(script)) {
7324  DCHECK_EQ(script, Smi::uninitialized_deserialization_value());
7325  continue;
7326  }
7327  if (!sfi->CanCollectSourcePosition(this)) continue;
7328  sfis.push_back(Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>(sfi, this));
7329  }
7330  }
7331  for (auto sfi : sfis) {
7332  SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(this, sfi);
7333  }
7334 }
7335

7340 std::string GetStringFromLocales(Isolate* isolate,
7341  DirectHandle<Object> locales) {
7342  if (IsUndefined(*locales, isolate)) return "";
7343  return std::string(Cast<String>(*locales)->ToCString().get());
7344 }
7345 
7346 bool StringEqualsLocales(Isolate* isolate, const std::string& str,
7347  DirectHandle<Object> locales) {
7348  if (IsUndefined(*locales, isolate)) return str.empty();
7349  return Cast<String>(locales)->IsEqualTo(
7350  base::VectorOf(str.c_str(), str.length()));
7351 }
7352

7355 const std::string& Isolate::DefaultLocale() {
7356  if (default_locale_.empty()) {
7357  icu::Locale default_locale;
7358  // Translate ICU's fallback locale to a well-known locale.
7359  if (strcmp(default_locale.getName(), "en_US_POSIX") == 0 ||
7360  strcmp(default_locale.getName(), "c") == 0) {
7361  set_default_locale("en-US");
7362  } else {
7363  // Set the locale
7364  set_default_locale(default_locale.isBogus()
7365  ? "und"
7366  : Intl::ToLanguageTag(default_locale).FromJust());
7367  }
7368  DCHECK(!default_locale_.empty());
7369  }
7370  return default_locale_;
7371 }
7372 
7373 void Isolate::ResetDefaultLocale() {
7374  default_locale_.clear();
7375  clear_cached_icu_objects();
7376  // We inline fast paths assuming certain locales. Since this path is rarely
7377  // taken, we deoptimize everything to keep things simple.
7378  Deoptimizer::DeoptimizeAll(this);
7379 }

7408 bool StackLimitCheck::HandleStackOverflowAndTerminationRequest() {
7409  DCHECK(InterruptRequested());
7410  if (V8_UNLIKELY(HasOverflowed())) {
7411  isolate_->StackOverflow();
7412  return true;
7413  }
7414  if (V8_UNLIKELY(isolate_->stack_guard()->HasTerminationRequest())) {
7415  isolate_->TerminateExecution();
7416  return true;
7417  }
7418  return false;
7419 }
7420 
7421 bool StackLimitCheck::JsHasOverflowed(uintptr_t gap) const {
7422  StackGuard* stack_guard = isolate_->stack_guard();
7423 #ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
7424  // The simulator uses a separate JS stack.
7425  Address jssp_address = Simulator::current(isolate_)->get_sp();
7426  uintptr_t jssp = static_cast<uintptr_t>(jssp_address);
7427  if (jssp - gap < stack_guard->real_jslimit()) return true;
7428 #endif // USE_SIMULATOR
7429  return GetCurrentStackPosition() - gap < stack_guard->real_climit();
7430 }
7431 
7432 bool StackLimitCheck::WasmHasOverflowed(uintptr_t gap) const {
7433  StackGuard* stack_guard = isolate_->stack_guard();
7434  auto sp = isolate_->thread_local_top()->secondary_stack_sp_;
7435  auto limit = isolate_->thread_local_top()->secondary_stack_limit_;
7436  if (sp == 0) {
7437 #ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
7438  // The simulator uses a separate JS stack.
7439  // Use it if code is executed on the central stack.
7440  Address jssp_address = Simulator::current(isolate_)->get_sp();
7441  uintptr_t jssp = static_cast<uintptr_t>(jssp_address);
7442  if (jssp - gap < stack_guard->real_jslimit()) return true;
7443 #endif // USE_SIMULATOR
7444  sp = GetCurrentStackPosition();
7445  limit = stack_guard->real_climit();
7446  }
7447  return sp - gap < limit;
7448 }

7481 namespace {
7482 
7483 bool Overlapping(const MemoryRange& a, const MemoryRange& b) {
7484  uintptr_t a1 = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(a.start);
7485  uintptr_t a2 = a1 + a.length_in_bytes;
7486  uintptr_t b1 = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(b.start);
7487  uintptr_t b2 = b1 + b.length_in_bytes;
7488  // Either b1 or b2 are in the [a1, a2) range.
7489  return (a1 <= b1 && b1 < a2) || (a1 <= b2 && b2 < a2);
7490 }
7491 
7492 } // anonymous namespace
7493 
7494 #endif // DEBUG
7495 
7496 void Isolate::AddCodeMemoryRange(MemoryRange range) {
7497  base::MutexGuard guard(&code_pages_mutex_);
7498  std::vector<MemoryRange>* old_code_pages = GetCodePages();
7499  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(old_code_pages);
7500 #ifdef DEBUG
7501  auto overlapping = [range](const MemoryRange& a) {
7502  return Overlapping(range, a);
7503  };
7504  DCHECK_EQ(old_code_pages->end(),
7505  std::find_if(old_code_pages->begin(), old_code_pages->end(),
7506  overlapping));
7507 #endif
7508 
7509  std::vector<MemoryRange>* new_code_pages;
7510  if (old_code_pages == &code_pages_buffer1_) {
7511  new_code_pages = &code_pages_buffer2_;
7512  } else {
7513  new_code_pages = &code_pages_buffer1_;
7514  }
7515 
7516  // Copy all existing data from the old vector to the new vector and insert the
7517  // new page.
7518  new_code_pages->clear();
7519  new_code_pages->reserve(old_code_pages->size() + 1);
7520  std::merge(old_code_pages->begin(), old_code_pages->end(), &range, &range + 1,
7521  std::back_inserter(*new_code_pages),
7522  [](const MemoryRange& a, const MemoryRange& b) {
7523  return a.start < b.start;
7524  });
7525 
7526  // Atomically switch out the pointer
7527  SetCodePages(new_code_pages);
7528 }
7529 
7530 // |chunk| is either a Page or an executable LargePage.
7531 void Isolate::AddCodeMemoryChunk(MutablePageMetadata* chunk) {
7532  // We only keep track of individual code pages/allocations if we are on arm32,
7533  // because on x64 and arm64 we have a code range which makes this unnecessary.
7534 #if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
7535  void* new_page_start = reinterpret_cast<void*>(chunk->area_start());
7536  size_t new_page_size = chunk->area_size();
7537 
7538  MemoryRange new_range{new_page_start, new_page_size};
7539 
7540  AddCodeMemoryRange(new_range);
7541 #endif // !defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
7542 }
7543 
7544 void Isolate::AddCodeRange(Address begin, size_t length_in_bytes) {
7545  AddCodeMemoryRange(
7546  MemoryRange{reinterpret_cast<void*>(begin), length_in_bytes});
7547 }

7553 v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId Isolate::GetOrRegisterRecorderContextId(
7554  DirectHandle<NativeContext> context) {
7555  if (serializer_enabled_) return v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId::Empty();
7556  i::Tagged<i::Object> id = context->recorder_context_id();
7557  if (IsNullOrUndefined(id)) {
7558  CHECK_LT(last_recorder_context_id_, i::Smi::kMaxValue);
7559  context->set_recorder_context_id(
7560  i::Smi::FromIntptr(++last_recorder_context_id_));
7561  v8::HandleScope handle_scope(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this));
7562  auto result = recorder_context_id_map_.emplace(
7563  std::piecewise_construct,
7564  std::forward_as_tuple(last_recorder_context_id_),
7565  std::forward_as_tuple(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this),
7566  ToApiHandle<v8::Context>(context)));
7567  result.first->second.SetWeak(
7568  reinterpret_cast<void*>(last_recorder_context_id_),
7569  RemoveContextIdCallback, v8::WeakCallbackType::kParameter);
7570  return v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId(last_recorder_context_id_);
7571  } else {
7572  DCHECK(IsSmi(id));
7573  return v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId(
7574  static_cast<uintptr_t>(i::Smi::ToInt(id)));
7575  }
7576 }
7577 
7578 MaybeLocal<v8::Context> Isolate::GetContextFromRecorderContextId(
7579  v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId id) {
7580  auto result = recorder_context_id_map_.find(id.id_);
7581  if (result == recorder_context_id_map_.end() || result->second.IsEmpty())
7582  return MaybeLocal<v8::Context>();
7583  return result->second.Get(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this));
7584 }

7615 // |chunk| is either a Page or an executable LargePage.
7616 void Isolate::RemoveCodeMemoryChunk(MutablePageMetadata* chunk) {
7617  // We only keep track of individual code pages/allocations if we are on arm32,
7618  // because on x64 and arm64 we have a code range which makes this unnecessary.
7619 #if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
7620  void* removed_page_start = reinterpret_cast<void*>(chunk->area_start());
7621  std::vector<MemoryRange>* old_code_pages = GetCodePages();
7622  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(old_code_pages);
7623 
7624  std::vector<MemoryRange>* new_code_pages;
7625  if (old_code_pages == &code_pages_buffer1_) {
7626  new_code_pages = &code_pages_buffer2_;
7627  } else {
7628  new_code_pages = &code_pages_buffer1_;
7629  }
7630 
7631  // Copy all existing data from the old vector to the new vector except the
7632  // removed page.
7633  new_code_pages->clear();
7634  new_code_pages->reserve(old_code_pages->size() - 1);
7635  std::remove_copy_if(old_code_pages->begin(), old_code_pages->end(),
7636  std::back_inserter(*new_code_pages),
7637  [removed_page_start](const MemoryRange& range) {
7638  return range.start == removed_page_start;
7639  });
7640  DCHECK_EQ(old_code_pages->size(), new_code_pages->size() + 1);
7641  // Atomically switch out the pointer
7642  SetCodePages(new_code_pages);
7643 #endif // !defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
7644 }

7651  std::make_unique<wasm::WasmExecutionTimer>(this, false);

7657 // static
7658 Address Isolate::load_from_stack_count_address(const char* function_name) {
7659  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(function_name);
7660  if (!stack_access_count_map) {
7661  stack_access_count_map = new MapOfLoadsAndStoresPerFunction{};
7662  }
7663  auto& map = *stack_access_count_map;
7664  std::string name(function_name);
7665  // It is safe to return the address of std::map values.
7666  // Only iterators and references to the erased elements are invalidated.
7667  return reinterpret_cast<Address>(&map[name].first);
7668 }
7669 
7670 // static
7671 Address Isolate::store_to_stack_count_address(const char* function_name) {
7672  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(function_name);
7673  if (!stack_access_count_map) {
7674  stack_access_count_map = new MapOfLoadsAndStoresPerFunction{};
7675  }
7676  auto& map = *stack_access_count_map;
7677  std::string name(function_name);
7678  // It is safe to return the address of std::map values.
7679  // Only iterators and references to the erased elements are invalidated.
7680  return reinterpret_cast<Address>(&map[name].second);
7681 }

7683 void Isolate::LocalsBlockListCacheRehash() {
7684  if (IsEphemeronHashTable(heap()->locals_block_list_cache())) {
7685  Tagged<EphemeronHashTable> cache =
7686  Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(heap()->locals_block_list_cache());
7687  cache->Rehash(this);
7688  }
7689 }
7690 void Isolate::LocalsBlockListCacheSet(
7691  DirectHandle<ScopeInfo> scope_info,
7692  DirectHandle<ScopeInfo> outer_scope_info,
7693  DirectHandle<StringSet> locals_blocklist) {
7694  Handle<EphemeronHashTable> cache;
7695  if (IsEphemeronHashTable(heap()->locals_block_list_cache())) {
7696  cache = handle(Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(heap()->locals_block_list_cache()),
7697  this);
7698  } else {
7699  CHECK(IsUndefined(heap()->locals_block_list_cache()));
7700  constexpr int kInitialCapacity = 8;
7701  cache = EphemeronHashTable::New(this, kInitialCapacity);
7702  }
7703  DCHECK(IsEphemeronHashTable(*cache));
7704 
7705  DirectHandle<Object> value;
7706  if (!outer_scope_info.is_null()) {
7707  value = factory()->NewTuple2(outer_scope_info, locals_blocklist,
7708  AllocationType::kYoung);
7709  } else {
7710  value = locals_blocklist;
7711  }
7712 
7713  CHECK(!value.is_null());
7714  cache = EphemeronHashTable::Put(cache, scope_info, value);
7715  heap()->set_locals_block_list_cache(*cache);
7716 }
7717 
7718 Tagged<Object> Isolate::LocalsBlockListCacheGet(
7719  DirectHandle<ScopeInfo> scope_info) {
7720  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
7721 
7722  if (!IsEphemeronHashTable(heap()->locals_block_list_cache())) {
7723  return ReadOnlyRoots(this).the_hole_value();
7724  }
7725 
7726  Tagged<Object> maybe_value =
7727  Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(heap()->locals_block_list_cache())
7728  ->Lookup(scope_info);
7729  if (IsTuple2(maybe_value)) return Cast<Tuple2>(maybe_value)->value2();
7730 
7731  CHECK(IsStringSet(maybe_value) || IsTheHole(maybe_value));
7732  return maybe_value;
7733 }

7740 void DefaultWasmAsyncResolvePromiseCallback(
7741  v8::Isolate* isolate, v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
7742  v8::Local<v8::Promise::Resolver> resolver, v8::Local<v8::Value> result,
7743  WasmAsyncSuccess success) {
7744  MicrotasksScope microtasks_scope(context,
7745  MicrotasksScope::kDoNotRunMicrotasks);
7746 
7747  Maybe<bool> ret = success == WasmAsyncSuccess::kSuccess
7748  ? resolver->Resolve(context, result)
7749  : resolver->Reject(context, result);
7750  // It's guaranteed that no exceptions will be thrown by these
7751  // operations, but execution might be terminating.
7752  CHECK(ret.IsJust() ? ret.FromJust() : isolate->IsExecutionTerminating());
7753 }
7754 
7755 // Mutex used to ensure that the dispatch table entries for builtins are only
7756 // initialized once.
7757 base::LazyMutex read_only_dispatch_entries_mutex_ = LAZY_MUTEX_INITIALIZER;
7758 
7759 void Isolate::InitializeBuiltinJSDispatchTable() {
7760 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7761  // Ideally these entries would be created when the read only heap is
7762  // initialized. However, since builtins are deserialized later, we need to
7763  // patch it up here. Also, we need a mutex so the shared read only heaps space
7764  // is not initialized multiple times. This must be blocking as no isolate
7765  // should be allowed to proceed until the table is initialized.
7766  base::MutexGuard guard(read_only_dispatch_entries_mutex_.Pointer());
7767  JSDispatchTable* jdt = IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table();
7768 
7769  bool needs_initialization =
7770  !V8_STATIC_DISPATCH_HANDLES_BOOL ||
7771  jdt->PreAllocatedEntryNeedsInitialization(
7772  read_only_heap_->js_dispatch_table_space(),
7773  builtin_dispatch_handle(JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::Idx::kFirst));
7774 
7775  if (needs_initialization) {
7776  std::optional<JSDispatchTable::UnsealReadOnlySegmentScope> unseal_scope;
7777  if (V8_STATIC_DISPATCH_HANDLES_BOOL) {
7778  unseal_scope.emplace(jdt);
7779  }
7780  for (JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::Idx idx =
7781  JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::kFirst;
7782  idx < JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::kCount;
7783  idx = static_cast<JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::Idx>(
7784  static_cast<int>(idx) + 1)) {
7785  Builtin builtin = JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::to_builtin(idx);
7786  DCHECK(Builtins::IsIsolateIndependent(builtin));
7787  Tagged<Code> code = builtins_.code(builtin);
7788  DCHECK(code->entrypoint_tag() == CodeEntrypointTag::kJSEntrypointTag);
7789  // TODO(olivf, 40931165): It might be more robust to get the static
7790  // parameter count of this builtin.
7791  int parameter_count = code->parameter_count();
7792 #if V8_STATIC_DISPATCH_HANDLES_BOOL
7793  JSDispatchHandle handle = builtin_dispatch_handle(builtin);
7794  jdt->InitializePreAllocatedEntry(
7795  read_only_heap_->js_dispatch_table_space(), handle, code,
7796  parameter_count);
7797 #else
7798  CHECK_LT(idx, JSBuiltinDispatchHandleRoot::kTableSize);
7799  JSDispatchHandle handle = jdt->AllocateAndInitializeEntry(
7800  read_only_heap_->js_dispatch_table_space(), parameter_count, code);
7801  isolate_data_.builtin_dispatch_table()[idx] = handle;
7802 #endif // V8_STATIC_DISPATCH_HANDLES_BOOL
7803  }
7804  }
7805 #endif
7806 }
7807 
7808 void Isolate::PrintNumberStringCacheStats(const char* comment,
7809  bool final_summary) {
7810 #define FETCH_COUNTER(name) \
7811  uint32_t name = static_cast<uint32_t>(counters()->name()->Get());
7812 
7813  FETCH_COUNTER(write_barriers)
7814  FETCH_COUNTER(number_string_cache_smi_probes)
7815  FETCH_COUNTER(number_string_cache_smi_misses)
7816  FETCH_COUNTER(number_string_cache_double_probes)
7817  FETCH_COUNTER(number_string_cache_double_misses)
7818 #undef FETCH_COUNTER
7819 
7820  PrintF("=== NumberToString cache usage stats (%s):\n", comment);
7821  if (final_summary && write_barriers == 0) {
7822  // If write barriers count is zero, then it's most likely because
7823  // builtins are compiled without --native-code-counters.
7824  PrintF(
7825  "=== WARNING: empty stats! Ensure gn args contain: "
7826  "`v8_enable_snapshot_native_code_counters = true`\n");
7827  }
7828  double smi_miss_rate =
7829  number_string_cache_smi_probes
7830  ? static_cast<double>(number_string_cache_smi_misses) /
7831  number_string_cache_smi_probes
7832  : 0;
7833 
7834  double double_miss_rate =
7835  number_string_cache_double_probes
7836  ? static_cast<double>(number_string_cache_double_misses) /
7837  number_string_cache_double_probes
7838  : 0;
7839 
7840  PrintF("=== SmiStringCache miss rate: %.6f (%d / %d)\n", //
7841  smi_miss_rate, number_string_cache_smi_misses,
7842  number_string_cache_smi_probes);
7843  PrintF("=== DoubleStringCache miss rate: %.6f (%d / %d)\n", //
7844  double_miss_rate, number_string_cache_double_misses,
7845  number_string_cache_double_probes);
7846 
7847  uint32_t smi_string_cache_capacity =
7848  factory()->smi_string_cache()->capacity();
7849  uint32_t smi_string_used_entries =
7850  factory()->smi_string_cache()->GetUsedEntriesCount();
7851 
7852  uint32_t double_string_cache_capacity =
7853  factory()->double_string_cache()->capacity();
7854  uint32_t double_string_used_entries =
7855  factory()->double_string_cache()->GetUsedEntriesCount();
7856 
7857  double smi_cache_utilization_rate =
7858  static_cast<double>(smi_string_used_entries) / smi_string_cache_capacity;
7859  double double_cache_utilization_rate =
7860  static_cast<double>(double_string_used_entries) /
7861  double_string_cache_capacity;
7862  PrintF("=== SmiStringCache utilization: %.6f (%d / %d)\n", //
7863  smi_cache_utilization_rate, smi_string_used_entries,
7864  smi_string_cache_capacity);
7865  PrintF("=== DoubleStringCache utilization: %.6f (%d / %d)\n", //
7866  double_cache_utilization_rate, double_string_used_entries,
7867  double_string_cache_capacity);
7868 
7869  if (final_summary) {
7870  PrintF("=== --smi-string-cache-size=%d\n",
7871  v8_flags.smi_string_cache_size.value());
7872  PrintF("=== --double-string-cache-size=%d\n",
7873  v8_flags.double_string_cache_size.value());
7874  }
7875  PrintF("\n");
7876 }
7877 
7878 } // namespace internal
7879 } // namespace v8
